Carol Cleveland ( born 13 January 1942 ) is a British actress and comedian , most notable for her appearances on Monty Python 's Flying Circus .

Tobias Hill ( born 30 March 1970 in London , England ) is an award - winning British poet , essayist , writer of short stories and novelist .

David Rolf ( born 1969 ) is an American labor union leader who currently serves as president of the Seattle - based Local 775 of the Service Employees International Union ( SEIU ) , which represents health care workers , and as international vice president of SEIU .
Matthew B. Brown ( 1964 -- October 5 , 2011 ) was a Latter - day Saint ( Mormon ) author and historian whose emphasis was on the history and doctrine of Joseph Smith and his successors through Brigham Young .

William Henry Wesley ( 1841 - -1922 ) was an engraver , artist , astronomer and administrator , who worked as assistant secretary of the Royal Astronomical Society from 1875 to his death in 1922 .
Frank Bateman ( 6 June 1924 -- 5 August 1991 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Annie Jennings , née Thomas ( 12 November 1884 -- 20 November 1999 ) was a British supercentenarian and the world 's second oldest living person , after American Sarah Knauss , at Jennings ' death at age 115 years 8 days .
Jackie Levy ( Hebrew : ז'קי לוי‎ , born 28 October 1960 ) is an Israeli politician who currently serves as a member of the Knesset for Likud and as Deputy Minister of Construction .
Mark Schilling ( born 1949 in Zanesville , Ohio ) is an American film critic , journalist , translator , and author based in Tokyo , Japan .
Sonja Smolec ( born 1953 ) is a Croatian artist , writer , and poet .
Eliot Weinberger ( born 6 February 1949 ) is a contemporary American writer , essayist , editor , and translator .
Helen Wu ( born 1956 ) is a martial artist living in Toronto , Canada .
Rahul Chandran ( born 1976 ) is a policy analyst working in the fields of conflict and security , widely known for his work on resilience , statebuilding and on United Nations reform .
Tal Rosner ( born in Jerusalem , 9 June 1978 ) is a London - based Israeli filmmaker and video artist .
Mickey Cantwell ( born 23 November 1964 ) is a British former boxer who was British flyweight champion in 1996 and fought for European and World titles .
Pekka Niemelä ( born 1974 in Helsinki ) is a Finnish ski jumping coach and a former ski jumper .
Wade Guyton ( born 1972 ) is a post - conceptual American artist who among other things makes digital paintings on canvas using scanners and digital inkjet technology .
Prince Manuel of Bavaria ( German : Manuel Maria Alexander Leopold Jörg Prinz von Bayern ) ( born 27 December 1972 ) is a member of the deposed Bavarian Royal House of Wittelsbach , and a cardiology researcher at Columbia University .
Peter Tufts ( 1617 -- May 13 , 1700 ) was a prominent early citizen of Medford , Massachusetts , and ancestor of Charles Tufts who donated land for the Tufts University campus .
Janet Fairbank ( 1903 -- October 6 , 1947 ) was an American operatic singer .
Shirley Gee ( b. 25 April 1932 , London , England ) is a British playwright .
Clement Booth ( born 11 May 1842 in Friskney , Lincolnshire ; died 14 July 1926 at Hundleby Grange , Spilsby , Lincolnshire ) was an English cricketer played first - class cricket between 1862 and 1886 .
Hector de Castro(1849 -- January 30 , 1909 ) was an Ottoman born American businessman and diplomat .
Stan Openshaw ( born 10 August 1946 ) is a retired British geographer .
António Calvário da Paz ( born 17 October 1938 , in Mozambique ) is a famous Portuguese singer and artist from the late 1950s and 1960s .
Adrian Coughlan ( born 1977 ) is an Irish hurler who played as a right wing - forward for the Cork senior team .
Pamela May OBE ( 30 May 1917 -- 6 June 2005 ) was a Trinidad born British dancer and teacher of classical ballet .
Albert Odulele ( born 5 January 1964 ) is a pastor , author and televangelist .
Ettore Zappi ( 1904 - -1986 ) , aka Anthony Russo , was an Italian - American Gambino crime family capo .
Salvatore Scala ( 1944 -- December 30 , 2008 ) , also known as `` Fat Sal '' and `` Uncle Sal '' , was a New York mobster who became a caporegime in the Gambino crime family .
Alice Dellal ( born 29 July 1987 ) is a Brazilian - British model of Iraqi descent .
Conrad von Pyhy ( died 1553 ) was a Swedish statesman of German descent , originally from Frankfurt am Main .
Madeline Montalban ( born Madeline Sylvia Royals ; 8 January 1910 -- 11 January 1982 ) was an English astrologer and ceremonial magician .
Alejandro Korn ( 3 May 1860 -- 9 October 1936 ) was an Argentine physician , psychiatrist , philosopher , reformist and politician .
Frans Geerts or Augustinus Franciscus Maria ( Frans ) Geerts ( Antwerp , 14 February 1869 -- Borgerhout , 30 June 1957 ) was a Belgian painter .
Erik Briand Clausen ( 24 January 1901 -- 29 March 1945 ) was a farmer and member of the Danish resistance executed by the German occupying power .
Iuput A or simply Iuput , was High Priest of Amun from 944 to 924 BCE , during the reigns of his father Shoshenq I and his brother Osorkon I. Iuput held a variety of titles including high priest of Amun , generalissimo and army - leader and Governor of Upper Egypt .
John Graham Bell ( July 12 , 1812 -- October 1899 ) was an American taxidermist and collector .
Augustus Hoppin ( 1828 - -1896 ) was an American book illustrator , born in Providence , R. I ..
Lieutenant General Sir Chandos Blair KCVO OBE MC & Bar ( 25 February 1919 -- 22 January 2011 ) was General Officer Commanding Scotland .
Abel Beach ( February 7 , 1829 -- 1899 ) , born in Groton , New York , was a well - known poet and one of the six founders of the international fraternity Theta Delta Chi .
Georgina Cecilia Mary White ( --1944 ) , better known by her pen name , Bride Broder , was a prominent Canadian journalist .
Howell Harris ( 23 January 1714 -- 21 July 1773 ) ( Welsh : Hywel Harris ) was one of the main leaders of the Welsh Methodist revival in the 18th century , along with Daniel Rowland and William Williams Pantycelyn .
Aliagha Hasanov ( Azerbaijani : Əliağa Həsənov ; 1871 - -1933 ) , also spelled as Ali Aga Hasanov , was an Azerbaijani statesman who served as Minister of Finance in the fourth cabinet of Azerbaijan Democratic Republic , and was member of Parliament of Azerbaijan .
Hugh Cuming ( 14 February 1791 -- 10 August 1865 ) was an English collector who was interested in natural history , particularly in conchology and botany .
Ingálvur av Reyni ( 18 December 1920 -- 26 November 2005 ) was the most celebrated painter of the Faroe Islands during the last years .
Jessica Ainscough ( July 1985 -- 26 February 2015 ) was an Australian cancer patient and advocate of alternative cancer treatments who went by the self - coined nickname The Wellness Warrior .
Puccio Corona ( 9 April 1942 -- 31 December 2013 ) was an Italian journalist and television presenter , whose career spanned over three decades .
Pu Chaozhu ( Chinese : 普朝柱 ) ( 1929 - -2002 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Sir Nicholas Kemeys , 1st Baronet ( before 1593 -- 25 May 1648 ) was a Welsh landowner and soldier during the English Civil War in South Wales and played a key part in events in the region during that conflict .
Cliff Padgett ( 19 December 1879 -- 7 August 1951 ) was a boat builder .
Major General Ananda Hamangoda † RWP , RSP , USP , Msc , Psc , SLA ( 1 November 1950 -- 4 July 1996 ) was the former Commanding Officer of 51 - 2 Brigade based in Jaffna .
Friedrich Gottlieb Barth ( 3 August 1738 , Wittenberg -- 6 October 1794 ) was a German philologist and writer .
Sir Thomas Pelham , 1st Baronet ( died 2 December 1624 ) was an English politician .
Stefano di Francesco ( died 1427 ) was an Italian ( Florentine ) painter , who probably died young , as he left a five - year - old son , and was outlived twenty years by his father - in - law , the painter Giuliano Pesello ( 1367 - -1446 ) .
William FitzAlan , 16th Earl of Arundel , 6th Baron Maltravers KG ( 23 November 1417 -- 1487 ) .
Akhund Abdul Ghaffur ( Pashto : اخوند عبدالغفور‎ ) , commonly known as Saidu Baba ( Pashto : سيدو بابا 1878 - 1793‎ ) , was from the Khatana Gujjar tribe settled in Swat area , and a prominent religious Mullah or priest , from Barr Swat .
Harvey Bartlett Gaul ( b. 12 Apr 1881 , Brooklyn ; d. 1 December 1945 , Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania ) was an American composer , organist , choirmaster , lecturer , music critic , and writer from Pittsburgh .
Annie Praed ( 1873 ? - 26 December 1948 ) was one of the first two women to graduate from the University of Sydney with a Licence in Dental Surgery .
James James ( also known by the bardic name Iago ap Ieuan ) ( 1833 - -1902 ) was a harpist and musician from Pontypridd , Wales .
Amory Dwight Mayo ( 31 January 1823 - 8 April 1907 ) was a Unitarian clergyman and educator .
Conrad Heyer ( 1749 - 1856 ) was an American farmer and veteran of the Revolutionary War who is notable for being the earliest - born person known to have been photographed .
James Alexander Seton ( 1816 - 2 June 1845 ) was the last British person to be killed in a duel on English soil .
Baw Beese ( c. 1790 - -c . 1850 ) was a Potawatomi Indian chief in the area of Hillsdale , Michigan until November 1840 .
Levente ( between 1010 and 1015 -- 1047 ) was a member of the House of Árpád , a great - grandson of Taksony , Grand Prince of the Hungarians .
Charles A. Hepburn ( 1891 -- 16 July 1971 ) was a Scottish businessman , a joint founder , along with Herbert Ross , of the Hepburn and Ross whisky blending company , which was the first to blend the popular Red Hackle whisky ( blended today by Lang Brothers ) .
Marea Gazzard AO , CBE ( 22 June 1928 - 28 October 2013 ) was an Australian sculptor and ceramicist .
Krishna Prasad Bhattarai ( Nepali : कृष्णप्रसाद भट्टराई ) ( 13 December 1924 -- 4 March 2011 ) was a Nepalese political leader .
Charlie Kolb ( 14 May 1907 -- 27 February 1994 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hans von Dellingshausen ( 1641 - -1705 ) was a Swedish statesman and soldier .
Tigernach mac Fócartai ( died 865 ) , also called Tigernach of Lagore , was King of Lagore .
Ghulam Mohammad Saznawaz ( died 13 February 2014 ) was the last known master of Kashmiri Sufiyana Music in the world .
James Watney junior ( 19 May 1832 -- 2 November 1886 ) was Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) for East Surrey from 1871 to 1885 .
David Jones ( 1 April 1871 -- 23 November 1899 ) who fought under the name Dai St. John was a Welsh heavyweight boxer .
Sir John Prichard - Jones , 1st Baronet ( 31 May 1841 -- 17 October 1917 ) was a self - made Welsh business man of the Victorian and Edwardian era .
Nauryzbai Batyr 1706 - 1781 , ( Kutpanbet - Uly Nauryzbai , Shaprashty Nauryzbai ) was a Khazak batyr or warrior known for fighting against the Dzungars in the Dzhungar - Kazakh wars .
August Gillhaus ( died 1932 ) was the Socialist Labor candidate for U.S. President in 1908 and for U.S. Vice President in 1912 and 1920 .
Andrew Onderdonk ( 30 August 1848 -- 21 June 1905 ) was an American construction contractor who worked on several major projects in the West , including the San Francisco seawall in California and the Canadian Pacific Railway in British Columbia .
Artur von Casimir ( 4 September 1908 - 15 December 2005 ) was a German Oberst and former bomber pilot who flew for the Luftwaffe during World War II . Since 2004 he has received a great deal of publicity in Norway .
Henri Nathansen ( 17 July 1868 -- 16 February 1944 ) was a Danish writer and stage director , today best known for the play Inside the Walls ( Danish : Indenfor Murene ) .
Prospero Ricca ( 1838 - 1895 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of snowy landscapes .
Jules Néraud ( 9 April 1795 , La Châtre -- 11 April 1855 , La Châtre ) was a French botanist , who collected spermatophytes in France , Mauritius , and Réunion , but is best known as a friend of George Sand .
Allen Abraham ( 1865 -- 9 July 1922 ; born Subramaniar Ambalavanar ) was a Ceylon Tamil academic and astronomer .
Edwin T. Baker ( 1873 - -1936 ) was a tax adviser , a government employee , a member of the California Legislature and of the Los Angeles City Council and he was active in the theater .
Captain Thomas Tyrwhitt - Drake ( 16 March 1783 - 23 March 1852 ) was a British Member of Parliament for Amersham from 1805 to 1832 .
Vasilis Logothetidis ( Greek : Βασίλης Λογοθετίδης ; 1897 -- 20 February 1960 ) was a Greek comedian .
Princess Helga - Lee of Schaumburg - Lippe ( Helga - Lee Prinzessin zu Schaumburg - Lippe , née Roderbourg ) ( Cologne 24 February 1911 -- New York 9 July 2005 ) was the wife of Prince Max of Schaumburg - Lippe ( 1898 - -1974 ) , who was a racecar driver .
Swithun Mombeshora ( August 20 , 1945 -- 2003 ) was a former Minister of Transport and Communications and Higher and Tertiary Education in Zimbabwe .
Harry Fischel ( 1865 - 1948 ) was an American businessman and philanthropist based in New York City at the turn of the 20th century .
Prince Akbar Mass'oud ( or Akbar Mirza Sarem - ed - Dowleh ) ( 1885- 29 November 1975 ) was Persian Prince and a member of Qajar Dynasty , son of Mass'oud Mirza Zell - e Soltan and grand son of Nasser al - Din Shah Qajar .
Jonathan Barry Boyle ( 21 October 1944 -- 7 August 1999 ) was an Australian professional wrestler who is known worldwide under the name `` Lord '' Jonathan Boyd .
Schalk Verhoef ( 5 August 1935 -- 18 January 1997 ) was a Dutch cyclist who won a bronze medal in the road race at the 1957 UCI Road World Championships .
Carlotta Grisi ( born Caronne Adele Josephine Marie Grisi ; 28 June 1819 -- 20 May 1899 ) was an Italian ballet dancer .
Lawrence Dalton ( died 13 December 1561 ) was an officer of arms at the College of Arms in London .
Hugh Sykes Davies ( 1909 -- 1984 ) was an English poet , novelist and communist who was one of a small group of 1930s British surrealists .

George Campbell Ross C.B. , C.B.E. ( 9 August 1900 -- 30 July 1993 ) was an Engineer and a Rear Admiral in Britain 's Royal Navy .
Guttormur Andrasson , died 1572 in Bergen , was , from 1544 to 1572 , First Minister of the Faroe Islands .
Odd Højdahl ( 5 January 1921 -- 23 February 1994 ) is a Norwegian trade unionist and politician for the Labour Party .
William Stanley Russell Thomas ( 1896 -- 21 March 1957 ) was a physician , barrister and Welsh Liberal politician who served as a Liberal National Member of Parliament .
Arthur Loftus Tottenham ( 5 April 1838 -- 4 December 1887 ) was a landowner and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1880 to 1887 .
Richard C. H. Lenski ( September 14 , 1864 in Greifenberg , Brandenburg - Prussia ( now Gryfice , Poland ) -- 1936 ) was a German - born American - naturalized Lutheran scholar , and author , who published a series of Lutheran New Testament commentaries ( some of the volumes were published after his death ) .
Edward Shirley Kennedy ( usually known as E. S. Kennedy ) ( 1817 - -1898 ) was an English mountaineer and author , and a founding member of the Alpine Club .
Ketema Yifru ( 12 December 1929 - 14 January 1994 ) was a prominent Ethiopian diplomat and politician .
John Martin ( born John Martin Scripps , 9 December 1959 -- 19 April 1996 ) was an English spree killer who murdered three tourists--
Air Marshal William Ross MacBrien , OBE , CD , RCAF ( 1913 - -1986 ) , commonly known as Bill MacBrien or Iron Bill , was a senior Royal Canadian Air Force officer during World War II and a senior commander in the 1950s and 60s .
Septimus Winner ( 11 May 1827 -- 22 November 1902 ) was an American songwriter of the 19th century .
Ashley Foley ( 27 December 1915 -- 20 February 2005 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Robert Munro , 5th Baronet of Foulis ( died 11 September 1729 ) was also 23rd Baron and 26th chief of the Clan Munro .
Johann Rufinatscha ( 1 October 1812 -- 25 May 1893 ) was an Austrian composer , theorist and music teacher .
St. Nicodemus of Palermo ( died 1083 ) was a Sicilian Orthodox bishop .
Marie Eleonore of Dietrichstein ( 1 January 1623 -- 20 March 1687 ) , was a German noblewoman by birth member of the House of Dietrichstein and by her two marriage Countess of Kaunitz and Oppersdorf .

Adolf Bötticher or Adolf Boetticher ( 12 December 1842 -- 9 June 1901 ) was a German art historian and conservator .
Alonso de Molina ( 1513 or 1514 -- 1579 or 1585 ) was a Franciscan priest and grammarian , who wrote a well - known dictionary of the Nahuatl language published in 1571 and still used by scholars working on Nahuatl texts in the tradition of the New Philology .
John George Cochrane ( 1781 - -1852 ) was a Scottish editor and bibliographer , also a librarian , with a general knowledge of literary history .
Ottone Hamerani ( 1694 - -1768 ) , also known as Otto Hamerani , was an Italian medallist .
Emanuel Aromaa ( 27 February 1873 , Teisko - 14 January 1933 ; surname until 1894 Sylgren ) was a Finnish shoemaker and politician .
Walter Hayle Walshe ( 1812 - -1892 ) was an Irish physician , a pioneer in the study of cancer with his discovery that malignant cells can be recognised under a microscope .
Ioannis Malokinis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Μαλοκίνης , 1880 -- 1942 ) was a Greek swimmer .
Darcy Conyers ( 1919 - -1973 ) was a British screenwriter , actor , producer and film director .
Millard F. Malin ( 1891 - -1974 ) was an American sculptor most noted for his statues of the Angel Moroni such as the one on the Los Angeles Temple .
Major Moses Van Campen ( 1757 - -1849 ) was a soldier during the American Revolutionary War .
Östen Mäkitalo ( 27 August 1938 -- 16 June 2011 ) was a Swedish electrical engineer .
Zygmunt Marek ( born March 17 , 1872 in Kraków , died 1931 in Kraków ) was a Polish socialist politician .
Deborah Anapol died unexpectedly in England on 18 August 2015 .
Dillard Chandler ( April 16 , 1907 -- January 1992 ) was an American Appalachian Folk singer from Madison County , North Carolina .
Sir William Sambach ( died 1653 ) was an English - born lawyer and politician of the seventeenth century who spent much of his career in Ireland , but was driven back to England by the political turmoil of the 1640s , and died there .
Lorina Bulwer ( 1838 -- 5 March 1912 ) was a British needleworker .
Salomón Hakim Dow ( 4 June 1922 -- 5 May 2011 ) was a Colombian neurosurgeon , researcher , and inventor .
Karl Gustaf Lennart Moberg ( 26 December 1918 -- 5 February 1991 ) was a Swedish triple jumper .

Thomas Rosling Howlett ( 1827 - 1898 ) was a Baptist pastor and early proponent of British Israelism .
Sir Walter de la Pole ( November 1371 -- 1434 ) , of Dernford in Sawston , Cambridgeshire , was an English politician .
Donald James ( born Donald James Wheal ; 22 August 1931 - -28 April 2008 ) was a British television writer , novelist and non - fiction writer .
Rafael Bernal ( 28 June 1915 -- 17 September 1972 ) was a Mexican diplomat and novelist , best known for his crime novels , particularly The Mongolian Conspiracy .
William Haslam ( 2 April 1850 -- 7 May 1898 ) was a small businessman and politician in the colony of South Australia .
Kishen Singh Kapoor ( 1873 - -1936 ) was a mathematician , author and a teacher .
Hare Pomare ( ? --1864 ) was of Māori descent and identified with the Ngāpuhi and Ngati Manu iwi .
John Neville , 3rd Baron Neville de Raby , KG c.1337 -- 17 October 1388 ) was an English peer and soldier .
Salih al - Ja'fari ( 1910 - -1979 ) was a Sufi and scholar , who lived and taught in Cairo , Egypt .
Anne Lykke ( April 30 , 1595 -- 1641 ) was a Danish noblewoman and royal mistress of Christian , Prince Elect of Denmark .
Aleksandar Đokić ( Cyrillic : Александар Ђокић ) ( 28 December 1936 - -22 May 2002 ) was a Serbian architect who gained fame for his original designs created in the Brutalist and postmodernist styles .
Carlota Matienzo Román ( 1881 , Barcelona -- 1926 ) was a Puerto Rican teacher and feminist .
Charles Schreyvogel ( January 4 , 1861 -- January 27 , 1912 ) was an American painter of Western subject matter in the days of the disappearing frontier .
Hans Henkemans ( The Hague , 23 December 1913 -- Nieuwegein , 29 December 1995 ) was a Dutch pianist , teacher , composer of classical music and psychiatrist .
Fede Galizia ( 1578 - -1630 ) was an Italian Renaissance painter , a pioneer of the still life genre .
Henry Jenkes ( died 1697 ) , was a Gresham Professor of Rhetoric .
Isobel Schenk , BEM ( 1898 - -1980 ) was a Christian missionary who worked for many years alongside her husband , Rev. Rodolphe Samuel Schenk ( 1888 - -1969 ) , at the Mount Margaret Mission in Western Australia .
Pauline Léon ( 28 September 1768 -- 5 October 1838 ) , was a radical organizer and feminist during the French Revolution .
Zhang Hanzhi ( Chinese : 章含之 ; pinyin : Zhāng Hánzhī ; Wade -- Giles : Chang Han - chih ; 1935 -- 26 January 2008 ) was a Chinese diplomat who was Mao Zedong 's English tutor and U.S. President Richard Nixon 's interpreter during his historic 1972 trip to China .
Fan Zhi ( 范質 ) ( c. 911 -- 5 November 964 ) was a civil official who served under 12 emperors of 6 dynasties during imperial China 's Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period and the subsequent Song Dynasty .
Prosper Garnot ( 13 January 1794 -- 8 October 1838 ) was a French surgeon and naturalist .

Arvid Olsson ( born 1888 , died 1958 , Stockholm ) was a Swedish politician and trade unionist .

Heidi Bucher ( 1926 - -1993 ) was a Swiss artist interested in exploring architectural space and the body through sculpture .
John Wickham Legg ( 28 December 1843 -- 28 October 1921 ) was the third son of the printer and bookseller George Legg , and was born at Alverstoke near Portsmouth in Hampshire , England , on 28 December 1843 .
Bishop Thomas Joseph Power BA ( Lon ) MA ( Lon ) ( 1830 - -1893 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic Bishop .
Pablo Dreyfus ( 1969/70 -- 1 June 2009 ) was an Argentine arms control expert that worked in South America , particularly Brazil , to help end the illegal weapons trade prevalent in South America .
John Wesley Etheridge ( 24 February 1804 -- 24 May 1866 ) was an English nonconformist minister and scholar .
Abu al - Abbas Ahmad II ( reigned 1370 - -1394 ) was an Hafsid Caliph of Ifriqiya .
Robert Stricker ( born 16 August 1879 , Brno , d. 1944 , Auschwitz ) was a Jewish Austrian politician .
Sarah Rachel Russell or Leverson or Levison , best known as Madame Rachel ( died 12 October 1880 ) was a British criminal and con artist in Victorian - era London during the late 19th century .
Len Richardson ( 10 February 1891 -- 7 April 1924 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Eric Thornton ( 5 July 1882 -- 5 December 1945 ) was a British - born Belgian football player who competed in the 1900 Olympic Games .
Aleksandr Verzhbilovich died in the city of his birth on 15 March 1911 ( ns ) , aged 61 .
Admiral Sir William Henry Dillon Kt KCH ( 8 August 1779 - 9 September 1857 ) was a British naval officer .
Tryphosa Bates - Batcheller ( April 14 , 1876 - -1952 ) , born Tryphosa Duncan Bates , was an American socialite , club woman and concert singer .
Joannes Seyve ( 1900 - -1966 ) was a French biochemist who often used Seibel wine grape hybrids produced in 1860s .
Sir Mitchell Mitchell - Thomson , 1st Baronet ( 5 December 1846 -- 15 November 1918 ) was a Lord Provost of Edinburgh .
Malcolm Henry Ellis , CMG ( 21 August 1890 -- 18 January 1969 ) was an Australian journalist , historian , critic , reviewer and staunch anti - communist .
Tiryaki Hasan Pasha ( Turkish ) ; also called Alacaatlı Hasan Pasha ( 1530 ? -- 1611 ) , was a commander of the Ottoman army during the early 17th century .
Himmatsinhji M. K. ( 9 October 1928 -- 22 February 2008 ) was a noted ornithologist , politician and scion of the erstwhile Jadeja ruling family of Kutch .
William of Maleval ( or William the Great ) ( died 10 February 1157 ) was the founder of the Catholic congregation of Williamites , a branch of the Hermits of St. Augustine .
Chubby Oates born Arthur Oates ( 23 December 1942 -- 10 November 2006 ) was a Cockney clubland comic and character actor .
Lieven Ferdinand de Beaufort ( March 23 , 1879 in Den Treek , Leusden -- 11 May 1968 in Amersfoort ) was a Dutch biologist who , in 1903 , participated in the North New Guinea Expedition .
Kabita Sinha , ( b. Kolkata,1931 - -1999 ) , Bengali poet , novelist , feminist and radio director .
Henry Thingstad ( 9 April 1916 -- 19 May 1943 ) was a Norwegian sports official and communist resistance member .
Krishna II ( 878 - -914 CE ) ascended the Rashtrakuta throne after the demise of his famous father Amoghavarsha I. His Kannada name was Kannara .
Jack Hargreaves OBE ( 31 December 1911 in London -- 15 March 1994 ) was an English television presenter and writer .
Martin Eichler ( 29 March 1912 -- 7 October 1992 ) was a German number theorist .
Else Mayer ( 1891 - -1962 ) was a German nun and women 's liberation activist during the period of the First - wave feminism .
Tamara Danz ( 14 December 1952 -- 22 July 1996 ) was the lead singer and lyricist of the East German rock group Silly .
Alfred Hart Everett ( 11 October 1848 -- 18 June 1898 ) was a British civil servant and administrator in Borneo as well as being a naturalist and natural history collector .
George Toogood Smith ( 1903 -- 5 June 1955 ) was the maternal uncle , through marriage , of John Lennon .
Charles Corri ( c.1862 -- 8 June 1941 ) was an English musician , conductor and arranger .
Rasoul Mollagholipour ( also spelt Rasool Mollagholi Poor , 1955 -- 6 March 2007 ) was an Iranian film director , screenwriter , and cinematographer .
Anna Salome of Manderscheid - Blankenheim ( 12 December 1628 -- 15 March 1691 ) was Abbess of Thorn Abbey from 1648 to 1688 , and the abbess of Essen Abbey from 1688 until her death .
Júlio Prates de Castilhos ( Cruz Alta , 29 June 1860 -- Porto Alegre , 24 October 1903 ) was a Brazilian journalist and politician .
Sepp Daxenberger ( 10 April 1962 -- 18 August 2010 ) was a German Green Party politician .
Chen Wen - Yu ( 20 November 1925 -- 7 December 2012 ) , ( simplified Chinese : 陈文郁 ; traditional Chinese : 陳文郁 ) was a Taiwanese botanist , horticulturist and an inventor in agriculture science .
Louis van Praag ( 1926 - -1993 ) was a British fashion and industrial designer , described as an influence on a generation of British designers from the 1960s onward .
Henk Nijdam ( 26 August 1935 -- 30 April 2009 ) was a Dutch road and track cyclist .
Lubaba bint al - Harith ( Arabic : لبابة بنت الحارث‎ ) ( c.593 - 655 ) , also known as Umm Fadl , was a prominent early Muslim .
Philip Sherman ( 1611 - -1687 ) was a prominent leader and one of the founding settlers of Portsmouth in the Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations .
Minoru Miki ( 三木 稔 Miki Minoru ) ( 16 March 1930 -- 8 December 2011 ) was a Japanese composer and artistic director , particularly known for his promotional activities in favor of Japanese ( as well as Chinese and Korean ) traditional instruments and some of their performers .
Marius Bunescu ( 14 May 1881 -- 31 March 1971 ) was a Romanian painter , organizer of the National Museum of Art , and director of the Anastase Simu Museum .
Julius Moser ( 8 Novbember 1863 -- 4 July 1929 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in beetles .
Mpisekhaya Ngangomhlaba Sigcawu was the 9th paramount chief of the Gcaleka sub - group of the Xhosa nation from 1923 to the 2 June 1933 .
Rickard Deasy PC ( 1812 -- 6 May 1883 ) was an Irish lawyer and judge .
Lois Dwight Cole Taylor ( 1903 -- 20 July 1979 ) was an American editor and children 's author .
Hans Andrias Djurhuus ( 20 October 1883 - 6 May 1951 ) was a Faroese poet and teacher .
Tsegmidiin Namsraijav ( Mongolian : Цэгмидийн Намсрайжав ; 1927 - 1987 ) was a Mongolian composer .
Major Hiram Mills ( c. 1796 - -1882 ) was an American - born philanthropist .
Daniel Tinayre ( 14 September 1910 -- 24 October 1994 ) was a French - born Argentine film director , screenwriter and film producer .
Carl - Herman Tillhagen ( December 17 , 1906 - 28 May 2002 ) was a Swedish folklorist and ethnologist who did extensive research on Scandinavian folklore .
Wu - chi Liu ( traditional Chinese : 柳無忌 ; simplified Chinese : 柳无忌 ; pinyin : Liǔ Wújì ; Wade -- Giles : Liu Wu - chi ; 1907 -- 3 October 2002 ) was a scholar of Chinese literature and writer .
Amédée Jacques ( 4 July 1813 - 13 October 1865 ) , often known as Amadeo , was a Franco - Argentine pedagogue and philosopher and one of the most prestigious educators of his time .
Mieczysław Wilczek ( 25 January 1932 -- 30 April 2014 ) was a Polish politician , chemist and businessman who was Minister of Industry ( 1988 - 1989 ) .
Donald Dempsey Sr . ( c. 1932 -- 27 January 2005 ) was an American recording executive who helped launch Ozzy Osbourne and Merle Haggard .
Zhang Qinlin ( 1888 - -1967 ) was an influential martial artist , teacher , and lineage holder of the Yangjia Michuan ( Yang family hidden tradition ) style of t’ai chi ch’uan .
James Freeburn ( 1808 -- 5 August 1876 ) was a Scottish engineer , inventor and industrial designer .
Derek Senior ( 4 May 1912 -- 6 December 1988 ) was a British freelance writer principally known for being a member of the Royal Commission on Local Government in England , chaired by Lord Redcliffe - Maud .
Otto von Rosen ( 11 May 1884 -- 26 May 1963 ) was a Swedish military officer and sport shooter .
Peter Crockaert ( c. 1465 - -1514 ) , known as Peter of Brussels , was a Flemish scholastic philosopher .
Dr. Cecile O'Rahilly ( Irish : Sisile Ní Rathaille , born 17 December 1894 , Listowel , County Kerry , Ireland ; died 2 May 1980 ) was a scholar of the Celtic languages .
Gottlieb Wilhelm Leitner or Gottlieb William Leitner M.A. , Ph.D. , L.L.D. , D.O.L. ( 14 October 1840 -- 22 March 1899 ) was a British orientalist .
Robert John Hopper , FSA ( 1910 -- 3 July 1987 ) , known as R. J. Hopper , was an archaeologist and historian of Ancient Greece .
Alexander Colquhoun - Stirling - Murray - Dunlop ( 27 December 1798 -- 1 September 1870 ) was a Scottish church lawyer and Liberal Party politician .
Jan František Beckovský ( 18 August 1658 -- 26 December 1722 ) , was a Czech historian , writer , translator , and priest .
Kalle Jalkanen ( 10 May 1907 in Suonenjoki - 5 September 1941 in Kirjasalo ) was a Finnish cross - country skier who competed in the late 1930s .
Rt Hon . John William Wilson , PC JP ( 22 October 1858 -- 18 June 1932 ) was a British chemical manufacturer and politician who served for 27 years as a member of parliament ( MP ) , initially as Liberal Unionist and then as a Liberal .
John `` Jack '' Andrew Davey ( 8 February 1907 -- 14 October 1959 ) , known as Jack Davey , was a New Zealand - born singer and pioneering star of Australian radio in the 1930s , ' 40s and ' 50s .
Father Georgy Kossov ( Russian : Георгий Коссов ) also known as Yegor Chekryakovsky ( Егор Чекряковский , literally Yegor of Chekryak , Yegor being a simplified form of Georgy ; 4 April 1855 -- April 1928 ) was a Russian Orthodox priest and a starets .
William Walter Keeton ( 30 April 1905 -- 10 October 1980 ) was an English cricketer who played in two Tests in 1934 and 1939 .
George Emlen Roosevelt ( 1887 - -1963 ) a banker and philanthropist , was a first cousin once - removed of U.S. President Theodore Roosevelt and one of the most prominent railroad financiers of his day , involved in no fewer than 14 railroad reorganizations .
Maharaja Jawahar Singh ( r. 1763 -- 1768 ) ( Hindi : महाराजा जवाहर सिंह ) was a ruling Maharaja of the Bharatpur State .
Jim Caffery ( 7 May 1872 -- 8 June 1918 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frank Armington ( 1876 - -1941 ) was a Canadian born and raised artist who lived most of his adult life in France .
Radivoj of Bosnia ( Serbo - Croatian : Radivoj Ostojić/Радивој Остојић ; died in late May or early June 1463 ) was anti - king of Bosnia from 1432 until 1435 , when he lost all control over the kingdom but did not relinquish the title , and again from 1443 until 1446 , when he abandoned his claim .
Ada Cambridge ( 21 November 1844 -- 19 July 1926 ) , later known as Ada Cross , was an English - born Australian writer .
Hugo Pesce ( 17 June 1900 -- 26 July 1969 ) was a Peruvian physician and left - wing activist .
John Holden Greene ( born 1777 Warwick , Rhode Island ; died 1850 Providence , Rhode Island ) was a noted early 19th century Federal Period architect practicing in Providence , Rhode Island .
Philip Crosbie Morrison ( 19 December 1900 -- 1 March 1958 ) , generally known as `` Crosbie Morrison '' , was an Australian naturalist , educator , journalist , broadcaster and conservationist .
Moses Carter ( 1801 - -1860 ) , known as ' The Histon Giant ' , was a strongman who lived in the village of Histon , near Cambridge in the United Kingdom .
Kalyan Mitter ( Bengali : কল্যাণ মিত্র ; 5 May 1936 -- 16 August 2013 ) was an Indian first - class cricketer , coach and curator .
Gordon M. Graham ( 1918 - 2008 ) was a United States Air Force Lieutenant General .
Vlastimil Opálek ( born 7 February 1959 in Trnava - died 5 October 1995 ) was a Slovak football goalkeeper .
John Kenneth Pennington ( 1927 - -25 August 2011 ) was a priest in the Church of England , Nottingham City councillor and Sheriff of Nottingham .
Ofelia Irene Grabowski Edery ( 10 September 1936 -- 16 June 1983 ) , commonly known as Ofelia Montesco , was a Peruvian actress who is best remembered for her roles in cinema and television of Mexico .
Guo Wei ( 郭威 ) ( 10 September 904 -- 22 February 954 ) , also known by his temple name Taizu ( 太祖 ) , was the founding emperor of imperial China 's short - lived Later Zhou during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period , reigning from 951 until his death .
Maria Stein , CBE ( Maria Donata Nanetta Paulina Gustava Erwina Wilhelmine ; 18 October 1926 -- 6 March 2014 ) , known as Marion Stein , and later by marriage as Marion Harewood and Marion Thorpe , was an Austrian - born British concert pianist .
Felicia Sanders ( c. 1922 -- February 7 , 1975 ) was a singer of traditional pop music .
Michael Linning , Writer to the Signet WS ( 24 September 1774 - 17 February 1838 ) was a Scottish solicitor who wrote The First Book of Napoleon .
Martín Yanzón ( 1799 -- 29 July 1842 ) was an Argentine soldier and caudillo who died fighting against the supporters of the dictator Juan Manuel de Rosas .
Rudolf Burkert ( 31 October 1904 -- 7 June 1985 ) was an Ethnic German Czechoslovak Nordic skier who competed in the 1920s and 1930s .
Georgie White Clark ( 1911 - -1992 ) was a river - running guide in the Grand Canyon .
Sonnie Hale ( 1 May 1902 -- 9 June 1959 ) was an English theatre and cinema actor and director .
Theodoor Verstraete , also spelled Theodor Verstraete and Théodore Verstraete ( 5 January 1850 -- 8 January 1907 ) was a Belgian Realist painter and printmaker who is known for his landscapes depicting life in the countryside as well as his paintings of the Belgian coastal landscape .
Dionysius the Philosopher ( Greek : Διονύσιος ὁ Φιλόσοφος ; ca . 1560 -- 1611 ) was a Greek monk who led two farmer revolts against the Ottoman Turks .
Edward Pomeroy Barrett - Lennard ( 19 June 1799 in England -- 29 June 1878 in Upper Swan , Western Australia ) was an early settler in the Guildford area of Western Australia and later with his nephew Edmund Thomas Barrett - Lennard , the founder of the well known Western Australian Beverley family .
Joseph Wechsberg ( 29 August 1907 -- 10 April 1983 ) was a Jewish Czech writer , journalist , musician , and gourmet .
Lorenzo Antonetti ( 31 July 1922 -- 10 April 2013 ) was a Cardinal in the Catholic Church , who held several positions in the Vatican diplomatic service .
Henry William Weber ( 1783 - -1818 ) was an English editor of plays and romances and literary assistant of Sir Walter Scott .
Kristian Strøm ( 24 December 1892 -- 10 November 1980 ) was a Norwegian speedskater .
Gillacommain mac Niall ( died 991 ) was king of Uí Díarmata .
Archibald Campbell , 5th Earl of Argyll ( 1532/1537 -- 12 September 1573 ) was one of the leading figures in the politics of Scotland during the reign of Mary , Queen of Scots , and the early part of that of James VI .
Louis Roeder ( 1835 - -1915 ) was a member of the governing body of Los Angeles , California , in the 19th Century , who rose from being a pioneer blacksmith and carriage maker to one of the wealthiest landowners in the city .
Jean - Baptiste Cervoni ( 29 August 1765 -- 22 April 1809 ) became a general officer in the French army during the French Revolutionary Wars and was killed in action in 1809 during the Napoleonic Wars .
Sir Frederick Augusta Barnard KCH FRS ( 1 September 1743 -- 27 January 1830 ) was principal librarian to George III during much of the British King 's reign .
Rudolph Karl Alexander Schneider , commonly known as Sascha Schneider ( 21 September 1870 -- 18 August 1927 ) , was a German painter and sculptor .
Gaston La Touche , or de La Touche ( 24 October 1854 - 12 July 1913 ) was a French painter , illustrator , engraver and sculptor .
Elfed Morris ( 9 June 1942 -- 4 November 2013 ) was a Welsh professional footballer .
William Frank Calderon aka W. Frank Calderon ( 1865 , London - 21 April 1943 ) , was an English Victorian painter of portraits , landscapes , figure subjects and sporting pictures .
Frederick II of Isenburg - Covern ( German : Friedrich II . von Isenburg - Covern ) was the Count of Isenburg - Covern from 1272 until 1277 .
William Asplin ( 1686/7 - -1758 ) was a British writer , theologian , and churchman .
Robert de Mowbray ( died 1125 ) , a Norman , was Earl of Northumbria from 1086 , until 1095 , when he was deposed for rebelling against William Rufus , King of England .
Ary Bitter ( 1883 - -1973 ) was a French artist , best known for his animal sculptures .
Sir John Elwill , 1st Baronet ( c. 1640 -- 25 April 1717 ) was an English aristocrat and politician .
Sir John Perrot ( 7 - -11 November 1528 -- 3 November 1592 ) served as Lord Deputy to Queen Elizabeth I of England during the Tudor conquest of Ireland .
Konstantinos Typaldos - Alfonsatos ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Τυπάλδος-Αλφονσάτος , 1873 - -1945 ) was a Greek Navy officer .
William Robert Broughton ( 22 March 1762 -- 14 March 1821 ) was a British naval officer in the late 18th century .
Lieutenant Colonel Wilfrith Elstob VC , DSO , MC ( 8 September 1888 -- 21 March 1918 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Zhang Chun ( died c. 189 ) was a rebel leader during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Karl Schönherr ( 24 February 1867 - 15 March 1943 ) was an Austrian writer of Austrian Heimat themes .
Wenceslaus III of Oława ( Polish : Wacław III oławski ) ( 1400 -- between 14 January and 28 May 1423 ) , was a Duke of Oława ( Ohlau ) since 1419/20 until his death .
Betty Jumel ( 1901 -- 14 October 1990 ) was a British variety hall entertainer and actress .
Elzada Clover ( 1897 - -1980 ) was an American botanist who was the first to catalog plant life in the Grand Canyon on the Colorado River .
Julius Stafford Baker ( 1869 - -1961 ) was an English cartoonist .
King Andriantsimitoviaminandriandehibe ( `` the noble without equal among great nobles '' ) was the King of Imerina in the central highlands of Madagascar from 1650 to 1670 .
Norzang ( 1403 - -1466 ) , in full Norbu Zangpo ( Wylie : Nor bu bzang po ) , was the founder of the power of the Rinpungpa Dynasty in Central Tibet .
Kenneth Tempest DFC ( 9 April 1922 -- 2 June 2015 ) was a Royal Air Force navigator with 139 Squadron during the Second World War flying Mosquitos .
Kim Yuk ( Hangul : 김육 ; Hanja : 金堉 ; 1570 -- September 1658 ) was a Korean Neo - Confucian scholar , politician and writer of the Korean Joseon Dynasty .
Albrecht Becker ( 14 November 1906 -- 22 April 2002 ) was a production designer , photographer , and actor , who was imprisoned by the Nazi regime for the charge of homosexuality .
Tommaso Laureti , often called Tommaso Laureti Siciliano ( c. 1530 -- 22 September 1602 ) , was an Italian painter from Sicily who trained in the atelier of the aged Sebastiano del Piombo and worked in Bologna .
Ann Lancaster ( 5 May 1920 - 31 October 1970 ) was a well - known character actress who appeared in many British films , television shows and in theatre .
Arthur Doherty ( 19 January 1932 - 6 February 2003 ) was a nationalist politician in Ireland .
Terrell Croft ( 1880 - -1967 ) was an American engineer and author of technical books on electrical and mechanical subjects , most or all of which were published by McGraw - Hill .
Gilla na Naemh Ua Duinn ( 1102 -- 17 December 1160 ) was an Irish poet , historian , and cleric .
Junnosuke Ofusa ( 1908 - -1994 ) was the first journalist ever to receive Japan 's Order of the Sacred Treasure .
Sybil Elgar ( 10 June 1914 -- 8 January 2007 ) was a pioneer in the education and care of both children and adults with autism .
Brendan Bracken , 1st Viscount Bracken , PC ( 15 February 1901 -- 8 August 1958 ) , was an Irish - born businessman and a minister in the British Conservative cabinet .
Kathleen Dalziel ( 1881 - 1969 ) was an Australian writer who was born in Durban , South Africa in 1881 .
Alfred Lansing ( July 21 , 1921 -- 1975 ) was an American journalist and writer , best known for his book Endurance ( 1959 ) , an account of Ernest Shackleton 's Antarctic explorations .
Ludwig Fahrenkrog ( 20 October 1867 -- 27 October 1952 ) was a German writer , playwright and artist .
Andreas Bang - Haas ( 6 December 1846 -- 7 February 1925 ) was a Danish entomologist and insect dealer .
Theodor Estermann ( 5 February 1902 -- 29 November 1991 ) was a mathematician , working in the field of analytic number theory .
David Erskine , Lord Dun ( 1670 - -1758 ) , was a Scottish advocate , judge and commissioner to parliament .
Edward Carleton Tufnell ( 27 October 1806 , Marylebone , London ( then part of Middlesex ) -- 3 July 1886 Belgravia , London ) was a civil servant and educationist .
Sir James Dundas , Lord Arniston ( died 1679 ) was a Scottish politician and judge .
Edward Percy Hallam ( 1887 - -1957 ) ( also Edwin ) was an English cathedral organist , who served in St Edmundsbury Cathedral .
Marie Popelin ( 17 September 1846 -- 5 June 1913 ) was a Belgian feminist , lawyer and political campaigner .
Riad Shehata ( Arabic : رياض شحاتة‎ ) ( died in 1942 ) was an Egyptian photographer .
Theobald Butler , 3rd Chief Butler of Ireland ( c.1224- December 26 1248 ) was 6 years old when his father , Theobald died .
John Campbell , 3rd Earl of Breadalbane and Holland KB ( 10 March 1696 -- 26 January 1782 ) , styled Lord Glenorchy from 1716 until 1752 , was a Scottish nobleman , diplomat and politician .
Eille Norwood ( born Anthony Edward Brett , 11 October 1861 - 24 December 1948 ) was an English actor who spent most of his screen career playing Sherlock Holmes .
Major General Syed Ali Nawab ( Urdu : سید علی نواب‎ ; 10 June 1925 -- 23 September 1994 ) , was a career officer of the Pakistan Army Corps of Electrical and Mechanical Engineering ( EME ) .
Raja Ghazanfar Ali Khan ( 16 August 1895 - 1963 ) was born in Pind Dadan Khan , a town in Jhelum district , British India .
Muiris Ó Begléighinn , Irish physician , died 1528 .
Major General James Wolfe ( 2 January 1727 -- 13 September 1759 ) was a British army officer , known for his training reforms but remembered chiefly for his victory over the French at the Battle of the Plains of Abraham in Canada in 1759 .
Árni beiskur ( or Árni the Bitter ) ( died 22 October 1253 ) was an Icelander .
Teferra Wolde - Semait ( 1938 - -2013 ) , ( Ge'ez : ተፈራ ወልደሰማዕት ) was an Ethiopian government official .
Reinhard Döhl ( 16 September 1934 -- 29 May 2004 ) was a German writer and scholar in the fields of literature and media studies , also remembered as a poet and artist .
Ernst Johann Schmitz ( 18 May 1845 -- 3 December 1922 ) was a German naturalist , ornithologist , entomologist and Roman Catholic priest who settled in Madeira in the late 1870s , serving as vice chancellor of the Funchal Seminary from 1891 to 1898 , and again from 1902 to 1908 , becoming a naturalised Portuguese citizen .
Marius Sandvei ( 15 January 1905 -- 1 November 1993 ) was a Norwegian linguist , educator and language politician .
Tsarevna Natalya Alexeyevna of Russia ( 22 August 1673 -- 18 June 1716 ) was a Russian playwright .
Émile Metz ( 23 February 1835 - 13 February 1904 ) was a Luxembourgish politician , industrialist and engineer .
Sir Howard Dalton , FRS ( 8 February 1944 -- 12 January 2008 ) was a British microbiologist .
Nevins Selvadurai ( Tamil : நெவின்ஸ் செல்வதுரை ; 15 October 1863 -- 28 April 1938 ) was a Ceylon Tamil teacher , principal of Jaffna Hindu College and a member of the State Council of Ceylon .
Nathaniel Mist ( died 30 September 1737 ) was an 18th - century British printer and journalist whose Mist 's Weekly Journal was the central , most visible , and most explicit opposition newspaper to the whig administrations of Robert Walpole .
Laureana Wright de Kleinhans ( 1846 - 1896 ) ( also known as Laurena ) was a Mexican writer and feminist pioneer .
Elizabeth Pain ( c. 1652 -- 26 November 1704 ) , sometimes spelled Elizabeth Paine or Elisabeth Payne , was a settler in colonial Boston who was brought to trial after the death of her child .
William Heather ( c. 1563 -- 1627 ) was a musician , and founder of the position of the Heather Professor of Music at the University of Oxford .
Kwesi Brew ( Osborne Henry ) ( 1928 -- 30 July 2007 ) was a Ghanaian poet .
Carron Clementina ( November 21 , 1823 -- April 1912 ) was the granddaughter of Count Carron Giovanni .
Lewis Wade Jones ( March 13 , 1910 -- September 1979 ) was a sociologist and teacher .
Dr John Archibald Venn , CMG FSA JP ( 10 November 1883 -- 15 March 1958 ) , was a British economist .
Denis Anthony Brian Butler , 9th Earl of Lanesborough ( 28 October 1918 -- 27 December 1998 ) was an Irish aristocrat .
Thomas Hinds Duggan ( 20 April 1815 -- 26 December 1865 ) was an early Texas settler and two - time Texas State Senator from Guadalupe County , Texas .
Wallerant Vaillant ( 30 May 1623 -- 28 August 1677 ) was a painter of the Dutch Golden Age and one of the first artists to use the mezzotint technique , which he probably helped to develop .
Lorin Blodget ( born in Chautauqua County , New York , May 23 , 1823 - 1901 ) , American physicist and writer .
Arthur Laing , PC ( 9 September 1904 -- 13 February 1975 ) was a Canadian politician .
Júlio Francisco António Adeodato Barreto ( 3 December 1905 -- 6 August 1937 ) , better known as Adeodato Barreto , was a Luso - Goan poet and writer .
Gopaler Ma ( translation : Mother of Gopala , an epithet for Sri Krishna ) ( 1822 -- 8 July 1906 ) was a devotee and a householder disciple of Sri Ramakrishna , the saint and mystic from Bengal .
Eugénie Cotton ( 13 October 1881 -- 16 June 1967 ) was a French scientist and Women 's rights activist .
Alexander von Suchten ( c. 1520 in Dirschau ( Tczew ) or Danzig ( Gdańsk ) -- 7 November 1575 in Linz ) was an alchemist , doctor and writer .
Mina Fonda Ochtman ( 1862 - -1924 ) was an American Impressionist painter noted for her watercolors of landscapes and coastal scenes .
William M. Grace ( September 10 , 1934 -- 2004 ) was a building developer who played an important role in bringing casinos to the Midwest .
Dongchu ( Chinese : 東初 ; pinyin : Dōngchū , 1907 - -1977 ) was a Chinese Ch'an Master in Mainland China and later in Taiwan , and also the teacher of respected modern - day Ch'an Master Sheng - yen .
Gaston Moch ( 1859 - -1935 ) was the secretary of the Esperantist Centra Oficejo and a member of the Lingva Komitato .
Ermocrate Bucchi ( 1842 -- 1885 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of still lifes with flowers .
Esteban Gil Borges ( Caracas , 1879 - Caracas , 3 August 1942 ) , was a Venezuelan politician , diplomat , writer and university professor .
King Wuling of Zhao ( Traditional Chinese : 趙武靈王 , Simplified Chinese : 赵武灵王 ) ( died 295 BCE , reigned 325 BCE -- 299 BCE ) reigned in the State of Zhao during the Warring States period of Chinese history .
Valens ( 328 -- 9 August 378 ) , fully Flavius Julius Valens Augustus ( Latin : FLAVIVS IVLIVS VALENS AVGVSTVS ) , was Eastern Roman Emperor from 364 to 378 .
Niels Christian Kierkegaard ( 24 September 1806 - 14 August 1882 ) was a Danish draftsman and lithographer .
Edward Milward ( 1712?--1757 ) was an English physician and historian of medicine .
Franz Seldte ( 29 June 1882 -- 1 April 1947 ) was co - founder of the German Stahlhelm paramilitary organization , a Nazi politician , and Minister for Labour of the German Reich from 1933 to 1945 .
Henry Ernest Hardy ( later known as Father Andrew ) ( 7 January 1869 -- 31 March 1946 ) was a British Anglican clergyman and friar , who co - founded the Society of Divine Compassion to work with the poor in the East End of London .
Fred Barratt ( 12 April 1894 -- 29 January 1947 ) played first - class cricket for Nottinghamshire from 1914 to 1931 and represented England in five Test matches , one in the home series against South Africa in 1929 and four on the inaugural Test series against New Zealand in the 1929 - 30 season .
Arthur Preston Mellish ( 10 June 1905 -- 7 February 1930 ) was a Canadian mathematician , known for his generalization of Barbier 's theorem .
Jack Cruise ( 15 August 1915 -- 4 May 1979 ) was a famous Irish comedian & actor who performed in and wrote many shows in the Royal and Olympia theatres in Dublin .
Margretta Bowen , best known as Gretta Bowen ( 1 January 1880 - -8 April 1981 ) was a self - taught Irish artist .
Father Eugenio Barsanti ( 12 October 1821 -- 19 April 1864 ) , also named Nicolò , was an Italian engineer , who together with Felice Matteucci of Florence invented the first version of the internal combustion engine in 1853 .
Wally O'Cock ( 17 June 1875 -- 14 June 1951 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League .
Matthias Eugen Oscar Liebreich ( 14 February 1839 -- 2 July 1908 ) was a German pharmacologist .
Raymond Caron , O.M.R. , ( also known as Raymond Redmond ) ( b. at Athlone , Ireland , in 1605 ; d. at Dublin , 1666 ) was an Irish Recollect Franciscan friar and author .
Pope Clement XIII ( Latin : Clemens XIII ; 7 March 1693 -- 2 February 1769 ) , born Carlo della Torre di Rezzonico , was Pope from 6 July 1758 to his death in 1769 .
Reuven Ben - Yosef ( Hebrew : ראובן בן יוסף‎ ; 1937 - -2001 ) was an Israeli poet
Rony Uzay Heparı ( 24 July 1969 - 31 May 1994 ) was a Turkish composer , music producer , songwriter and actor .
Ennio Bolognini ( 1893 - -1979 ) was an Argentine - born American cellist , guitarist , composer , conductor , professional boxer , pilot , and flight instructor .
Gerulfus ( also known as Gerolf ; Merendree 740- 748 ) is a Roman Catholic Saint of Flanders .
Simon Hartog ( 8 February 1940 -- 18 August 1992 ) was a British filmmaker who worked as both director and producer .
John Cameron of Lochiel ( 1663 - -1748 ) was the 18th Chief of Clan Cameron and a prominent Jacobite .
Viscount Mishima Michitsune ( 三島通庸 , 26 June 1835 -- 23 October 1888 ) was a vassal of the Satsuma Domain during the Late Tokugawa shogunate , Home Ministry bureaucrat and viscount .
Ronald Stuart McGregor , commonly R. S. McGregor ( or Stuart McGregor ) , ( died 19 August 2013 ) was a philologist of the Hindi language .
John Acheson ( died 19 February 1998 ) was a British actor whose screen career extended from 1970 to 1976 .
Henrik Palmstrøm ( 22 July 1900 -- 1 February 1998 ) was a Norwegian actuary and statistician .
Helen Donald - Smith ( fl . 1880 - -1930 ) was an English artist who worked in oil and watercolour , and was active circa 1890 - -1925 .
Hovel Helseth ( 27 August 1779 -- 8 November 1865 ) was a Norwegian industrial entrepreneur .
Sir Thomas Jaffrey , 1st Baronet ( 11 April 1861 - -23 July 1953 ) was a Scottish actuary and a prominent citizen of Aberdeen .
Sir James Spearman Winter , KCMG ( 1 January 1845 in Lamaline , Newfoundland -- 6 October 1911 ) was a Newfoundland politician and Premier .
Cornelis Kruseman ( Dutch pronunciation : ( kɔrˈneːlɪs ˈkrysəˌmɑn ) ; 25 September 1797 -- 14 November 1857 ) was a Dutch painter , draughtsman , etcher , lithographer , silhouettist , paper - cut artist , and art collector .
Mabel Constanduros ( 29 March 1880 -- 8 February 1957 ) , birth name Mabel Tilling , was an English actress and screenwriter .
Joan Boughton ( c. 1410s -- 28 April 1494 ) was an English martyr .
Antonia Forest ( 26 May 1915 -- 28 November 2003 ) was the pseudonym of Patricia Giulia Caulfield Kate Rubinstein , an English writer of children 's novels whose real name was not made public during her lifetime .
Juan de Flandes ( `` John of Flanders '' ; c. 1460 -- by 1519 ) was an Early Netherlandish painter who was active in Spain from 1496 to 1519 ; his actual name is unknown , although an inscription Juan Astrat on the back of one work suggests a name such as `` Jan van der Staat '' .
Tapas Sen ( 1924 - June 28 , 2006 ) was a noted Indian stage lighting designer , who was an important figure in 20th - century Indian theatre .
Abdul Majid Hussein ( d. 29 March 2004 ) was the Permanent Representative of Ethiopia to the United Nations .
Isabel of Cambridge , Countess of Essex ( 1409 -- 2 October 1484 ) was the only daughter of Richard , 3rd Earl of Cambridge and Anne Mortimer .
Francesco I Crispo , Patrizio Veneto ( died 1397 ) was the tenth Duke of the Archipelago through his marriage and the will of Venice .
Charles Comber ( 26 December 1891 -- 4 February 1966 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jean Houymet or Wuillemet or Ouimet ( September 6 , 1634 - November 18 , 1687 ) , son of Nicolas and Pérette Nicayse , originated from Vrigny , archdiocese of Reims located in the province of Champagne department of Marne in France .
Vrindavanam Venugopalan ( 24 October 1935 -- 25 December 2009 ) was an Indian journalist , educationist and writer who wrote in both Malayalam and English .
Hans Leopold Meyer 31 March 1871 - -28 November 1942 ) was an Austrian chemist .
Peter de Rivo ( Petrus ) ( died 1499 ) was a Flemish scholastic philosopher , teaching at the Catholic University of Leuven .
Marthe Bigot ( 1878 - -1962 ) was a French primary schoolteacher , feminist , pacifist and communist .
Herman Silver ( 1831 - -1913 ) was a Republican politician , superintendent of the United States Mint in Colorado , a collector of internal revenue , a railroad official and a member of the Los Angeles , California , City Council .
Charles Christian Hennell ( 30 March 1809 -- 2 September 1850 ) was an English merchant , known as a Christian apologist for his work An Inquiry concerning the Origin of Christianity .
Thomas Turgis ( 1623 - 11 June 1704 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1659 and 1704 , eventually in 1701 becoming the Father of the House , as the member with the longest unbroken service .
Thomas Stackhouse ( 1677 - -1752 ) was an English theologian and controversialist .
Félix Saurí Vivas ( ca . 1852 -- ca . 1912 ) , also known as Félix Saurí y Vivas , was a Puerto Rican businessman and Mayor of Ponce , Puerto Rico , in 1895 .
John LaMountain ( 1830 Wayne County , New York - 1878 Lansingburgh , New York ) was a ballooning pioneer .
Ruth Drexel ( 14 July 1930 , Vilshofen an der Donau , Lower Bavaria -- 26 February 2009 ) was a German actress , director , and theatre director / manager .
Ithell Colquhoun ( 9 October 1906 -- 11 April 1988 ) was a British Surrealist painter and author .
Ludwig Bäumer ( 1 September 1888 -- 28 August 1928 ) was a German writer and Communist activist .
Reverend Campbell Stephen ( 1884 -- 25 October 1947 ) was a Scottish socialist politician .
Charles Croke ( died 1657 ) was an English clergyman and Gresham Professor of Rhetoric .
Mariota Tiumalu Tuiasosopo ( 1905 - 1957 ) was the author of Amerika Samoa , the national anthem of American Samoa .
Cedd ( c. 620 -- 26 October 664 ) was an Anglo - Saxon monk and bishop from Northumbria .
Private Charles D. Ennis ( 8 August 1843 -- 29 December 1930 ) was an American soldier who fought in the American Civil War .
Juan de la Cruz , also known as Palaris , ( 8 January 1733 -- 26 February 1765 ) was a Pangasinan leader in the province of Pangasinan in the Philippines who led a revolt against the colonial authoritires during the 18th century .
Jean Meuvret ( 1901 - -1971 ) was a historian of early modern France .
Nikos Alexiou ( Greek : Νίκος Αλεξίου ; 1960 -- 25 February 2011 , Athens ) is a Greek artist who specialized in visual art , contemporary art , installation art and set design for theatre and dance .
Umesh Chandra Banerjee ( 18 November 1937 -- 5 November 2012 ) was a Bengali Indian jurist , who served as the chief justice of the Andhra Pradesh High Court in 1998 .
Paolo Anesi ( 1697 -- 1773 ) was an Italian painter of the 18th century , active mainly in painting capriccios and landscapes ( vedute ) in the style of Giovanni Paolo Pannini .
Thoma Abrami ( 1869 - 1943 ) , also known as Thoma Avrami , was an Albanian poet , journalist and activist of the Albanian National Awakening .
Ignatius Scoles SJ ( 1 December 1834 -- 15 July 1896 ) was a Roman Catholic Jesuit priest , architect and writer .
Maria Martha Saran , known as Mary Saran , ( 13 July 1897 -- 16 February 1976 ) was a journalist and author .
Benedikt Dreyer ( born before 1495 - died after 1555 ) was a German sculptor , carver and painter working in Lübeck .
Djauhar Zaharsjah Fachruddin Roesli ( 10 September 1951 -- 11 December 2004 ) , better known as Harry Roesli , was an Indonesian singer - songwriter .
Alfred Mellon ( 7 April 1820 -- 24 March 1867 ) was an English violinist , conductor and composer .
Pieter Schouten ( fl . 1622 - 1625 ) was a 17th - century Dutch corsair and privateer .
R. N. Jayagopal ( 1935 -- 19 May 2008 ) was an Indian film director and lyricist in Kannada cinema .
Henry Nelson Coleridge ( 25 October 1798 -- 26 January 1843 ) was an editor of the works of his uncle Samuel Taylor Coleridge .
Hongshi ( Manchu : Hungši ; 18 March 1704 -- 20 September 1727 ) was a Manchu prince of the Qing Dynasty .
Pamela Askew ( 1925 - -1997 ) was an American art historian who wrote influential works on Domenico Fetti and Caravaggio .
Constance Collier ( 22 January 1878 -- 25 April 1955 ) was an English stage and film actress and acting coach .
Sir Thomas Pycroft KCSI ( 4 December 1807 -- 29 January 1892 ) was a British administrator and civil servant who served as a member of the Madras Legislative Council from 1862 to 1867 .
Francisco Augusto Lora Gonzales ( 1910 - -1993 ) , was a former Vice President of the Dominican Republic and Presidential candidate for the country in 1966 , 1970 , 1974 and 1978 .
Arnold Hazeland , Jr. ( 8 May 1900 -- 15 December 1977 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and judge .
Gheorghe Grigore Cantacuzino , or Cantacuzino - Nababul ( 22 September 1833 -- 22 March 1913 ) , was a Romanian politician and lawyer , one of the leading Conservative Party policymakers .
Utagawa Toyoharu ( 歌川 豊春 , c. 1735 -- 1814 ) was a Japanese artist in the ukiyo - e genre , known as the founder of the Utagawa school and for his uki - e pictures that incorporated Western - style geometrical perspective to create a sense of depth .
Guidobaldo del Monte ( 11 January 1545 -- 6 January 1607 , var . Guidobaldi or Guido Baldi ) , Marquis del Monte , was an Italian mathematician , philosopher and astronomer of the 16th century .
Henry of Isenburg - Covern ( German : Heinrich von Isenburg - Covern ) was the Count of Isenburg - Covern from 1229 until 1263 .
Manoel Ceia Laranjeira ( 1903 - -1994 ) was a Brazilian Bishop of the Independent Catholicism movement , particularly the Brazilian Catholic Apostolic Church .
Saint Agapius of Spain was a Christian martyr and most likely a bishop who died under the persecutions of the emperor Valerian in AD 259 .
Wally May ( 11 September 1926 -- 16 May 2011 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) and later in the South Australian Football League SANFL .
Edward Bootle - Wilbraham , 1st Baron Skelmersdale ( 7 March 1771 -- 3 April 1853 ) , was a British landowner and politician .
William Caslon I ( 1692/1693 -- 23 January 1766 ) , also known as William Caslon the elder , was an English gunsmith and designer of typefaces .
Alhaj Hazrath Kareemullah Shah ( died 15 April 1913 ) was a renowned Muslim Sufi , saint and scholar of the Naqshbandi order from Indian sub continent .
Eugene Schieffelin ( 29 January 1827 , New York , N.Y. -- 15 August 1906 , Newport , Rhode Island ) belonged to the New York Genealogical and Biographical Society and the New York Zoological Society .
Petrus Wilhelmi de Grudencz or Piotr of Grudziądz ( ca . 1400 -- ca . 1480 ) was a medieval composer from Graudenz ( Grudziądz ) , the author of songs and motets .
Séamus Ó Néill , ( 1910 - -1981 ) , was a versatile Irish writer from Clarkhill , Castlewellan , County Down , Ireland .
Jack Sheppard ( 4 March 1702 -- 16 November 1724 ) was a notorious English thief and gaol - breaker of early 18th - century London .
George Bourne ( 1780 - -1845 ) was a 19th - century American abolitionist and editor credited as the first public proclaimer of `` immediate emancipation without compensation '' of American slaves .
Carlos Casado del Alisal ( March 16 , 1833 -- June 29 , 1899 ) was a Spanish Argentine businessman .
Thomas Worrall Casey ( 13 October 1869 -- 29 November 1949 ) was a British Liberal politician and Trade Union leader .
William Whiteley ( 29 September 1831 -- 24 January 1907 ) was an English entrepreneur of the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Friedrich Wilhelm Noë ( 1798 , Berlin -- 1858 , Constantinople ) was a German - born , Austrian pharmacist and botanist .
William Bradley Lamond RBA ( 1857 - 1924 ) was a Scottish painter , born at Newtyle , Angus .
Colonel Buckner H. Payne ( 1799 - 1889 ) was an American clergyman , publisher and racist pamphleteer .
Hugh Singleton ( 30 July 1851 -- 17 December 1934 ) was an English prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Travers Buxton ( 1865 - 1945 ) was an English anti - slavery activist .
Oldman ( died 1687 ) , King of the Miskito Nation from c. 1650 until his death in 1687 , was the son of a Miskito leader whose name is not recorded .
Boček III of Poděbrady ( also : Boček III of Kunštát and Poděbrady , German : Boček III . von Podiebrad , Czech : Boček III . z Poděbrad or Boček III . z Kunštátu a Poděbrad or Boček mladší z Poděbrad ; died : 1429 ) was a Bohemian - Moravian nobleman and supporter of the Hussites .
Thomas Carlyle Joseph Robert Hamish Deakin , known as Robert Deakin ( 1917 - -1985 ) , was the Anglican Bishop of Tewkesbury from 1973 until his death in 1985 .
Ruth Flowers ( 29 March 1931 -- 27 May 2014 ) aka `` Mamy Rock '' , was a British disc jockey .
Salomão Barbosa Ferraz ( 18 February 1880 -- 11 May 1969 ) was a Brazilian Roman Catholic priest and Bishop whose career took him through membership of several Christian denominations from the Presbyterian Church to the Roman Catholic Church .
Jan Grzebski ( 1942 -- 12 December 2008 ) was a Polish railroad worker who fell into a coma in 1988 and woke up in 2007 .
Colonel David E. Pergrin ( 26 July 1917 -- 7 April 2012 ) was commanding officer of the 291st Engineer Combat Battalion of the United States Army during World War II . Before the war he earned an engineering degree at Pennsylvania State University , graduating in 1940 .
José Botelho de Carvalho Araújo ( 18 May 1881 -- 14 October 1918 ) was a Portuguese Navy officer and colonial administrator .
Hermann Zingerle ( 31 March 1870 -- 25 April 1935 ) was an Austrian neurologist and psychiatrist born in Trento .
Matti Raivio ( 22 February 1893 -- 25 May 1957 ) was a Finnish cross country skier in the 1920s .
Korla Awgust Kocor ( 3 December 1822 -- 19 May 1904 ; German : Karl August Katzer ) was a Sorbian composer and conductor .
Ole Jacob Skattum ( 8 June 1862 -- 15 January 1930 ) was a Norwegian geographer , educator and politician for the Liberal Left Party .
Pedro Núñez del Valle ( Madrid , c. 1597 -- 1649 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque era .
Dumitru Coliu ( born Dimitar Kolev , Romanian : Dimităr Colev , Bulgarian : Димитър Колев ; November 7 , 1907 -- 1979 ) was a Romanian communist activist and politician .
David Crosley or Crosly ( 1670 - -1744 ) was an English Particular Baptist minister .
Roland Mortier ( 21 December 1920 - 31 March 2015 ) was a Belgian scientist at the Université Libre de Bruxelles .
Václav Eusebius František , Prince of Lobkowicz ( German : Fürst Wenzel Eusebius von Lobkowicz ) ( 30 January 1609 -- Roudnice , 22 April 1677 ) was a Bohemian military leader and diplomat of the Lobkowicz family .
Henri Eugène Lucien Gaëtan Coemans ( 30 October 1825 , Brussels -- 8 January 1871 , Ghent ) was a Belgian Catholic priest and botanist .
Dame Jacobena Angliss , DBE ( 23 May 1896 -- 10 November 1980 ) was an Australian philanthropist , arts supporter , and community worker .
Dragan Kresoja ( Serbian Cyrillic : Драган Кресоја , 23 March 1946 -- 6 November 1996 ) was a Serbian film director .
Pennant Roberts ( 15 December 1940 -- 22 June 2010 ) was a British director noted for his work on British television .
Caroline Iverson Ackerman ( March 6 , 1918 -- September 23 , 2012 ) was an American aviator , journalist , reporter and educator .
Henri Gillain ( 1913 -- 10 August 1999 ) was a Belgian teacher and comics enthusiast who on several occasions wrote scripts for Franco - Belgian comics publications in the segment known as Bande Dessinée .
Alan Fennell ( 10 December 1936 -- 10 December 2001 ) was a British writer and editor best known for work on series produced by Gerry Anderson , and for having created the magazines TV Century 21 and Look - in .
Dap Chhuon , also known as Chuan Khemphet ( Thai : ชวน เข็มเพชร ) , Khem Phet , Chhuon Mochulpich or Chhuon Mchoul Pech ( 1912 - -1959 ) was a right - wing Cambodian nationalist , guerrilla leader , regional warlord , and general .
Veli bek Jedigar ( 1897 - 1971 ) was a soldier of the Imperial Russian Army and officer of both the Azerbaijani Armed Forces , Polish Army in the Second Polish Republic and the Home Army .
Lois Gunden ( 1915 - 2005 ) was one of five Americans named `` Righteous Among the Nations '' by Yad Vashem , the Shoah Martyrs ' and Heroes ' Remembrance Authority of Israel .
Bhai Jodh Singh ( Punjabi : ਭਾਈ ਜੋਧ ਸਿੰਘ,Hindi : भाई जोध सिंघ , 1882 - -1981 ) was a Sikh theologist , author , mentor and social activist .
Benjamin Flint ( 12 January 1893 - 20 July 1959 ) was an English cricketer active from 1919 to 1924 .
Sir John Robinson , 1st Baronet , of London ( 10 January 1615 -- February 1680 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1660 and 1667 .
Gyani Nand ( 1943 -- 23 July 2007 ) was a Fijian politician of Indian descent .
Karl Rothammel ( 1914 - -1987 ) was an amateur radio enthusiast , author and educator .
Margaret McMurray ( died 1760 ) appears to have been one of the last native speakers of a Lowland dialect of Scottish Gaelic in the Galloway variety .
Robert Presslie ( 1920 - -2002 ) was a British science fiction author active in the late 1950s and early 1960s .
Juan José Calandria ( 1902 -- 1980 ) , Uruguayan painter and sculptor .
Jeyaveera Cinkaiariyan ( Tamil : செயவீர சிங்கையாரியன் ) ( died 1410 ? ? ) was the Aryacakravarti king of the Jaffna Kingdom in modern - day northern Sri Lanka , who had a military confrontation with a southern chief known as Alagakkonara .
Ludwig Ott ( 24 October 1906 in Neumarkt - St . Helena -- 25 October 1985 in Eichstaett ) was a Catholic theologian and Medievalist from Bavaria .
Michael Purefoy ( 1562 - -1627 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1584 and from 1621 to 1622 .
George William Athol Sharp ( 1 April 1894 -- 19 April 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Peachey , 2nd Baron Selsey ( 16 March 1749 -- 27 June 1816 ) , styled The Honourable John Peachey between 1794 and 1808 , was a British politician .
George St. John ( 14 April 1878 -- 19 February 1934 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Nicolas Beaujon ( 1718 - -1786 ) was a wealthy French banker at the Court of King Louis XV .
Edward Gibson , 1st Baron Ashbourne PC , QC ( 4 September 1837 -- 22 May 1913 ) was an Irish lawyer and Lord Chancellor of Ireland .
Charles Boissevain ( 28 October 1842 -- 5 May 1927 ) was a journalist , editor and part - owner of the Amsterdam Algemeen Handelsblad , a leading newspaper of the time .
Alfred Peek Stevens ( 1839 -- 26 December 1888 ) , best known by his stage name of Alfred Vance , was a 19th - century English music hall singer .
Sir Roger Antony Hornby ( 5 February 1904 - 1987 ) , was senior partner at the stockbrokers Cazenove .
Robert Hungerford , 3rd Baron Hungerford ( 1431 - -1464 ) was an English nobleman .
The Right Reverent Caesar Gatimu ( b. 18 May 1921 , Limuru , Kenya - d. 20 February 1987 , Nyeri , Kenya ) was the Roman Catholic Bishop of Nyeri , Kenya .
Marian Emma Chase ( 1844 -- 1905 ) was a British water colour artist .
Maurice - Marie - Matthieu Garrigou ( 21 September 1766 -- 27 September 1852 ) was a French Roman Catholic priest who established the Sisters of Our Lady of Compassion .
Émile Bescherelle ( 3 January 1828 , Paris -- 26 February 1903 ) was a French botanist and bryologist .
Augustine Scriven ( 1852 - -1916 ) was an eminent Anglican priest in the last decades of the nineteenth century and the first two of the twentieth .
K. P. R. Gopalan ( 1906 -- 6 August 1997 ) , popularly known as KPR was a politician and militant Naxalite communist leader from Kalliasseri , Kerala .
Brigadier William Bain Thomas CBE DSO ( 11 May 1898 -- 22 November 1967 ) was a British Army officer who commanded the Polish Resettlement Corps after the Second World War .
Hovsep Arghutian ( Armenian : Յովսէփ Արղութեան ; 1863 -- 1925 ) , also known as Khanasori Ishkhan and Ishkhan Arghutian , was an Armenian military commander and political activist .
Adam Ndlovu ( 26 June 1970 -- 16 December 2012 ) was a footballer , who played as a striker .
Charles Ross Taggart ( 19 March 1871 , Washington , D.C. - 4 July 1953 , Kents Hill , Maine ) was an American comedian and folklorist who appeared all over North America as `` The Man From Vermont '' and `` The Old Country Fiddler '' from 1895 - 1938 .
Edmund John Millington Synge ( /sɪŋ/ ; 16 April 1871 -- 24 March 1909 ) was an Irish playwright , poet , prose writer , travel writer and collector of folklore .
Christian Gustav Wilhelm Müller ( 17 February 1857 , Mühlberg near Erfurt -- 18 February 1940 ) was a German zoologist specializing in Ostracoda .
Robert Ludvigovich Bartini ( or Roberto Oros di Bartini ) ( 14 May 1897 -- 6 December 1974 ) was an Italian aircraft designer and scientist .
Aline Towne ( 7 November 1919 -- 2 February 1996 ) born Fern Aline Eggen , also known as Fern Aline Waller , was an American film and television actress , best remembered for her lead roles in 1950s Republic serials , such as Radar Men from the Moon .
Lu Diping ( 1887 - -1935 ) was a Chinese military general and politician .
Juliusz Petry ( born 1890 , died 1961 ) - was a Polish writer , and radio director ; he was the first director of Polish Radio in Lwów and Wilno and , after World War II , in Wrocław .
Gretchen Bender ( 1951 in Seaford , Delaware -- 2004 in New York City ) was an American artist who worked in film , video , and photography .
Michael Hobart Seymour ( 1800 - -1874 ) was an Anglo - Irish Protestant clergyman and religious controversialist .
Alexander Urquhart ( died 1727 ) was a Scottish officer in the British Army and a Jacobite politician .
Debu Bhattacherjee ( 1934 - -1994 ) was a Bangladeshi painter , composer , and music director .
Victor Cushwa IV ( 1925 -- 19 August 1991 ) was a Democratic state senator representing Legislative District 2 in Western Maryland .
Matilda of Amboise ( Mahaut , Mathilde d'Amboise ; c. 1200 ‒ 12 May 1256 ) was a French medieval noblewoman , the Countess of Chartres .
Wilhelm Reiss ( 13 June 1838 -- 29 September 1908 ) was a German geologist and explorer born in Mannheim .
William Tryon ( 8 June 1729 -- 27 January 1788 ) was a British soldier and colonial administrator who served as governor of the Province of North Carolina ( 1765 - -1771 ) and the Province of New York ( 1771 - -1780 ) .
John Hanks ( February 9 , 1802 -- 1889 ) was Abraham Lincoln 's first cousin , once removed , his mother 's cousin .
Zalman Sorotzkin , also known as the Lutzker Rav ( Hebrew : זלמן סורוצקין‎ ; 1881 - -1966 ) , was a famous Orthodox rabbi who served as the rabbi of Lutsk , Ukraine .
Herman von Nördlinger ( 13 August 1818 -- 19 January 1897 ) , was a German forestry expert , botanist and entomologist .
Mehmet Vedat Tek ( 1873 - -1942 ) was a notable Turkish architect , who has been one of the leading figures of the First Turkish National Architectural Movement .
Bertha Jane Grundy was a novelist born in 1837 ? ; she died on 5 September 1912 .
William Reading ( 1674 - -1744 ) was an English clergyman and librarian of Sion College , known for his edition of early church historians .
Karl Heinrich Meier was a Dutchman of German origin ( then aged 24 ) , who , with his accomplice Jose Waldberg , a German national ( then aged 25 ) , was hanged at Pentonville Prison in London on 10 December 1940 , following their conviction at the Old Bailey the previous month .
Together with then husband Edward Anhalt , screenwriter Edna Anhalt ( April 10 , 1914 -- 1987 ) enjoyed some considerable success in a ten - year stretch from 1947 to her retirement in 1957 .
Lars Mortimer ( 22 March 1946 -- 25 August 2014 ) was a Swedish comic artist who wrote and illustrated , among many others , the Swedish comic strips Bobo and Hälge .
Rómulo Rossi ( 1879 - -1945 ) was a Uruguayan politician , journalist and writer .
Joaquim Lobo da Silveira , 7th Count of Oriola ( 1772 - -1846 ) was a Portuguese plenipotentiary at the Congress of Vienna in 1815 .
Fedor Krause ( 10 March 1857 -- 20 September 1937 ) was a German neurosurgeon who was native of Friedland ( Lower Silesia ) .
Hywel ab Owain Gwynedd ( died 1170 ) Wales Prince of Gwynedd in 1170 , a Welsh poet and military leader .
Béla Schick ( 16 July 1877 -- 6 December 1967 ) was a Hungarian - born American pediatrician .
Isidor George Beaver ( December 1859 -- 24 October 1934 ) , often mis - spelled `` Isidore '' and frequently initialized as `` J. G. Beaver '' , was an architect from England who had a substantial career in Adelaide , South Australia and Melbourne , Victoria .
Ezra Rachlin ( 5 December 1915 -- 21 January 1995 ) was an American conductor and pianist .
Sir Arthur Gorges ( c. 1569 -- 10 October 1625 ) , was a sea captain , poet , translator and courtier .
Percy Martin ( 1871 - 1958 ) was an American born British engineer and automobile manufacturer .
Sarah Anne Bright ( 1793 - 1866 ) was a 19th - century English artist and photographer who produced the earliest surviving photographic images taken by a woman .
Thomas Burgh , 1st Baron Burgh also spelt Borough , KG ( c. 1488 -- 28 February 1550 ) , 1st Baron Borough of Gainsborough , also de jure 5th Baron Strabolgi and 7th Baron Cobham of Sterborough , was an English peer .
Mary Leakey ( 6 February 1913 -- 9 December 1996 ) was a British paleoanthropologist who discovered the first fossilised Proconsul skull , an extinct ape now believed to be ancestral to humans .
Francesco Dattaro ( c. 1495 -- 1576 ) and his son Giuseppe Dattaro ( c. 1540 -- 1616 ) , are the two principal builders of the most important family of Cremonese architects of the fifteenth century .
Topham Beauclerk ( pronounced bo - CLAIR ; 22 December 1739 -- 11 March 1780 ) was a celebrated wit and a friend of Dr Johnson and Horace Walpole .

Richard Weymouth ( 1780/1 -- 24 August 1832 ) was a Royal Navy commander , notable as compiler of the Naval , Military , and Village Hymn Book , published in the year of his death and designed for non - denominational use : thus it aimed to exclude hymns which promulgated `` controverted doctrines '' .
Pedro de Répide Gallegos ( Madrid , 1882 -- Madrid , 1947 ) was a Madrid - based writer and journalist .
Thomas Darcy , 1st Baron Darcy of Chiche KG ( 4 December 1506 -- 28 June 1558 ) was an English courtier during the reign of Edward VI .
Lt .- Colonel William McKay ( 1772 -- 18 August 1832 ) is remembered for leading the Canadian Forces to victory at the Siege of Prairie du Chien during the War of 1812 .
Mabel Young ( 18 August 1889 -- 8 February 1974 ) was a British artist , who spent her career painting in Ireland .
Henry Livings ( 20 September 1929 -- 20 February 1998 ) was an English playwright and screenwriter , who worked extensively in British television and theatre from the 1960s to the 1990s .
Pyrros Spyromilios ( Greek : Πύρρος Σπυρομήλιος ; 1913 -- 31 March 1962 ) was a Greek officer of the Greek Navy in World War II and later director of the Greek Radio Orchestra .
William Ayermin ( or Ayermine ) ( died 27 March 1336 ) was a medieval Bishop of Norwich .
Fritz Nieden ( 1883 -- 1942 ) was a German zoologist who specialized in African herpetology .
Hans van Steenwinckel the Elder ( c. 1550 -- 10 May 1601 ) was a Flemish - Danish architect and sculptor .
Anton Graff ( 18 November 1736 -- 22 June 1813 ) was an eminent Swiss portrait artist .
Ernest Beaux ( 8 December 1881 -- 9 June 1961 ) was a Russian and French perfumer who is best known for creating Chanel No . 5 which is perhaps the world 's most famous perfume .
Izak Barnard ( 19 September 1933 , Transvaal - 6 March 2011 ) was a well - known Southern African safari guide , photographer , writer , son of the notorious outlaw hunter Bvekenya , also related to the famous heart transplant surgeon Christiaan Barnard .
Michel Bastarache dit Basque ( 7 February 1730 -- 15 January 1820 ) is notable in Canadian history for his role in the expulsion of the Acadians from New Brunswick .
Amélie Claire Leroy ( 1851 - -1934 ) was an English writer , who wrote over 60 works often using the pseudonym Esmè Stuart .
Don Pablo Xochiquentzin ( died 1536 ) was a ruler of the Aztecs .
Sir John Eyles , 2nd Baronet ( 1683 -- 11 March 1745 ) of Gidea Hall , Essex , was a British financier .
Sima Fu ( 180 - -272 ) was a politician of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period of Chinese history .
