Rafael Mendiluce Elizondo ( 31 July 1939 -- 29 May 2014 ) was a Spanish football striker and coach .
Maria van Arkel ( c. 1385 -- 19 July 1415 ) was the only daughter and heiress of Lord John V of Arkel and Joanna of Jülich .
Billy Merson ( 1879 - -1947 ) was an English music hall performer and songwriter .
Witold Urbanowicz ( 30 March 1908 -- 17 August 1996 ) was a Polish fighter ace of the Second World War .
Ya'akov Meir Hayyim Jerome Schottenstein ( Hebrew : ג'רום ( יעקב מאיר חיים ) שוטנשטיין‎ ; died March 10 , 1992 ) was an American entrepreneur and philanthropist , founder of Schottenstein Stores Corp.
Jacob Pleydell - Bouverie , 2nd Earl of Radnor FRS FSA ( 4 March 1750 -- 27 January 1828 ) was a British nobleman , styled Hon . Jacob Pleydell - Bouverie from 1761 to 1765 and Viscount Folkestone from 1765 to 1776 .
Alberto Morán ( born Remo Andrea Domenico Recagno , Strevi , Alessandria , Italy , 15 March 1922 -- Buenos Aires , 16 August 1997 ) was an Argentine tango musician .
Wang Sengbian ( 王僧辯 ) ( died 555 ) , courtesy name Juncai ( 君才 ) , was a general of the Chinese dynasty Liang Dynasty .
Thomas Mellard Reade FGS ( 1832 - 1909 ) was an English geologist , architect and civil engineer .
John Pilcher ( 1766 -- 16 March 1838 at Canterbury , Kent ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .
Anna Sissak - Bardizbanian , née Hallman , also known as Anna Hallman - Knös and Anna Sissak ( 1876 - 1919 ) , was a Swedish journalist and author .
Hifz - ur - Rehman ( died 1970 ) was a Pakistani archaeologist , historian and linguist .
Hugh Tennent ( 1863 - -1890 ) was a Scottish brewer , the great - great - grandson of the founder ( also Hugh Tennent ) of the Tennent 's brewery .
Ritchie Bodily ( 1 February 1918 -- 13 November 1997 ) was a British philatelist and stamp dealer who was added to the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1990 .
Thomas Gaskin ( 1810 - -1887 ) was an English clergyman and academic , now known for contributions to mathematics .
Charles Lacquehay ( 4 November 1897 -- 3 October 1975 ) was a French professional cyclist who won the UCI Motor - paced World Championships in 1933 and 1935 , finishing second in 1936 .
Carmelo Domênico Recchia , O. Cist , ( 14 December 1921 -- 26 August 2015 ) was an Italian prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Zhu Wuhua ( Chinese : 朱物华 ; January 1902 -- March 1998 ) was a Chinese electronic engineer , an acoustic expert and an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences .
Emperor Wu of Liang ( 梁武帝 ) ( 464 - -549 ) , personal name Xiao Yan ( 蕭衍 ) , courtesy name Shuda ( 叔達 ) , nickname Lian'er ( 練兒 ) , was the founding emperor of the Liang Dynasty of Chinese history .
Forman Brown ( 1901 - -1996 ) was one of the world 's leaders in puppet theatre in his day , as well as an important early gay novelist .
Colonel Alexander Campbell of Possil ( see Carter - Campbell of Possil ) ( 1754 - 1849 ) entered the army as an ensign in the 42nd Regiment in April 1769 , and obtained a lieutenancy in the 2nd Battalion Royals the following year in Minorca .
Yannis Hotzeas ( Greek : Γιάννης Χοντζέας ) ( 1930 -- 24 October 1994 ) was a Greek communist , Marxist theoretician and one of the principal founders of the Greek Marxist - Leninist movement .
Renato Pagliari ( 28 June 1940 -- 29 July 2009 ) was an Italian singer , probably most notable for being lead vocalist it the short - lived 1980s pop group Renée and Renato .
Frederick Juengling ( born Friedrich Jüngling , 8 October 1846 -- 31 December 1889 ) was a wood engraver and painter .
Saint Eleuchadius ( died 112 ) is a 2nd - century Christian saint venerated by the Roman Catholic and Eastern Orthodox Church .
Dorino II Gattilusio ( died circa 1488 ) was the Lord of Ainos , Samothrace and Imbros from 1455 to January 1456 .
Eileen Ellison ( 12 December 1910 -- 29 July 1967 ) was an English Grand Prix racer .
Pedro Manuel de Arandía Santisteban ( Ceuta , 1699 -- Manila , 1759 ) was a Spanish knight and colonial official .
Sir James Montgomery , 2nd Baronet Stanhope ( 9 October 1766 -- 27 May 1839 )
Ernst Frederick II , Duke of Saxe - Hildburghausen ( Hildburghausen , 17 December 1707 -- Hildburghausen , 13 August 1745 ) , was a duke of Saxe - Hildburghausen .
Karl Penka ( 26 October 1847 -- 10 February 1912 ) was an Austrian philologist and anthropologist .
Thomas Mapilton ( fl . 1408 - died 1438 ) was an English gothic architect responsible for old St Stephen Walbrook ( London ) , the cloisters of Durham Cathedral and the south western tower of Canterbury Cathedral .
Gaétan Cathelineau ( 1787 - -1859 ) was a French painter of portraits and of historical and genre subjects .
John Hay of Cromlix ( 1691 - -1740 ) was the Jacobite Duke of Inverness and a courtier and army officer to the King James VIII & III ( known as the `` Old Pretender '' ) .
Lieutenant Colonel Robert Duckenfield ( 1619 - -1689 ) was a Parliamentarian commander during the English Civil War .
Geoff Brokenshire ( 15 July 1922 -- 28 April 1986 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Halil - Salim Jabara ( Arabic : خليل سليم جبارة‎ , Hebrew : חליל - סלים ג'בארה‎ ; 1913 - -1999 ) was an Israeli Arab politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Ahdut HaAvoda between 1964 and 1965 .
Henry Holland Buckman ( 1858 - -1914 ) was an attorney from Duval County , Florida , who became a member of the Florida Legislature and served on the Judiciary Committee .
Horst van Cuyck ( 29 July 1939 -- 26 June 2014 ) was a German business consultant .
Charles Gaudelet ( 1817 - -1870 ) was a French master - glass - maker from Lille .
Joseph McNally , CVO ( 17 July 1942 -- 1 March 2012 ) was a British businessman and philanthropist .
Frederic Beecher Perkins ( 27 September 1828 , Hartford , Connecticut - 3 February 1899 , Brooklyn , New York ) was a United States editor , librarian and writer .
Alec Hooper ( 5 January 1900 -- December quarter 1978 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a left - back .
Andreas Hohwü ( Gråsten , July 18 , 1803 -- October 28 1885 ) was a Danish clockmaker active in Amsterdam .
John George Norman Bird ( 30 October 1924 -- 22 April 2005 ) was an English character actor .
William Francis Ainsworth ( 9 November 1807 -- 27 November 1896 ) was an English surgeon , traveller , geographer and geologist , known also as a writer and editor .
Nicolaas Grevinckhoven ( Grevinchovius , Grevinghoven or Grevinchoven in German sources ) ( died 1632 ) was a Dutch Protestant minister , a combative proponent of the Remonstrant party .
Al Vandenberg ( 1932 - 2012 ) was an American photographer notable for his street portraiture and collaboration on the album cover of Sgt Pepper 's Lonely Hearts Club Band by The Beatles .
Johnny Dunne ( 1905 - -1954 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a full - forward for the Kilkenny senior team .
Friedrich Katzer ( 5 June 1861 , Rokitzan - 3 February 1925 ) was an Austrian geologist and mineralogist .
Edward Shepherd ( died 1747 ) was a prominent London - based English architect and developer in the Georgian period .
José Ignacio Cárdenas ( 1874 -- 13 September 1949 ) was a Venezuelan physician and diplomat .
Philip Quaque ( 1741 -- 17 October 1816 ) was the first African to be ordained as a minister of the Church of England .
Rev. George Balderston Kidd ( Cottingham , near Hull , 28 July 1794 - -1852 ) was a Dissenting Minister and theological writer .
Baron Arthur Haulot ( 15 November 1913 -- 24 May 2005 ) was a Belgian journalist , humanist and poet who served , during World War II as an active member of the Belgian resistance .
William Lygon , 1st Earl Beauchamp ( 25 July 1747 -- 21 October 1816 ) , known as The Lord Beauchamp between 1806 and 1815 , was a British politician .
Rudolf von Ems ( ca . 1200 -- 1254 ) , also called in English Rudolf of Ems , was a mediaeval Austrian epic poet .
Hampus Wilhelm Arnell ( 2 August 1848 in Härnösand -- 1932 in Uppsala ) was a Swedish bryologist .
Joyce Blair ( born Joyce Ogus ; 4 November 1932 -- 19 August 2006 ) was an English actress and dancer .
Zhang Tailei ( simplified Chinese : 张太雷 ; traditional Chinese : 張太雷 ; pinyin : Zhāng Tàiléi ) ( June 1898 -- 12 December 1927 ) was the leader of the 1927 Guangzhou Uprising , during which he was killed .
Iris Tree ( 27 January 1897 -- 13 April 1968 ) was an English poet , actress and artists ' model , described as a bohemian , an eccentric , a wit and an adventuress .
Egon Schultz ( 4 January 1943 -- 5 October 1964 ) was a non - commissioned officer of the East German Border Troops , who , at 21 , was killed in the line of duty .
Kingsley Sambo ( 1936 - -1977 ) was a Rhodesian painter and cartoonist .
Iain Macnab of Barachastlain ( 21 October 1890 -- 24 December 1967 ) was a Scottish wood - engraver and painter .
Samuel Myerscough ( 1854 - -1932 ) , was an acclaimed musician(organist ) , teacher and examiner .
Raymond McCullough ( 1919 -- June 1985 ) was a Northern Ireland politician with the Ulster Unionist Party .
Sir Hugh de Cressingham ( died 11 September 1297 ) was the treasurer of the English administration in Scotland from 1296 to 1297 .
Alexander Bell Filson Young ( 1876 - -1938 ) was a journalist , who published the first book about the sinking of the RMS Titanic , called Titanic , published in 1912 only 37 days after the sinking .
Levi Redfern ( 18 February 1905 -- 1976 ) was an English footballer , who played for York City , Huddersfield Town and Bradford City .
Jakob August Isaksson ( 16 June 1886 , Uudenkaupungin maalaiskunta - 11 July 1929 ) was a Finnish journalist and politician .
Joseph Pasquale Crazzolara ( 12 April 1884 -- 25 March 1976 ) was a Christian missionary in Africa , an ethnologist and a linguist .
Jürgen Ohlsen ( 15 March 1917 -- 23 September 1994 ) was a Nazi propaganda film actor best - remembered for the role of Heini Völker in Hitlerjunge Quex ( Our Flag Leads Us Forward ) ( 1933 ) .
Jacek Jezierski ( 1722 - -1805 ) was a Polish writer and businessman , a member of the Polish nobility and a political writer .
Avraham Yoffe ( Hebrew : אברהם יפה‎ , born 25 October 1913 , died 11 April 1983 ) was an Israeli general during the Six - Day War .
Guan Ning ( 158 - -241 ) , courtesy name You'an , was a politician of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Joanikije II ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јоаникије II ; fl . 1337 - - d. 1354 ) was the Serbian Archbishop ( 1338 - -1346 ) and first Serbian Patriarch ( 1346 - -1354 ) .
Frank Wesley ( 1923 - 2002 ) was an internationally recognised artist .
Max van Gelder ( 12 February 1916 -- 2 October 2004 ) , professionally known as Max Geldray , was a jazz harmonica player .
Margaret Ashton Stimson Lindsley ( 2 January 1889 -- 12 July 1956 ) , known professionally as Lorna Lindsley , was a journalist , war correspondent , and author of the book , War Is People ( Houghton Mifflin , 1945 ) .
Henry Marney , 1st Baron Marney KG ( c. 1447 -- 4 May 1523 ) was a politician of the Tudor period in England .
Jack Solomons ( December 1900 -- 8 December 1979 ) was a British boxing promoter who has been called `` one of the greatest boxing promoters in history '' and `` England 's greatest boxing impresario '' .
Emperor Xuan of Northern Zhou ( ( 北)周宣帝 ) ( 559 - -580 ) , personal name Yuwen Yun ( 宇文贇 ) , courtesy name Qianbo ( 乾伯 ) , was an emperor of the Xianbei dynasty Northern Zhou .
Josias Priest ( c. 1645 -- 3 January 1735 in Chelsea , London ) was an English dancer , dancing - master and choreographer .
Sir Joseph Banks , 1st Baronet , GCB , PRS ( 24 February ( O.S. 13 February ) 1743 -- 19 June 1820 ) was a British naturalist , botanist and patron of the natural sciences .
William Vincent Fitzgerald , ( 21 July 1867 -- 6 August 1929 ) was an Australian botanist .
Baruch Kamin ( Hebrew : ברוך קמין‎‎ , born 15 April 1914 , died 10 July 1988 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai from 1953 until 1955 .
Achille Solari ( Naples , October 9 , 1835 - 1884 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of landscapes of the region around Naples .
Milan Budimir ( Serbian Cyrillic : Милан Будимир ; 2 November 1891 -- 17 October 1975 ) was the most distinguished Serbian classical scholar , professor of the Serbian philosopher and Chair of the Department of the Classical Philology .
Francis Irby Gwaltney ( born 9 September 1921 in Traskwood , Arkansas died 27 February 1981 ) was a prolific Southern American author .
Leib Weissberg ( January 9 , 1893 Probuzina , Poland -- 1942 Jasenovac concentration camp ) was Slavonski Brod rabbi who was killed during the Holocaust .
Private Shinyei Nakamine distinguished himself by extraordinary heroism in action on 2 June 1944 , near La Torreto , Italy .
Barun Sengupta ( Bengali : বরুণ সেনগুপ্ত ) ( 23 January 1934 -- 19 June 2008 ) , the founder - editor of Bartaman newspaper , was a Bengali journalist and popular political critic .
Ernest Griffith Price ( 13 May 1870 -- 5 January 1962 ) was a British National Liberal , later Liberal politician and wharfinger .
Milorad M. Drachkovitch ( 8 November 1921 -- 16 June 1996 ) was the posthumous son of Milorad Drašković , Minister of the Interior in the Former Kingdom of Yugoslavia .
Evangelos Sarris ( Greek : Ευάγγελος Σαρρής ; 1881 - 1917 ) was an officer of the Cretan gendarmerie and one of the leaders of the National Defence movement in Greece .
Caleb Stetson ( January 6 , 1801 -- January 1885 ) was an American businessman and politician from the Commonwealth of Massachusetts .
Peter Crawley ( born 5 December 1799 , Newington Green , London -- 12 March 1865 , West Smithfield , London ) was a British bare - knuckle boxer .
Simeon I of Yerevan or Simeon Yerevantsi ( Armenian : Սիմեոն Ա Երևանցի `` Simon of Yerevan '' ; 1710 - -1780 ) was the Catholicos of All Armenians from 1763 to 1780 .
William Upcott ( 1779 - -1845 ) was an English librarian and antiquary .
Fazaldad Wahla , alias ' Mahmud Khan ' , or ' Mahmood Khan ' ( 1962 - -1999 ) was one of the youngest elected Members of the National Assembly of Pakistan in the country 's history .
William Morrant Baker ( 20 October 1839 , Andover , Hampshire , England -- 3 October 1896 , Pulborough , Sussex ) was an English physician and surgeon .
Roderick Ross CVO CBE KPM ( 24 May 1865 -- 6 March 1943 ) was Chief Constable of Edinburgh City Police from 1900 to 1935 .
Anders Stilloff ( 1866 - -1941 ) was a Norwegian journalilst , playwright , newspaper editor and theatre critic .
Jacob Taubes ( 25 February 1923 -- 21 March 1987 ) was a sociologist of religion , philosopher , and scholar of Judaism .
David Kresh ( 1940 - 2006 ) was an American poet , with three published volumes of poetry .
Roekiah ( Jawi:روكيه ; pronounced Rukiah ( ruˈkiah ) ; born 1917 -- died 2 September 1945 ) , often credited as Miss Roekiah , was an Indonesian kroncong singer and film actress .
Joseph Maria Wolfram ( 21 July 1789 -- 30 September 1839 ) was a German - Czech politician and amateur composer who wrote operas which were performed with success .
Nawi Ismail ( 18 April 1918 - 8 February 1990 in Jakarta ) was an Indonesian film director and actor .
Walter Montgomerie Neilson ( 28 November 1819 -- 8 July 1889 ) was a Scottish locomotive engineer and manufacturer .
Richard Fellowes Benyon ( 17 November 1811 -- 26 July 1897 ) , born Richard Fellowes , was a British Conservative politician and civil servant .
Kimweri ye Nyumbai ( or Shekulwavu ) ( died 1862 ) was the ruler of the Shambaa people of the Usambara Mountains in what is now Tanzania between around 1815 and 1862 .
Joseph Graves Olney ( October 9 , 1849 -- December 3 , 1884 ) was a rancher and cattleman in what is now Cochise County , Arizona .
Irene Rooke ( 1878 -- 14 June 1958 ) was an English theatre and film actress from Bridport , Dorset , England .
Harriet Pitt ( 1748 ? -- 10 December 1814 ) was a British actress and dancer .
Friedrich Traugott Friedemann ( 31 March 1793 , Stolpen ; -- 2 May 1853 , Idstein ) was a German educator , philologist and archivist .
Olive Sloane ( 16 December 1896 -- 28 June 1963 ) was an English actress whose film career spanned over 40 years from the silent era through to her death .
Gideon Schocken ( Also spelled Gideon Shocken ; Hebrew : גדעון שוקן‎ ; December 28 , 1919 - 1981 ) was Haganah fighter , Major in the British Army during World War II , and Aluf ( major general ) in the Israel Defense Forces ( IDF ) .
Alexander de Tartagnis ( c. 1424 -- 1477 ) was a medieval jurist .
Isaac Colfe ( by 1560 - -1597 ) was an English divine .
Jane Barlow ( 17 April 1857 -- 20 April 1917 ) was an Irish novelist , noted for her poems describing the lives of the Irish peasantry , chiefly about Lisconnel and Ballyhoy , in relation to both landlords and the Irish potato famine .
Moropant Trimbak Pingle ( 1620 - -1683 ) , also known as Moropant Peshwā , was the first peshwa ( prime minister ) of the Maratha Empire , serving on Shivaji 's Council of Eight ( English - Ashtapradhan Mandal , Marathi-अष्टप्रधान मंडळ ) .
John Dagworthy ( 1721 - -1784 ) was a brigadier general who commanded the Sussex County ( Delaware ) militia during the American Revolutionary War .
Alajos Szokolyi ( also referred to as Alajos Szokoly , Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈɒlɒjoʃ ˈsokoji ) ; Slovak : Alojz Sokol ; 19 June 1871 -- 9 September 1932 ) was a Hungarian athlete , sports organizer , sports manager , archivist and physician .
Saint Silvia ( Sylvia ) ( c. 515 -- c. 592 ) was the mother of St. Gregory the Great ; she had another son but his name did not survive through the ages .
Géza Maróti ( 1875 - 1941 ) was a Hungarian architect , sculptor , painter , and applied artist .
Joseph Aspdin ( December ? 1778 -- 20 March 1855 ) was an English cement manufacturer who obtained the patent for Portland cement on 21 October 1824 .
Percy Outram ( 19 May 1903 -- 3 November 1981 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thrasyvoulos Stanitsas ( Greek : Θρασύβουλος Στανίτσας , 1910 - -1987 ) was a protopsaltes ( leading cantor ) in the Great Church of Constantinople from 1960 until 1964 .
Hans Haym ( 29 November 1860 -- 15 February 1921 ) was a German conductor of the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries .
Eva Haalke ( née Hansen ; 2 April 1912 -- 24 October 2003 ) was a Norwegian dancer and ballet teacher .
Adolf , Duke of Jülich - Berg ( c. 1370 -- 14 July 1437 ) , was the first Duke of the combined duchies of Jülich and Berg .
Sir John Burgoyne , 1st Baronet ( c 1592 - -1657 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1645 to 1648 .
Sir Thomas Stamford Raffles , FRS ( 6 July 1781 -- 5 July 1826 ) was a British statesman , Lieutenant - Governor of British Java ( 1811 - -1815 ) and Governor - General of Bencoolen ( 1817 - -1822 ) , best known for his founding of Singapore .
Abolhassan Etessami , Iranian architect , calligrapher , painter , and novelist , was born in 1903 and died in 1978 .
Franc Trkman ( 1903 - 1978 ) was an inventor and entrepreneur .
Dick Wilson , ( 30 July 1916 -- 19 November 2007 ) , was a British - born Canadian character actor who played the role of finicky grocery store manager Mr. George Whipple in more than 500 Charmin toilet paper television commercials ( 1965 - -1989 , 1999 - -2000 ) .
Maurus Corker ( baptised James ; 1636 -- 22 December 1715 ) was an English Benedictine who was accused and imprisoned as part of the Popish Plot , but was acquitted of treason .
Nuala Ní Conchobair ( died 1226 ) was Queen of Ulaid .
Hu Zhiyu ( Chinese : 胡祇遹 , 1227 - -1293 ) , also known as Purple Mountain Hu ( Chinese : 紫山胡 ) , was a period writer of Chinese Sanqu poetry during the Yuan Dynasty .
John Selkirk ( 1782 -- 1843 ) was a Tyneside songwriter of the 18th and 19th century .
James Hasleby ( born 1833 , Stamford Lincs UK ; died 1903 , Northampton , Western Australia ) , was an English convict transported to Western Australia .
John Silva Meehan ( 6 February 1790 -- 24 April 1863 ) was an American printer and publisher .
Henry Habberley Price ( 17 May 1899 -- 26 November 1984 ) , usually cited as H. H. Price , was a Welsh philosopher , known for his work on perception .
John Lancelot Cowan ( 14 August 1893 -- 19 May 1971 ) served as one of the 4 members for the District of Southern Districts in the South Australian Legislative Council from 26 May 1949 to 28 February 1959 .
John of Montfort ( in Breton Yann Moñforzh , in French Jean de Montfort ) ( 1295 -- 16 September 1345 , Château d'Hennebont ) , sometimes known as John IV , Duke of Brittany , and 6th Earl of Richmond from 1341 to his death .
Carl Valentin Falsen ( 27 May 1787 -- 14 April 1852 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and Member of Parliament .
Noel Frederick Hall ( 1902 - -1983 ) was an economist and academic who was one of Britain 's earliest post - war specialists in business theory and education .
Hon . Louisa Pitt ( 1754 - -1791 ) , was born in 1754 ( or 1756 ) in Stratfield - Say , Southampton , Hampshire , England , the second daughter of the British diplomat and politician George Pitt , 1st Baron Rivers ( 1721 - -1803 ) and his wife Penelope Atkins .
Velcho Stoyanov ( Bulgarian : Велчо Стоянов ; 1907 -- 1982 ) , was a Bulgarian football player .
John A. Caddell ( Tuscumbia , Alabama , 23 April 1910 -- 7 February 2006 ) was an American lawyer in the state of Alabama .
Gobinda Halder ( 1930 -- 17 January 2015 ) was a Bengali lyricist and poet .
Herbert Westfaling ( also spelled Westphaling , 1531/2 -- 1 March 1602 ) , was Anglican Bishop of Hereford and Vice - Chancellor of the University of Oxford .
James Hayden Tufts ( 1862 - -1942 ) , an influential American philosopher , was a professor of the then newly founded Chicago University .
Ian Crawley ( 14 May 1962 -- 8 July 2008 ) was an English footballer .
Jack L. Ryan ( 24 July 1907 -- 4 July 1959 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Downe Gillon ( 31 August 1801 -- 7 October 1846 ) was a Scottish Whig politician .
François Stoepel , also Dr. Franz Stoepel ( 1794 -- 19 December 1836 ) was a French music critic , writer , journalist , pianist , and pedagogue .
Willem Grasso ( 20 April 1833 -- 20 March 1903 ) was the founder of Grasso 's Royal Machine Factories Ltd.
Harvey Lonsdale Elmes ( 10 February 1814 -- 26 November 1847 ) was an English architect , the designer of St George 's Hall , Liverpool .
Francena H. Arnold ( 1888 - -1972 ) was a 20th - century novelist , author of the Christian fiction classic Not My Will and nine other books .
Evanthia Kairi ( 1799 - -1866 ) was a Greek intellectual , playwright , poet and feminist .
Ganga Kishore Bhattacharya ( died 1831 ) was an Indian journalist , teacher and reformer .
Helen Crummy MBE ( 10 May 1920 -- 11 July 2011 ) was a founder of The Craigmillar Festival Society , and served as the Organising Secretary for the group until 1985 .
James of Portugal ( 17 September 1433 -- 27 August 1459 ) , also known as James of Coimbra , James of Lusitania , was a Portuguese infante ( prince ) of the House of Aviz , and a bishop and cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Jagjit Singh , born Jagmohan Singh ( 8 February 1941 -- 10 October 2011 ) , was a prominent Indian Ghazal singer , composer and musician .
Pier Angelo Basili ( after 1550 -- 1604 ) was an Italian painter of the 16th century Renaissance period .
Pelagius would later suffer death as a martyr , with Hermogius retreating to Ribas del Sil , where he would eventually die , in 942 .
Sir John Grice ( 6 October 1850 -- 27 February 1935 ) was an Australian businessman , company director and University of Melbourne vice - chancellor .
Gertrude I. Johnson ( died 1961 ) was a college - educated teacher who , along with fellow teacher Mary T. Wales , founded Johnson & Wales Business School ( now University ) in 1914 in Providence , RI .
Florian Leopold Gassmann ( 3 May 1729 -- 21 January 1774 ) was a German - speaking Bohemian opera composer of the transitional period between the baroque and classical eras .
Stephen Grellet ( 2 November 1773 -- 16 November 1855 ) was a prominent French - born American Quaker missionary .
Jacobus Ó Cethernaig , aka James O'Kearney , Bishop of Annaghdown , 1323 - -1324 , Bishop of Connor 1324 - -1351 .
Sándor Józan ( 4 August 1932 - 13 May 1985 ) was a Hungarian state security officer and diplomat , who served as Hungarian Charge d'Affaires ad interim to the United States between 1967 and 1968 , after his predecessor , János Radványi applied for asylum from the US government .
Hendrik Becker ( sometimes `` Bekker '' ) ( 3 August 1661 , Amsterdam - ca 15 August 1722 , Amsterdam ) was the Governor of Ceylon from 1707 until 1716 .
Harry Caspar ( 4 November 1926 -- 1 July 1988 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Phillimore Watts Phillimore ; ( formerly Stiff , changed by royal licence 1873 ) MA BCL ( b. Nottingham 27 October 1853 , d . Torquay 9 April 1913 ) was a solicitor , genealogist and publisher .
Friedrich Ludwig Weidig ( 15 February 1791 - 23 February 1837 ) was a German Protestant theologian , pastor , activist , teacher and journalist .
William Henry McNeill ( 7 July 1803 -- 4 September 1875 ) was best known for his 1830 expedition as the captain of the brig Llama , which sailed from Boston , Massachusetts , United States , 12,000 miles around Cape Horn , to the Pacific Northwest on a fur trading expedition .
William II , Duke of Jülich ( c. 1327 -- 13 December 1393 ) was the second Duke of Jülich and the sixth William in the House of Jülich .
Sir Francis Harry Hinsley OBE ( 26 November 1918 -- 16 February 1998 ) was an English historian and cryptanalyst .
Édith Girard ( 1949 -- 6 September 2014 ) was a French architect who in particular designed a number of apartment buildings in the Paris area .
Tenskwatawa ( also called Tenskatawa , Tenskwatawah , Tensquatawa or Lalawethika ) ( January 1771 -- November 1836 ) was a Native American religious and political leader of the Shawnee tribe , known as the Prophet or the Shawnee Prophet .
Bill Clohesy ( 5 November 1894 -- 8 November 1945 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Andrew Spielman , Sc . D. ( 24 February 1930 -- 20 December 2006 ) was a prominent American public health entomologist and Professor of Tropical Public Health in the Department of Immunology and Infectious Diseases at the Harvard School of Public Health ( HSPH ) .
Henry Gillard Glindoni ( 1852 Kennington Lane--20 November 1913 Romford , Essex ) was an English painter noted for his depiction of period costumery in historical and genre scenes .
John Vandeleur Stewart ( 8 October 1804 - 1872 ) was an Irish naturalist , ornithologist and bird collector .
Sir Edward Warburton Jones PC(NI ) PC QC ( 3 July 1912 -- 18 March 1993 ) , was a Northern Irish barrister , judge and politician .
Peter the Patrician ( Latin : Petrus Patricius , Greek : Πέτρος ὁ Πατρίκιος , Petros ho Patrikios ; c. 500 - -565 ) was a senior East Roman or Byzantine official , diplomat , and historian .
Don Pedro Navarro , Count of Oliveto ( c. 1460 -- 28 August 1528 ) was a Spanish military engineer and general who participated in the War of the League of Cambrai .
George Kadish , born Zvi ( Hirsh ) Kadushin ( died September 1997 ) , was a Lithuanian Jewish photographer who documented life in the Kovno Ghetto during the Holocaust , the period of the Nazi German genocide against Jews .
John Woodall ( 1570 - -1643 ) was an English military surgeon , Paracelsian chemist , businessman , linguist and diplomat .
Selwyn Walford Young ( 1899 - 1977 ) , usually known as Walford Young , was a Belizean musician and composer .
Pablo Balarezo Moncayo ( 10 December 1904 -- 23 January 1999 ) was an Ecuadorian poet , journalist and essayist .
Aurelio Bonelli ( c.1569 -- after 1620 ) was an Italian composer , organist and painter .
Serafino Brizzi ( 1684 - -1724 ) was an Italian engraver of the Baroque period , active in Bologna .
George William Marshall , LL.D. , FSA ( 1839 - -1905 ) was an English officer of arms , serving as Rouge Dragon Pursuivant from 1887 - -1904 , and as York Herald from 1904 - -1905 .
Hon . Patrick Perkins , J. P. , ( 10 October 1838 -- 17 May 1901 ) , nicknamed Paddy Perkins , was a brewer and politician in colonial Queensland .
Michael M. Davis ( 1879 - -1971 ) was the Executive Chair of the Committee for the Nation 's Health .
Thomas Eustace , 1st Viscount Baltinglass ( c.1480 - 1549 ) was an Anglo - Irish noble who achieved wealth and influence by prudently remaining loyal to the English Crown .
Angus Ross ( 7 February 1966 -- 17 January 2016 ) was a Scottish professional darts player who competed in the 1980s .
Skapti Þóroddsson ( died 1030 ) was an Icelandic lawspeaker and skald .
Christopher Rave ( 20 February 1881 -- 13 January 1933 ) was a German painting artist , explorer of polar regions and professor .
Jacques d'Annebaut ( Denebaud , Anebault and Annebault ) ( died 1557 ) was a French Cardinal .
David Hostetter ( 1819 - -1888 ) was an American businessman and banker .
Gabriele Rumi ( 4 September 1939 -- 21 May 2001 ) was a Formula One team owner .
Alexander Uber ( 1783 - 1824 ) was a German cello virtuoso , composer , and Kapellmeister ; he was a student of Johannes Jäger .
Joseph Willem Mengelberg ( 28 March 1871 -- 21 March 1951 ) was a Dutch conductor , famous for his performances of Mahler and Strauss with the Concertgebouw Orchestra .
Joseph Huddart F.R.S. ( 1741 - -1816 ) was a British hydrographer .
Nathaniel Hughson ( 16 July 1755 , New York - 1 November 1837 , Hamilton , Ontario ) was a farmer and hotel owner , Loyalist who moved to Canada following the American Revolution , one of the city founders of Hamilton , Ontario .
Henry Cyril Augustus Steele ( 11 June 1891 -- 18 January 1939 ) , commonly known as Cyril Steele , was an Australian rules footballer who played with University and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Maurice de Berkeley , 4th Baron Berkeley the Valiant ( ca . 1330 -- 8 June 1368 ) was an English peer born in Berkeley , Gloucestershire , England to Thomas de Berkeley , 3rd Baron Berkeley and Lady Margaret Mortimer .
Mel Tappan ( 1933 -- 1980 , born Melrose H. Tappan III ) was the editor of the newsletter Personal Survival ( `` P.S. '' ) Letter and the books Survival Guns and Tappan on Survival .
Thomas Stegg ( died 1652 ) was a Virginia merchant and politician .
James Henry Fields ( born c. November 1 , 1948 -- c. November 15 , 1984 ) was an American pianist .
Shyam Lal Tabdar ( Nepali : श्यामलाल ताबदार ) ( c. 1942 -- December 7 , 2012 ) was a Nepalese who served as Ambassador to Egypt from January 2010 until his death in December 2012 .
Samuel Marsden ( 25 June 1765 -- 12 May 1838 ) was an English born Anglican cleric and a prominent member of the Church Missionary Society , believed to have introduced Christianity to New Zealand .
Brunello Rondi ( 26 November 1924 -- 7 November 1989 ) was a prolific Italian screen writer and film director best known for his frequent script collaborations with Federico Fellini .
Sir John Meux , 1st Baronet ( died February 1657 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1643 .
Abraham Moles ( 1920 -- 22 May 1992 ) was an engineer of electrical engineering and acoustics , and a doctor of physics and philosophy .
Hendrik Verhoeff ( around 1645 -- 27 June 1710 in Utrecht ) was a silversmith and schutter from The Hague who played a role in the assassination of Cornelis- and Johan de Witt on August 20 1672 .
Graham Oxenden ( 1802 at Deane , Kent -- 8 December 1826 ) was an English first - class cricketer associated with Cambridge University who was active in the 1820s .
William Alfred Young ( 4 April 1863 - 1 July 1911 ) served as President of the Council , and Magistrate of the British Overseas Territory of Pitcairn Island three times , between 1897 and 1908 .
Rolf Friedemann Pauls ( 26 August 1915 in Eckartsberga -- 4 May 2002 ) was a German diplomat .
Ambati Brahmanaiah ( died 21 April 2013 ) was an Indian politician who was the MP for Machilipatnam 1999 - -2004 , the MLA for Machilipatnam 1994 - -1999 ( The other Contestants at that period are Perni Venkateswar Rao from Indian National Congress Party and Thota Chalapathi Rao ) , and Avanigadda ( since 2009 ) .
Georg Mayer - Marton ( 3 June 1897 -- 8 August 1960 ) was a significant figure in Viennese art between the First and Second World Wars working in oil , watercolour and graphics .
Isaac Arnauld ( 1566 -- 14 October 1617 ) , seigneur de Corbeville , was a member of the Arnauld family , a French family which during the 17th century produced several major Jansenists .
Gordon David Nunn ( 1927 - -2008 ) , better known as Bunny Nunn , was an Australian soccer player .
Edwin Lulham ( 7 April 1865 -- 27 June 1940 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Sussex .
Otto von Müller ( German pronunciation : ( ˈɔto fɔn ˈmʏlɐ ) ; 17 October 1875 -- 2 April 1976 ) was a German tennis player .
Police Constable Joseph Grantham ( died 1830 ) was the first police officer to be killed whilst on duty in the United Kingdom .
Peng Yubin , Peng Yu - pin , ( 彭毓斌 ) , ( ? --1945 ) , was a Nationalist Chinese general .
Peter Lennon ( 28 February 1930 -- 18 March 2011 ) was an Irish journalist and film director , probably best known as director of the social history documentary film Rocky Road to Dublin .
Albert Deutsch ( 1905 - -1961 ) was an American journalist and social historian .
John Hartcliffe ( 1651 - 16 August 1712 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1691 - 1712 and Headmaster of Merchant Taylors ' School , Northwood .
Ram Singh II ( 27 September 1835 -- 17 September 1880 ) , was the Maharaja of Jaipur from 1835 until 1880 .
( Edward ) Eardley Knollys ( 1902 - 1991 ) was an English artist of the Bloomsbury School of artists , art critic , art dealer and collector , active from the 1920s to 1950s .
Alice Amelia Chown ( 3 February 1866 -- 2 March 1949 ) was a Canadian feminist , pacifist , socialist and author .
Michael Burghers ( b. c.1647/8 -- 1727 ) was a Dutch illustrator and artist of the 17th century , who spent most of his career in England .
Baron Herman Baltia ( 1 September 1863 -- 16 September 1938 ) was a Belgian military officer , the son of the Belgian General Charles Baltia ( of Luxembourgish origin ) and of a German mother .
Yi Bong - chool or Lee Bong - chool ( 1925 - -1992 ) was an officer for the Republic of Korea .
Sher Bahadur Thapa ( Nepali : शेरबहादुर थापा ) VC ( 20 November 1921 -- 19 September 1944 ) was a Nepalese Gurkha recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Bernhard Josef Hilgers ( 20 August 1803 -- 7 February 1874 ) was a German Catholic church historian .
Ludwig Satz ( 18 February 1891 -- 31 August 1944 ) was an actor in Yiddish theater and film , best known for his comic roles .
Nicholas Bownde , Bownd or Bound ( died 1613 ) was an English clergyman , known for his Christian Sabbatarian writings .
Alonzo F. Salisbury ( 1808 - -1855 ) was a member of the second , third and fourth Nebraska Territorial Legislatures from 1855 - -1858 .
Alf Eivind Saxlund ( 25 April 1890 -- 17 January 1973 ) was a Norwegian military officer and barrister .
Jiang Ximing ( Chinese : 江希明 ; 1913~1990 ) , was a notable Chinese zoologist and politician .
Marcel Liebman ( 1929 - 1986 ) was a Belgian Marxist historian of political sociology and theory , active at the Université Libre de Bruxelles and Vrije Universiteit Brussel .
Sophia of Brandenburg - Stendal ( 1300 - 1356 ) was a daughter of Margrave Henry I ( 1256 - -1318 ) and his wife Agnes of Bavaria ( 1276 - -1345 ) .
Mark Fiennes ( 11 November 1933 -- 30 December 2004 ) was an English photographer and illustrator .
Thérèse Caval ( 1750 - -1795 ) , was a French revolutionary .
Hector St Clair ( died 1932 ) was an English comedian who came to Australia with the JC Williamson Theatre company in 1921 and stayed there for the rest of his career .
Sammy Creason ( 27 November 1944 -- 21 December 1995 ) was an American session drummer who played with Tony Joe White , Kris Kristofferson and Bob Dylan amongst others .
William John Yuill ( 10 October 1885 -- 5 October 1960 ) was an Australian agricultural writer , dairy industry leader and public servant .
Sir Edward Wilmot , 1st Baronet ( 1693 - -1786 ) was a surgeon and physician to both George II and George III of England .
Chambré Brabazon Ponsonby - Barker ( 12 June 1762 -- 13 December 1834 ) was an Irish Member of Parliament .
Heneage Finch , 5th Earl of Aylesford ( 24 April 1786 -- 3 January 1859 ) was a British peer , the eldest son of Heneage Finch , 4th Earl of Aylesford .
William of Villehardouin ( Guillaume de Villehardouin ; died 1 May 1278 ) was the last Villehardouin prince of Achaea ( as William II ) and ruled the principality at the height of its power and influence(1246 - 1278 ) .
Emil Reesen ( 30 May 1887 -- 27 March 1964 ) was a Danish composer , conductor and pianist .
Torolf Juell ( 4 November 1897 -- 16 September 1983 ) was a Norwegian military officer and judge .
William Douglas of Whittingehame ( c. 1540 -- 17 December 1595 ) was a Senator of the College of Justice at Edinburgh , and a Royal conspirator .
William Keith Neal ( 11 November 1905 -- 10 April 1990 ) was an English author , collector and enthusiast who amassed what is considered to be one of the greatest private collections of antique firearms ever assembled .
Henry Stuart Russell ( 16 March 1818 -- 5 March 1889 ) was an explorer , politician and pastoralist , best known for establishing the Cecil Plains Station around the Condamine River area .
Marco Barbaro ( 1511 - -1570 ) was of the Venetian noble Barbaro family and the author of a Genealogie Patrizie , and other works in Venetian .
Roger Dudman died in 1990 and several local landmarks bear his name : posthumously the Oxford road , `` Roger Dudman Way '' , north of Oxford railway station , the site of the Castle Mill student blocks .
Lakkoju Sanjeevaraya Sharma ( Telugu : లక్కోజు సంజీవరాయ శర్మ ) ( 27 November 1907 -- 1998 ) was an Indian mathematician from Andhra Pradesh .
James Eugene Munson ( born in Paris , New York , 12 May 1835 ; died 1906 ) was a United States court stenographer and inventor , noted mostly for his consolidation of his own work , and that of others , into the Munson Shorthand system .
Joachim the Korsunian ( Russian : Иоаким Корсунянин - Ioakim Korsunianin ) was the first bishop of Novgorod the Great ( r. ca . 989 - 1030 ) .
Joseph Pierre Alexis Contant ( 12 November 1858 -- 28 November 1918 ) was a Canadian composer , organist , pianist , and music educator .
Baron Nils Taube ( 25 July 1928 -- 11 March 2008 ) was Britain 's longest serving fund manager .
Richard Yeo RA ( ca 1720 - -1779 ) was a British medalist and Chief Engraver at the Royal Mint , in which capacity he supplied patterns for the guinea and five guinea coins of George III . He was a founding member of the Royal Academy of Art , and appears in the group portrait by John Zoffany .
Ahli Shirazi ( اهلی شیرازی ) , full name Muhammad ibn Yusuf Ahli Shirazi , was a Persian poet who lived in Shiraz from 858 to 942H ( circa 1454 - 1535 ) .
Matilda Ann Aston ( 11 December 1873 -- 1 November 1947 ) , better known as Tilly Aston , was a blind Australian writer and teacher , who founded the Victorian Association of Braille Writers , and later went on to establish the Association for the Advancement of the Blind , with herself as secretary .
Peter Woon ( 1931 -- May 2014 ) was a news and current affairs editor at the British Broadcasting Corporation .
Alfred Henry Forrester ( 10 September 1804 -- 26 May 1872 ) was an English author , illustrator and artist , who was also known under the pseudonym of Alfred Crowquill .
Gunnar Neels - Hansson ( 27 July 1883 -- 9 June 1967 ) was a Norwegian theatre director .
Henry Collins Walsh ( 1863 - -1927 ) was a journalist , historian , explorer of Central America and Greenland , a founding member of the Arctic Club of America ( 1894 ) and the nominal `` Founder '' of The Explorers Club ( 1904 ) .
Combe Miller ( 1745 - -1814 ) was a Church of England clergyman .
Alexander Watson Hutton ( 10 June 1853 -- 9 March 1936 ) was a Scottish teacher and sportsman who is considered `` The Father of Argentine football '' .
Andrew Tombes ( 29 June 1885 - -17 March 1976 ) was an American comedian and character actor .
Major General William George Walker VC , CB ( 28 May 1863 -- 16 February 1936 ) was a British recipient of the Victoria Cross .
Carl E. Guthrie ( 15 October 1905 , in St. Louis , Missouri -- 23 April 1967 , in Los Angeles ) was an American cinematographer .
Olaf Mørch Hansson ( 28 July 1856 -- 22 February 1912 ) was a Norwegian actor and theatre director , journalist and newspaper editor .
Colin Legum ( 3 July 1919 , Kestell , Orange Free State , South Africa -- 8 July 2003 ) was , along with his wife , Margaret ( 1933 - 2007 ) , an anti - apartheid activist and political exile .
Roger Seys ( died 1599 ) was Attorney general of all Wales ; and Under - Sheriff of Glamorganshire in 1570 .
Eric Needham ( 7 June 1913 -- 8 May 2000 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Torkel Halvorsen Aschehoug ( 27 June 1822 -- 20 January 1909 ) was a prominent Norwegian philosopher of law , economist , and conservative politician .
Gobnait Ní Bhruadair ( 17 December 1861 -- 16 January 1955 ) was one of the foremost Irish republican women of the twentieth century .
Sir Francis Pemberton ( 18 July 1624 -- 10 June 1697 ) was an English judge and briefly Lord Chief Justice of the King 's Bench in the course of a turbulent career .
Sir Charles Wheler , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1620 - -1683 ) of Birdingbury , Warwickshire , was an English cavalry office who served in the English and Spanish armies .
Flaithniadh mac Congal ( died 776 ) was Abbot of Clonfert , Ireland .
Sir Alexander William Shaw ( 27 October 1847 -- 1923 ) was an Irish bacon manufacturer and the founder of Limerick and Lahinch golf clubs .
Michael Maddox ( 1747 - -1822 ; Russian : Михаил Егорович Маддокс , Mikhail Yegorovich Maddox , also spelled Medoks , Maddocks , Mattocks ) was an English entrepreneur and theatre manager active in Imperial Russia .
Demetrios Palaiologos Metochites ( Greek : Δημήτριος Παλαιολόγος Μετοχίτης ; died 29 May 1453 ) was a Byzantine nobleman and high - ranking governor and official , who served as the last Byzantine governor of Constantinople .
Lewis H. Michaux ( 1884/5 - -1976 ) was a Harlem bookseller and civil rights activist .
Henry J. Crocker ( 1861 -- 11 October 1912 ) was a prominent San Franciscan businessman , one of the Committee of Fifty formed after the 1906 San Francisco earthquake and a noted philatelist .
Sir Moropant Vishvanath Joshi KCIE ( 1861 - -1962 ) was a leading barrister of Amravati , Central Provinces and Berar .
Brad Darrach ( real name Henry Bradford Darrach Jr. ; 1921 - -1997 ) was a journalist and film critic .
Bartholomew Augustine Santamaria , usually known as B. A. Santamaria ( 14 August 1915 -- 25 February 1998 ) , was an Australian Roman Catholic anti - Communist political activist and journalist .
Raymond Razafimbahiny ( 1919 - -1963 ) better known as R.R. Majunga was an artist known beyond the borders of his native Madagascar .
David Frankfurter ( 9 July 1909 -- 19 July 1982 ) was a Croatian Jew known for assassinating Swiss branch leader of the German NSDAP Wilhelm Gustloff in 1936 in Davos , Switzerland .
Rafic Charaf ( Baalbek , Lebanon , 1932 -- Beirut 2003 ) was a Lebanese painter .
Henry Bachtold DSO MC ( 22 August 1891 -- 9 May 1983 ) was an Australian soldier and railway engineer .
Reynolds Calthorpe of Elvetham in Hampshire ( Ampton , 12 August 1655 -- 1719 ) was a Whig Member of Parliament for Hindon .
Anacleto del Rosario ( born on 13 July 1860 at Santa Cruz , Manila -- died on 2 May 1895 ) was a leading chemist in the Philippines during the Spanish era in Philippine history .
Dúngal Eilni mac Scandail ( died 681 ) was a Dal nAraide king of the Cruithne .
Alby De Luca ( 9 November 1908 -- 30 June 1978 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Henry Harford ( April 5 , 1758 -- April 1835 ) , 5th Proprietor of Maryland , was the last proprietary owner of the British colony of Maryland .
Sean Earley ( May 7 , 1953 - May , 1992 ) was an American artist who resided mostly in the state of Texas .
( Benjamin ) Ifor Evans , Baron Evans of Hungershall ( 19 August 1899 -- 28 August 1982 ) was a British academic and university administrator .
Peter Nead ( 7 January 1796 - 16 March 1877 ) was an American preacher in the German Baptist Brethren church .
George Rigg ( 19 July 1814 -- 18 January 1887 ) was a Scottish Roman Catholic bishop who served as the Bishop of Dunkeld from 1878 to 1887 .
05 Andrew Jeptha died in South Africa in 1920 .
Charles Lisner ( 1928 - 1988 ) was the founder and first artistic director of the Queensland Ballet .
Adrian Hoven ( 18 May 1922 -- 28 April 1981 ) was an Austrian actor , producer and film director .
Ala al - Din Husayn ( Persian : علاء الدین حسین ) was king of the Ghurid dynasty from 1149 to 1161 .
Emanuel Vogel Gerhart ( born Freeburg , Snyder County , Pennsylvania , 13 June 1817 ; died Lancaster , Pennsylvania , 6 May 1904 ) was an American minister of the German Reformed Church .
Georg , Prince of Saxe - Meiningen ( 11 October 1892 -- 6 January 1946 ) was the head of the house of Saxe - Meiningen from 1941 until his death .
Sid French ( 1920 - -1979 ) was a British communist activist and organiser , former Surrey district secretary of the Communist Party of Great Britain ( CPGB ) and the founding general secretary of the New Communist Party of Britain .
Gui d'Ussel , d'Ussèl , or d'Uisel ( fl . 1195 - -1209 ) was a turn - of - the - thirteenth - century troubadour of the Limousin .
Sir Thomas FitzGerald of Laccagh ( c.1458 - 1487 ) , younger son of the 7th Earl of Kildare , was Lord Chancellor of Ireland under Richard III and Henry VII , but rebelled against Henry and was killed at the Battle of Stoke .
Felix Patrick Quinn ( 2 November 1874 -- 28 March 1961 ) was a Canadian industrialist and parliamentarian .
Geoffrey Reginald Gilchrist Mure ( /ˈdʒɛfri ˈrɛdʒənəld ˈɡɪlkrɪst mjʊər/ ; 1893 - -1979 ) was a British idealist philosopher and Oxford academic , who specialised in the works of the German philosopher , Hegel .
Sir John Mark Frederick Smith , KH ( 1790 - -1874 ) was a British general and colonel - commandant of the Royal Engineers .
Dearmid O'Cuana ( died 1248 ) , also spelled Dairmid O'Cuana , was a priest of the Diocese of Elphin in what is now County Sligo .
Axel Otto Normann ( 23 January 1884 -- 8 May 1962 ) was a Norwegian journalist , newspaper editor , theatre critic and theatre director .
Sir William Dalston , 1st Baronet ( died 13 January 1683 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1644 .
Franca Dominici ( 25 June 1907 -- 14 October 1999 ) was an Italian actress and voice actress .
Gregory V of Cilicia ( Armenian : Գրիգոր Ե. Քարավեժ ) was the Catholicos of the Armenian Apostolic Church from 1193 to 1194 .
Roberto Donis ( b. February 26 , 1934 -- d. 2008 ) was a Mexican painter and art teacher .
Joan Hassall ( 3 March 1906 -- 6 March 1988 ) was a wood engraver and book illustrator .
Anthony Ledwith CBE , FRS ( 4 August 1933 -- 5 January 2015 ) was a British chemist .
Udugama Sri Buddharakkitha Thero ( 17 March 1930 - 8 April 2015 ) was a Sri Lankan Buddhist monk , who was the 20th Mahanayaka of the Asgiriya chapter of Siyam Nikaya .
Silvi Vrait ( 28 April 1951 -- 28 June 2013 ) was an Estonian singer and music teacher .
Nigel Cassidy ( 7 December 1945 -- 19 May 2008 ) was an English footballer .
Sir James Hurtle Fisher ( 1 May 1790 -- 28 January 1875 ) was a lawyer and prominent South Australian pioneer .
Arise Evans ( or Rhys or Rice Evans ) ( 1607 - 1660 ) , was a Welsh prophet and fanatic .
Broughton Benjamin Pegge Burnell ( c. 1774 - - 1850 ) was a landowner who lived at Beauchief Abbey and Winkbourn Hall .
Vernon Hazel ( 28 October 1889 -- 18 April 1967 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for St Kilda , Melbourne and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Lucy Evelyn Cheesman ( 8 October 1881 , Westwell , Kent -- 15 April 1969 , London ) was a British entomologist and traveller .
Jascha Silberstein ( 21 April 1934 , Stettin , Germany , ( today Szczecin , Poland ) -- 21 November 2008 , Hot Springs , Arkansas ) was a German - born American musician .
Eugene Lindsay Bishop ( 1886 - 1951 ) was an American physician who served as the Commissioner for the Tennessee State Health Department from 1924 - 1935 and as the Director of the Health and Safety Department of the Tennessee Valley Authority ( TVA ) from 1935 - 1951 .
William St. Clair Tisdall ( 1859 - -1928 ) was a British historian and philologist who served as the Secretary of the Church of England 's Missionary Society in Isfahan , Persia .
Erasmo Marotta ( 1576 - -1641 ) was a Jesuit Sicilian composer of motets and madrigals .
Simpson McCall ( December 5 , 1807 -- 1898 ) was an Ontario farmer , businessman and political figure .
Jon Eriksson Helland ( 1790 - -1862 ) , born Jon Eriksson Hellos , was a Norwegian Hardanger violin maker from Bø in Telemark .
Abdelaziz al - Tebaa or Sidi Abdelaziz ibn Abdelhaq Tabbaa al - Hassani ( died 1499 ) was the founder of the first sufi zawiyya of the Jazuli order in Marrakesh .
Richard D. Lines ( died June 1992 ) was an American amateur astronomer .
Ballard Berkeley ( born Ballard Blascheck ; 6 August 1903 -- 16 January 1988 ) was an English actor of stage and screen .
George William Coventry , 11th Earl of Coventry ( born 25 January 1934 ; died 14 June 2002 in Málaga , Spain ) was a British hereditary peer and politician of the Conservative Party .
Jean - Philippe Maitre ( 18 June 1949 -- 1 February 2006 ) was a Swiss politician , member of the Swiss National Council ( 1983 - 2005 ) .
Mary Anna Draper ( 1839 - 1914)(née Palmer ) was an American astronomer known for her work with astronomical photography .
Trevor Drayton ( 18 February 1955 -- 17 January 2008 ) was an Australian winemaker , frequently described as an `` icon '' of the Australian wine industry .
Felix Idubor ( 1928 - -1991 ) was a Nigerian sculptor from Benin City , an African city with a rich history of artistic excellence .
V. Ramaswamy Aiyer ( 4 August 1871 -- 22 January 1936 ) was a civil servant in the Madras Provincial Service .
Johannes Wilhelm Meinhold ( 27 February 1797 -- 30 November 1851 ) was a Pomeranian priest and author .
Carl Theodor Schulz ( 5 April 1835 -- 16 August 1914 ) was a Norwegian gardener .
Gustav Karl Wilhelm Hermann Karsten ( 6 November 1817 , in Stralsund -- 10 July 1908 , in Zoppot ) was a German botanist and geologist .
Gladys Skillett ( 2 May 1918 -- 11 February 2010 ) , born Gladys Eileen Dillingham , was a British Guernsey nurse .
Charles Sholto Wyndham Marcon ( 31 March 1890 -- 17 November 1959 ) , known as Sholto Marcon , was a Church of England schoolmaster , clergyman and international field hockey player .
Jack Macgougan ( 21 August 1913 -- 12 December 1998 ) was a trade unionist and socialist activist in Ireland .
Henry II , Prince of Anhalt - Aschersleben ( 1215 -- 12 June 1266 ) was a German prince of the House of Ascania and ruler of the principality of Anhalt - Aschersleben .
Benjamin Petre ( 10 August 1672 -- 22 December 1758 ) was an English Roman Catholic prelate , Vicar Apostolic of the London District from 1734 .
Bernard Gates ( The Hague , 23 April 1686-North Aston , 15 November 1773 , aged 87 ) was an English composer , and a bass singer employed by Handel in his oratorios .
Jules Fétique ( 1875 in Mirecourt ( Vosges ) -- 1951 in Gagny ( Seine Saint Denis ) ) was a prominent French archetier from a family of bowmakers .
Bastiaan Ort ( born 6 January 1854 in Gorinchem -- died 4 November 1927 in The Hague ) was a Dutch lawyer , judge and politician .
William Roy Genders ( 21 July 1913 -- 28 September 1985 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1946 , for Worcestershire from 1947 to 1948 and for Somerset in 1949 .
Jane Ellen Harrison ( 9 September 1850 -- 15 April 1928 ) was a British classical scholar , linguist and feminist .
Philip Michael Faraday ( 1 January 1875 -- 6 February 1944 ) was an English lawyer , surveyor , composer , organist and theatrical producer .
Johann Niemann ( 4 August 1913 -- 14 October 1943 ) was a German SS - Untersturmführer ( Second Lieutenant ) and deputy commandant of Sobibor extermination camp .
Henry Sully ( 1680 - -1729 ) was an English clockmaker .
Nicolae Densușianu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( nikoˈla.e densuʃiˈanu ) ; 1846 - -1911 ) was a Transylvanian - born Romanian ethnologist and collector of Romanian folklore .
Aleksey Semyonovich Vishnyakov ( Russian : Алексей Семенович Вишняков ) ( 1859 - -1919 ) was a Russian entrepreneur and philanthropist .
Jonathan Raine ( 1763 - -1831 ) was an English barrister , judge and politician .
Eleanor Power ( died 11 October 1754 ) was the first English woman to be executed in what is today Canada .
William Henry Chippendale ( 14 August 1801 -- 3 January 1888 ) was an English actor , known in particular for his portrayal of old men .
Roberta Leigh was an assumed name for Rita Lewin ( née Shulman ) ( 22 December 1926 -- 19 December 2014 ) was a British author , artist and television producer .
William Wishart ( or Wischard ) ( died 28 May 1279 ) was a 13th - century Bishop of St. Andrews .
Lieutenant Colonel Herbert Walter Styles ( 4 April 1889 -- 5 October 1965 ) , known as Walter Styles , was a British soldier and Member of Parliament .
Saadia Kobashi ( Hebrew : סעדיה כובשי‎ ; Arabic : سعديه كوبشي‎ , 1904 - -1990 ) was a leader of the Yemenite Jewish community in Israel , and one of the signatories of the country 's declaration of independence .
Peter Reidy ( c. 1874 -- 17 January 1932 ) was an Australian politician who represented the South Australian House of Assembly multi - member seat of Victoria from 1915 to 1932 .
Thomas Ray Lippert ( 1950 - -1999 ) was a former convict and former business law professor at Southwest State College in Marshall , Minn. who worked at a fertility clinic named Reproductive Medical Technologies Inc. in Utah from 1988 to the mid 1990s where he reportedly replaced customer 's DNA with his own .
Jacek Karpiński ( 9 April 1927 -- 21 February 2010 ) was a Polish pioneer in computer engineering and computer science .
Juan Núñez I de Lara y León A.K.A. el Gordo ( d. Córdoba , April 1294 ) was a Spanish noble .
Eugène Joseph Verboeckhoven ( 9 June 1798 -- 19 January 1881 ) , Belgian painter , was born at Warneton in West Flanders .
Herman VII , Margrave of Baden - Baden , nicknamed the Clock , ( 1266 -- 12 July 1291 ) , was the ruling Margrave of Baden from 1288 until his death .
Richard Tottel ( died 1594 ) was an English publisher and influential member of the legal community .
Theodore Roscoe ( 1906 - -1992 ) was an American biographer and writer of adventure , fantasy novels and stories .
Goldsworthy Lowes Dickinson ( 6 August 1862 -- 3 August 1932 ) , known as Goldie , was a British political scientist and philosopher .
John Edward Errington ( 29 December 1806 -- 1862 ) was an English civil engineer , particularly noted for his work on railway construction in the United Kingdom .
Rudolf Hellgrewe ( 6 October 1860 -- 1935 ) was a landscape painter and illustrator .
Robert Earl Roeder ( 16 May 1931 -- 15 November 1998 ) was a historian and academic administrator who was one of the founders of the World History Association .
Peter Ernst I von Mansfeld - Vorderort ( 20 July 1517 -- 22 May 1604 ) was an Imperial and Spanish army commander of German origin and Governor of the Spanish Netherlands from 1592 to 1594 .
Sir Maurice Abbot ( Morris ) ( 1565 - -1642 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1626 .
Essam Baheeg ( Arabic : عصام بهيج‎ ) ( born 26 February 1931 - -4 December 2008 ) was an Egyptian footballer who played as a winger for Zamalek .
Captain Baltasar Fernandes ( also spelled Baltazar or Balthazar ) ( c.1580 - ~1667 ) was a Portuguese colonist of Brazil who led the expeditions called Bandeirantes into the interior seeking gold , silver , and iron .
Tibor Antalpéter ( 4 February 1930 -- 15 September 2012 ) was a Hungarian volleyball player who played for Csepel SC and the Hungarian national team .
Jean Joseph Étienne Lenoir also known as Jean J. Lenoir ( 12 January 1822 -- 4 August 1900 ) was a Belgian engineer who developed the internal combustion engine in 1858 .
Pál Maléter ( 4 September 1917 -- 16 June 1958 ) was the military leader of the 1956 Hungarian Revolution .
Eduard Flipse ( 26 February 1896 in Wissenkerke -- 12 September 1973 in Breda ) was a Dutch conductor and composer , the son of Cornelis Flipse and Geertje Kruis .
Caroline Chapman ( c. 1818 , London -- 8 May 1876 , San Francisco ) was an early - American actress ( early - to - mid-19th century ) , who spent a large part of her adult life acting in the theatres of San Francisco .
Dmitry Gulia ( Abkhaz : Дырмит Иасыф-иҧа Гәлиа ; Georgian : დიმიტრი გულია ; 9 February 1874 -- 7 April 1960 ) was an Abkhazian Soviet writer and poet , considered to be one of the founders of Abkhaz literature .
Eric Sharp , Baron Sharp of Grimsdyke , CBE ( 17 August 1916 in London - 2 May 1994 in London ) was a British business man and Member of the House of Lords .
Harold Orlob ( 3 June 1883 -- 25 June 1982 ) was a native of Logan , Utah who became a major composer and lyricist for Broadway theatre productions .
Jacob Liv Borch Sverdrup ( 8 February 1775 -- 15 May 1841 ) was a Norwegian educator and farmer , known for establishing the first agricultural school in Scandinavia .
John Proude ( died ca . 1409 ) , of Sellindge and Canterbury , Kent , was an English politician .
Lorenzo Quiros ( 1717 -- 1789 ) was a Spanish historical painter , and imitator of Murillo .
Gino Bramieri ( ˈdʒiːno braˈmjɛːri ) ( 21 June 1928 -- 18 June 1996 ) was an Italian comedian and actor .
Mary Merrall ( 5 January 1890 -- 31 August 1973 ) , born Elsie Lloyd , was an English actress whose career of over 60 years encompassed stage , film and television work .
Alan Rait ( 9 November 1908 -- 24 March 1965 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Philip Baston or Boston ( died 1320 ? ) , was an English Carmelite .
Billy McGregor ( 20 November 1876 -- 9 August 1919 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Bouvier ( 1787 - -1851 ) , American jurist and legal lexicographer , was born in Codognan , France .
Henry Sparrow ( 13 June 1889 -- 1973 ) was an English professional footballer who played for Faversham Thursday , Portsmouth , Sittingbourne , Croydon Common , Leicester Fosse , Tottenham Hotspur and Margate .
Abolhassan Diba ( 4 January 1894 - 16 April 1982 ) was born in Tabriz , Iran to a well - established family which can trace its line from the 8th century .
Otto Tief ( 14 August ( O.S. 2 August ) 1889 -- 5 March 1976 ) was an Estonian politician , military commander during the Estonian War of Independence , and lawyer .
Henry van Hien ( 1857 or 1858 -- 4 July 1928 ) was a Gold Coast merchant , politician , and nationalist leader .
Shiroshi Nasu ( 1888 - 1984 ) was a pioneer in practical humanitarianism , enhancing cooperation in agriculture by learning through multinational experience .
Nemanja Nešić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Немања Нешић ) ( 15 May 1988 -- 6 June 2012 ) was a Serbian rower .
Harold Calvin Marston Morse ( 24 March 1892 -- 22 June 1977 ) was an American mathematician best known for his work on the calculus of variations in the large , a subject where he introduced the technique of differential topology now known as Morse theory .
Katharine Luomala ( September 10 , 1907 - 1992 ) was an American anthropologist known for her studies of comparative mythology in Oceania .
Sir Norman Alexander ( 7 October 1907 -- 26 March 1997 ) was a physicist instrumental in the establishment of many of the modern Commonwealth universities , including Ahmadu Bello University in Nigeria , and the Universities of the West Indies , the South Pacific and Botswana , Lesotho and Swaziland .
Helen Montagu ( 21 April 1928 -- 1 January 2004 ) was an Australian actress , who later became a casting director , stage producer and impresaria in London .
George Arthur Fitton ( 30 May 1902 -- 10 September 1984 ) was an English footballer and cricketer .
Fredrik August Lidströmer ( 1787 - -1856 ) , son of Jonas Lidströmer .
Musa Naghiyev ( 1849 - 1919 ) was an Azerbaijani industrial oil magnate in late 19th - early 20th century .
Xi Zheng ( died 278 ) , courtesy name Lingxian , was an author and politician of the state of Shu Han during the late Three Kingdoms period .
Johan Frederik Classen , frequently also J. F. Classen , ( 11 February 1725 -- 24 March 1792 ) was a Danish - Norwegian industrialist , major general , landowner and founder of Det Classenske Fideicommis .
Elphinstone Jackson ( 9 October 1868 -- December 1945 ) was an English amateur footballer who made one appearance as a full back for England in 1891 .
Chote Chaba ( also written Tsultrim Dakpa ; Chinese : 出稱札巴 ; pinyin : Chūchēng Zhábā ) ( died 1934 ) was a Tibetan lama , the 12th incarnation of the Migyur Khutughtu , and the 18th king of Muli .
Varoujan Hakhbandian ( Persian : واروژان هاخباندیان‎‎ ) , mostly known as Varoujan ( Qazvin 4 December 1936 - Tehran 17 September 1977 ) was an Iranian songwriter , composer and arranger of Armenian descent .
Jan Staubo ( 28 September 1920 -- 15 June 2003 ) was a Norwegian sportsman , politician and sports official .
Giannina Marchini ( Florence , 18 January 1906 - 1976 ) was an Italian sprinter and middle distance runner .
Edmund Sykes ( born at Leeds ; executed at York Tyburn , 23 March 1587 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
Salvatore Di Silvestro , best known as Rino Di Silvestro ( 30 January 1932 - 3 October 2009 ) was an Italian director , screenwriter , producer and actor .
Mathilde Schjøtt ( 19 February 1844 -- 13 January 1926 ) was a Norwegian writer , literary critic , biographer and feminist .
Robert Bouvier ( 1886 - -1978 ) was a Swiss philosopher noted for popularising the work of Ernst Mach in French .
Jean - Pierre Hallet ( 1927 -- 1 January 2004 ) was a Belgian ( born in Africa ) ethnologist , naturalist , and humanitarian best known for his extensive work with the Efé ( Bambuti ) pygmies of the Ituri Rainforest .
Helvécio Martins ( 27 July 1930 -- 14 May 2005 ) was the first person of Black African descent to be called as a general authority of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) .
Jean - André Deluc or de Luc ( 8 February 1727 -- 7 November 1817 ) was a Swiss geologist and meteorologist .
Sir John Fray ( died 1461 ) was a lawyer who served as Baron of the Exchequer from 1426 and Chief Baron of the Exchequer until 1448 .
Arthur J. Stone ( 1847 - -1938 ) , a leading American silversmith , was born , trained and worked in Sheffield , England , and Edinburgh , Scotland , before travelling to the United States in 1884 .
Maria Louisa Charlesworth ( 1 October 1819 in The Rectory , Blakenham Parva -- 6 January 1880 in Nutfield , Surrey ) was an English author of religious books .
Joseph Estlin Carpenter ( 5 October 1844 -- 2 June 1927 ) was a Unitarian minister , the principal of Manchester College , Oxford .
Gyan Mukherjee ( 30 September 1909 -- 13 November 1956 ) was an Indian film director and screenwriter , who worked in Hindi cinema , most known for hits Jhoola ( 1941 ) and Kismet ( 1943 ) .
Nasser Minachi ( 1931 -- 25 January 2014 ) was an Iranian politician who held different ministerial positions at the initial phase of the 1979 Islamic revolution .
Sir John Tregonwell ( died 1565 ) was an English jurist , a principal agent of Henry VIII and Thomas Cromwell in the Dissolution of the Monasteries .
Jocelyn Devas ( died 1886 ) was the founder of the Devas Club in 1884 , a charitable club for young working men in Battersea , south London , England , originally in a room over a coffee shop in Stewarts Road .
Sir Frederick Francis Liddell , KCB , KC , ( 7 June 1865 -- 19 March 1950 ) was a British lawyer and civil servant .
Charles Schneeman ( 24 November 1912 , Staten Island , New York - 1 January 1972 , Pasadena , California ) was an American illustrator of science fiction .
Ken Shutt ( 1928-April 2 , 2010 ) was an American sculptor and watercolorist who was born in Long Beach , California .
Charles Bravo ( 1845 -- 21 April 1876 ) was a British lawyer who was fatally poisoned with antimony in 1876 .
Thomas Villiers , 2nd Earl of Clarendon ( 25 December 1753 -- 7 March 1824 ) , known as Lord Hyde from 1776 to 1786 , was a British peer and Tory Member of Parliament from the Villiers family .
John William Miller ( 1895 - -1978 ) was an American philosopher in the idealist tradition .
Ian Oswald ( 4 August 1929 -- 25 April 2012 ) was a sleep researcher and psychiatrist .
Muhsin al - Hakim ( 1889 - -1970 ) ( Arabic : أية الله العظمي سيد محسن الطباطبائ الحكيم‎ ) was born into a family , the Tabatabaei , renowned for its scholarship .
George Washington Dupee ( July 24 , 1826 -- 1897 ) was a former slave who became a Baptist leader in Kentucky , USA .
Toirdelbach mac Ruaidhi Ó Conchobair , Prince of Connacht , died 1239 .
Ralph Burkei ( 15 December 1956 , Munich -- 26 November 2008 ) was a German TV producer and co - owner of the Bavarian production company C.A.M.P. TV .
Milú ( Maria de Lourdes de Almeida Lemos ) ( 24 April 1926 -- 5 November 2008 ) was a Portuguese actress and singer .
Leonardo Benvenuti ( 8 September 1923 -- 3 November 2000 ) was an Italian screenwriter .
Stephen Mattoon ( May 5 , 1816 -- 1889 ) was an American Presbyterian missionary who worked in Siam from 1847 to 1864 .
Frank J. Hecker ( 1846 - -1927 ) was an American railroad - car manufacturer from Detroit , Michigan
Thomas Ickham ( died 1415 ) , of Canterbury , Kent , was an English politician .
Cesare Hercolani ( 1499 - -1534 ) was an Italian condottiero , or mercenary leader .
Marshall Monroe Kirkman ( July 10 , 1842 -- April 17 , 1921 ) was an American authority on railways , who wrote extensively on the subject of railways .
William Lees ( November 21 , 1821 -- February 1903 ) was an Ontario farmer , merchant and political figure .
Annie Fortescue Harrison ( 1850 or 1851 -- 12 February 1944 ) was an English composer of songs and piano pieces .
Emil Oberhoffer ( 10 August 1867 -- 22 May 1933 ) was a German - born American conductor and minor composer .
Roshan Singh ( 22 January 1892 , Shahjahanpur district - 19 December 1927 , Allahabad ) was an Indian revolutionary who was previously sentenced in the Bareilly shooting case during Non Cooperation Movement of 1921 - 22 .
Jan Kwapiński ( 1885 - -1964 ) , born Piotr Chałupka was a Polish independence activist , politician and statesman .
George Walter Fawcett ( 6 August 1929 -- 10 December 2015 ) was a cricketer from Northern Ireland .
Legh Barratt , erroneously recorded at times as Leigh Barratt ( 11 December , 1871 - 14 December , 1950 ) was an early cricketer from Altrincham in Cheshire , England .
Joe Edelston ( 27 April 1891 -- 10 March 1970 ) was an English professional football player and manager , best remembered for his 17 years serving Fulham in the Football League as a player , caretaker manager and reserve team manager .
Colonel José María San Martín ( 29 March 1811 -- 12 August 1857 ) was born in Nacaome , Honduras to Colonel Joaquín de San Martín and Joaquina Fugón .
Sir Henry Binns , KCMG ( 27 June 1837 -- 6 June 1899 ) was Prime Minister of the Colony of Natal , South Africa from 5 October 1897 -- 8 June 1899 .
Friedrich August Ukert ( 28 October 1780 -- 18 May 1851 ) was a German history scholar , teacher and humanitarian .
Thomas Baynton ( 5 October 1761 -- 31 August 1820 ) was an English medical writer and surgeon .
Andy Bakjian ( Born : August 20 , 1914 to February 26 , 1986 ) was a Hall of Fame Track and Field official and author on the subject .
Mohammad Anwar Elahee ( 9 July 1929 -- 26 November 2010 ) was a Mauritian football player and manager who coached the Mauritian national team at the 1974 African Cup of Nations and the 1985 Indian Ocean Games .
Nathaniel Langdon Frothingham ( 23 July 1793 -- 3 April 1870 ) was an American Unitarian minister and pastor of the First Church of Boston from 1815 to 1850 .
Dieterich Buxtehude ( German pronunciation : ( ˈdiːtəʁɪç bʊkstəˈhuːdə ) ; Danish : Diderich , pronounced ( ˈdiðəʁɪk buksdəˈhuːðə ) ; c. 1637/39 -- 9 May 1707 ) was a Danish - German organist and composer of the Baroque period .
Kwasimukamba or Graman Quassi ( also spelled Quacy , Kwasi and Quasi ) ( ca . 1690 -- ca . 1780 ) was a Surinamese healer , botanist , slave and later freedman of the 18th century , who is today best known for having given his name to the plant species quassia .
Miriam Camp ( 1916 - -1994 ) was an economist , author and State Department official .
Wanda Kosakiewicz ( Ukrainian : Ванда Козакевич ; 1917 - -1989 ) , French theatre actress in the 1940s , was one of Jean - Paul Sartre 's love interests and Olga Kosakiewicz 's sister .
Alexander Dale Oen ( Norwegian pronunciation : ( ɑlɛkˈsɑndər ˈdɑːlə ˈuːən ) ; 21 May 1985 -- 30 April 2012 ) was a Norwegian swimmer .
Preben Uglebjerg ( 16 January 1931 -- 31 May 1968 ) was a Danish film actor and entertainer .
Ragnvald Alfred Roscher Lund ( 24 February 1899 -- 23 October 1975 ) was a Norwegian military officer , with the rank of colonel .
William Augustus Muhlenberg ( 16 September 1796 -- 8 April 1877 ) was an Episcopal clergyman and educator .
Daniel L. Cease ( ? - March 22 , 1928 ) was editor and manager of The Railroad Trainman in Cleveland , Ohio .
William Milton Lamb ( 14 July 1909 -- 21 June 2006 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Julius Grøntved ( sometimes spelled Gröntved ) ( 1899 - 1967 ) was a Danish botanist and phycologist .
John Davies Evans OBE ( 22 January 1925 -- 4 July 2011 ) was an English archaeologist and academic , renowned for his research into the prehistory of the Mediterranean , and especially the prehistoric cultures of Malta .
Emile Weil ( 1878 - -1945 ) was a noted architect of New Orleans , Louisiana .
Karl Franz Lodron ( 1791 - -1828 ) , also known as Count von Lodron , was a Bishop of Brixen .
Evelyn Boscawen , 6th Viscount Falmouth ( 18 March 1819 -- 6 November 1889 ) , was a breeder of race horses and the winner of many classic races .
Sir Ernest Bullock CVO ( 15 September 1890 -- 24 May 1979 ) was an English organist , composer , and educator .
Sister Leonella Sgorbati ( 9 December 1940 - -17 September 2006 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic nun who was murdered in Somalia shortly after controversial comments by Pope Benedict XVI concerning Islam .
John Hayman Packer ( 12 March 1730 -- 16 September 1806 ) was an actor for David Garrick 's company at Drury Lane .
Maria Beling ( 1915 - 1994 ) was a German soprano and film actress .
Sir George Hamilton Kenrick FRES ( 1850 -- 28 May 1939 ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera especially those of New Guinea and he was a councillor in Birmingham .
Jean Henri Simon ( 28 October 1752 -- 12 March 1834 ) was a Belgian engraver and soldier .
Siegfried Graetschus ( 9 June 1916 -- 14 October 1943 ) was a German SS - Oberscharführer ( Staff Sergeant ) at Sobibor extermination camp in World War II during the deadliest phase of the Holocaust in occupied Poland .
Peter Ilsted ( 14 February 1861 , Sakskøbing -- 16 April 1933 , Copenhagen ) was a leading Danish artist and printmaker .
Edward Herrys ( 1612 - 1662 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Georg Joachim Zollikofer ( 5 August 1730 -- 22 January 1788 ) was a Swiss - German theologian who popularized Enlightenment theology , and published several books of sermons and hymns .
Dr. Ivan Lorković ( 1876 -- 1926 ) was a Croatian politician .
Luigi Rusca ( Алоизий Иванович Руска ; 1762 - 1822 ) was a Neoclassical architect from Ticino who worked in Russia and Ukraine between 1783 and 1818 .
Bob Rafkin ( 30 March 1944 -- 2 May 2013 ) was an American singer , songwriter and acoustic guitar player .
Edward Lewis Paraire ( 1826 - -1882 ) was a British theatre and music hall architect of the Victorian era .
Esteban Huertas López ( 1876 - 1943 ) was a Colombian and later Panamanian military commander .
Thomas Baskerfield ( died 1816 ) was an English topographical artist and cartographer who lived in Essex , active from 1785 through 1816 .
Dominic Collins , S.J. , ( 1566 - 31 October 1602 ) was an Irish Jesuit lay brother , an ex - army man , who died for his Catholic faith .
Marigje Arriens ( c. 1520 , Poederoijen , Gelderland -- 18 December 1591 , Schoonhoven ) , was an alleged Dutch witch and one of the better known victims of the witch hunt in the Netherlands .
Alois Plum was born in 1935 , the son of Josef Plum ( d. 1988 ) , who is mainly known for designing ecclesiastical paraments and especially robes and mitres .
Isabel Menzies Lyth ( 1917 - 2008 ) was a British psychoanalyst in the Kleinian tradition , best known for her work on unconscious mechanisms in institutional settings .
Nicholas of Gorran ( or Gorrain ) ( 1232 - -1295 ) was born in Gorron , France .
Zhu Changqing ( Chinese : 朱常清 ; died 1649 ) , Prince of Huai , was claimed to be emperor of the Southern Ming dynasty ; his regime name was Dongwu ( 東武 ) .
Möngke Temür ( Chinese : 猛哥帖木耳 ; pinyin : Měnggē Tiē mù'ěr or 猛哥帖木儿 ; Měnggē Tiē mù er ) or Dudu Mentemu ( ᡩᡠᡩᡠ ᠮᡝᠨᡨᡝᠮᡠ ; 孟特穆 ; Mèngtèmù ) ( 1370 -- 1433 ) was the Jurchen chieftain of the Odoli tribe , one of the three tribes of the lower Sunggari river valley in Manchuria .
Elieser Bassin ( 1840 - -1898 ) was a Russian - Jewish convert to Christianity , and an author and proponent of British Israelism .
Uta of Schauenburg ( ca . 1115/1120 -- ca . 1197 ) was sovereign countess of Schauenberg from 1151 to 1197 .
Makhdoom Muhammad Ameen Faheem ( Urdu : مخدوم محمد امین فھیم‎ ; alt . spelling : Amin Fahim ; 4 August 1939 -- 21 November 2015 ) was a Pakistani populist left - wing figure and a poet .
Zofia Baniecka ( 1917 in Warsaw -- 1993 ) was a Polish member of the Resistance during World War II . In addition to relaying guns and other materials to resistance fighters , Baniecka and her mother rescued over 50 Jews in their home between 1941 and 1944 .
Angela Rosalind Runcie , Baroness Runcie ( née Turner ; 23 January 1932 -- 12 January 2012 ) was a classical pianist and the wife of Robert Runcie , Archbishop of Canterbury .
Hubert Waelrant ( also Waelrand , first name occasionally Hubertus ) ( c. 1517 -- 19 November 1595 ) was a Flemish composer , teacher , and music editor of the Renaissance .
Blessed Serapion of Vladimir ( d. 1275 ) was a bishop of Vladimir .
Catharina Anna Grandon de Hochepied ( 21 May 1767 -- 1803 ) was a Hungarian and Swedish noble .
Rudolf Hoppe ( 29 October 1922 -- 24 November 2014 ) , a German chemist , discovered the first covalent noble gas compounds .
Georg N. Koskinas ( 1885 - 1975 ) was a Greek neurologist - psychiatrist .
Michel Bozon ( c.1949 -- 23 January 1970 ) , was a World Cup alpine ski racer from France .
Georg Wilhelm Heintze ( 4 July 1849 -- 10 January 1895 ) was a Swedish organist , music educator and music conductor .
Capt . James Callaway ( 1783 - -1815 ) , grandson of Daniel Boone .
John Heysham M.D. ( 1753 - -1834 ) was an English physician , now remembered as a statistician .
Aaron Wade ( March 17 , 1916 -- February 1985 ) was an American Middleweight boxer who fought from 1935 - 1950 .
Bogdan Cuvaj ( 21 October 1905 -- 23 July 1983 ) was a Croatian football manager in both club and international competition .
Bob Brooker ( 17 October 1926 -- 11 October 1986 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Lavender Doe is the nickname given to an unidentified murder victim whose body was found in 2006 in Kilgore , Texas .
Augustine Bryan ( died 1726 ) was an English classical scholar , known for his edition of Plutarch 's Lives .
George Alexander Kohut ( February 11 , 1874 -- 1933 ) was an American writer and bibliographer ; born in Stuhlweissenburg ( modern Székesfehérvár ) , Hungary .
Eric Philpott ( 1946 -- 25 December 2015 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a right wing - forward for the Cork senior football team .
Major General Robert Montresor Rogers VC CB ( 4 September 1834 -- 5 February 1895 ) was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Václav Karel Holan Rovenský ( 1644 -- 27 February 1718 ) was Czech baroque composer and organist .
Henry Pinkerton ( 7 May 1915 -- 1986 ) was a Scottish footballer .
Conversations with Gadalla Gubara , builds up a portrait of a great Sudanese film - maker , Gadalla Gubara ( 1920 -- 2008 ) .
Anton Suurkonka ( 12 August 1886 , Valkeala - 31 March 1964 ) was a Finnish farmer , business executive , lay preacher and politician .
Angus Chisholm ( 1908 - -1979 ) was a Canadian Cape Breton fiddler .
Judith Madan ( née Cowper ; 26 August 1702 -- 7 December 1781 ) was an English poet .
Tristão de Bragança Cunha ( Konkani:त्रिस्तांव ब्रागांझ कुन्ह्य ; 2 April 1891 -- 28 September 1958 ) , alternatively spelled as Tristao de Braganza Cunha , was a prominent Indian nationalist and anti - colonial activist from Goa ( then part of Portuguese India ) .
Sebastian Bach Mills ( 13 March 1839 -- 21 December 1898 ) was a noted English pianist , composer and piano instructor who made his concert career in the United States and gave the first American performances of many important works .
Ambrose Foss ( c. 1803 in England -- 1862 in Sydney , Australia ) was a chemist , druggist and dentist in Sydney .
K. Rajah Iyer ( 15 July 1890 - 18 February 1974 ) was an Indian lawyer of the Madras High Court who served as Advocate - General of Madras Presidency from July 1945 to 1950 .
Juan Alonso Idiáquez , 2nd Duke of Ciudad Real ( Milan , 1597 -- 25 November 1653 ) , was a Spanish noble and naval commander .
Pierre Van Halteren ( 24 February 1911 -- 23 September 2009 ) was a Belgian liberal politician and burgomaster from Brussels ( 1975 - -1982 ) .
Ditmar Koel , also Dithmar Koel , Ditmar Kohl or Dietmar Koehl ( born around 1500 , died 22 September 1563 in Hamburg ) , was a Captain , successful pirate hunter and Mayor of Hamburg .
