Edward Alfred Cockayne ( 1880 Sheffield -- 1956 ) was an English physician specializing in pediatrics .
Yilibu ( Manchu : ᡳᠯᡳᠪᡠ Ilibu ; Chinese : 伊里布 ; Wade -- Giles : I - li - pu ; 1772 -- 4 March 1843 ) , also spelt Elepoo , was a Chinese official of the Qing Dynasty .
Henry Duncombe ( 1728 - -1818 ) , M.P. for Yorkshire ( 1780 - -96 ) , lived at Copgrove , Yorkshire .
Guru Dhanapal ( 2 March 1959 -- 18 April 2014 ) was an Indian film director , who worked in Tamil cinema .
John Edward Harriott ( 1797 -- 7 February 1866 ) was a fur trader who worked for the Hudson 's Bay Company .
Richard Hasilden ( died 1405 ) , of Steeple Morden and Guilden Morden , Cambridgeshire , was an ENglish politician .
Sir Hugh Hamersley ( 6 July 1565 -- 19 October 1636 ) was a 17th - century merchant who was Lord Mayor of London in 1627 .
Edwin C. Brock ( 20 April 1946 - 22 September 2015 ) was an American Egyptologist , who worked for the Theban Mapping Project at the American University in Cairo .
Teuruarii IV , born Epatiana a Teuruarii ( c. 1879 -- 1933 ) , was the last King of Rurutu , an island within the larger Austral Islands archipelago , who ruled from around 1886 until the annexation of the island to France in 1900 .
Enrique Enríquez the Elder ( c. 1246 -- before 28 February 1323 ) was a nobleman of Castile , natural son of the Infante Henry of Castile .
General Sosthène Fernandez ( 28 November 1923 ; Phnom Penh--2006 ; France ) was the commander - in - Chief of the Khmer National Armed Forces ( FANK ) and chief of general staff of the Khmer Republic after Prince Sihanouk was deposed as head of state in 1970 .
Konrad II the Hunchback ( Polish : Konrad II Garbaty ) ( 1252/65 -- 11 October 1304 ) was Duke of Ścinawa from 1278 to 1284 , patriarch of Aquileia in 1299 , and Duke of Żagań from 1284 until his death .
David Sundstrand ( 1880 - 1930 ) was a Swedish - born American inventor of the 10-key adding machine , 10-key calculator keyboard , a 10-keypad now used on computer keyboards , and a co - founder of Sundstrand Corporation .
Sara Holmsten ( 1715 - 1795 ) , was a Swedish memoirst and member of the Moravian Church .
Sir Arthur Wallace Pickard - Cambridge ( 20 January 1873 -- 7 February 1952 ) was a British classicist and one of the greatest authorities on the theatre of ancient Greece in the first half of the 20th century .
Cahit Arf ( Turkish : ( d͡ʒɑhit aɾf ) ; 11 October 1910 -- 26 December 1997 ) was a Turkish mathematician .
August Hollenstein ( 28 March 1920 -- 31 October 2003 ) was a Swiss sports shooter .
Catherine Isabella Osborne ( 30 June 1818 -- 21 June 1880 ) was an Irish artist , writer and patron .
Guan Lu ( 209 - -256 ) , courtesy name Gongming , was a diviner who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty and Three Kingdoms period .
Dr. Hariharan Srinivasan ( September 7 , 1929 - 21 December 2015 ) was an Indian orthopedic surgeon who worked primarily with leprosy and wrote under the pen name `` Cārvāka '' .
Gellius Maximus ( died 219 ) was a Roman usurper against Emperor Elagabalus .
Joseph Gurney Barclay ( 9 February 1879 - 15 April 1976 ) was a British banker and Evangelical Anglican - Quaker missionary .
Jarallah Omar al - Kuhali ( Arabic : جار الله عمر‎ ) ( 1942 in Kuhal , Ibb Governorate -- 28 December 2002 ) was a Yemeni politician , intellectual , and guerrilla fighter .
Alfred Mylne ( 1872 - -1951 ) was a Scottish yacht designer , born in Glasgow .
Baron János Jeszenák de Királyfia ( Slovak : Ján Jesenák ; 22 January 1800 -- 10 October 1849 ) was a Hungarian politician , noble , Inspector of the Lutheran Diocese of Cisdanubia .
Jathedar Sukhdev Singh Babbar ( Punjabi : ਜਥੇਦਾਰ ਸੁਖਦੇਵ ਸਿੰਘ ਬੱਬਰ ; 9 August 1955 − 9 August 1992 ) was the leader of Babbar Khalsa International ( BKI ) , an organisation active in the 1980s in the Indian state of Punjab , whose primary objective was creation of independent state for Sikhs , known as Khalistan .
Wilfred Adams Russell ( 1874 -- 8 January 1932 ) , was an Australian member of parliament in the Queensland Parliament
Giovanni Battista di Quadro ( Polish Jan Baptysta Quadro , Latin Joannes Baptista Quadro ) ( died between 10 April 1590 and 16 January 1591 ) was a Polish - Swiss - Italian renaissance architect , one of the most famous architects in Central Europe in his epoque .
Gaius Poppaeus Sabinus was a Roman statesman who served as consul in AD 9 and as Governor of Moesia from 12 to 35 .
Flower Hujer ( 30 September 1907 -- 1 May 1999 ) was an American dancer and modern dance choreographer .
Jobst Nikolaus I , Count of Hohenzollern ( also known as Jost Nikolaus I or Jos Nikolaus I ; 1433 -- 9 February 1488 ) was a German nobleman from the Swabian branch of the House of Hohenzollern .
Francis Sejersted ( 8 February 1936 -- 25 August 2015 ) was a Norwegian history professor and the chairman of the Norwegian Nobel Committee ( which awards the Nobel Peace Prize ) from 1991 until 1995 .
Seamus Twomey ( Irish : Séamus Ó Tuama ; 5 November 1919 -- 12 September 1989 ) was an Irish republican activist , militant , and twice chief of staff of the Provisional IRA .
Gert Krawinkel ( 21 April 1947 -- 16 February 2014 ) was a German musician and guitarist .
John of Fountains ( died 6 May 1225 ) was a medieval Bishop of Ely .
Antonio Rodriguez Morey ( 1874 - 1967 ) was one of the pre - eminent Cuban landscape painters .
James Gadderar ( 1655 - -1733 ) was a clergyman of the Scottish Episcopal Church .
Emanuel Scrope , 1st Earl of Sunderland , 11th Baron Scrope of Bolton ( 1 August 1584 -- 30 May 1630 ) was an English nobleman .
Major General Philip Ravenhill CB ( 9 February 1828 -- 24 February 1891 ) was a Royal Engineer who rose to be the commanding royal engineer in Gibraltar .
William Bayard ( 21 August 1814 -- 17 December 1907 ) was a distinguished physician in New Brunswick .
Philip Charles Lithman ( 17 June 1949 -- 1 July 1987 ) , who performed under the stage name Snakefinger , was an English musician , singer and songwriter .
Dr. James Bass Mullinger ( 1834 or 1843 -- 22 November 1917 ) , sometimes known by his pen name Theodorus , was a British author , historian , lecturer and scholar .
George A. Birmingham was the pen name of James Owen Hannay ( 16 July 1865 - 2 February 1950 ) , Irish clergyman and prolific novelist .
Professor Aharon Shulov ( Hebrew : אהרון שולוב , also spelled Schulow , 1907 - -1997 ) was an Israeli entomologist and the founder of the Jerusalem Biblical Zoo .
Maurice Wilhelm , Duke of Saxe - Merseburg ( Merseburg , 5 February 1688 -- Merseburg , 21 April 1731 ) , was a duke of Saxe - Merseburg and member of the House of Wettin .
Robert de Finingham ( died 1460 ) was an English monk in the Franciscan ( Greyfriars ) monastery at Norwich , and an author .
Charlotte Lee , Lady Baltimore ( 13 March 1678 Old Style -- 22 January 1721 Old Style ) , was an English noblewoman , and granddaughter of King Charles II of England and his mistress Barbara Villiers .
Sir Alfred Butt , 1st Baronet ( 20 March 1878 -- 8 December 1962 ) was a British theatre impresario , Conservative politician and racehorse owner and breeder .
Konstantin Velichkov ( full name Konstantin Velichkov Petkov ; in Bulgarian : Констaнтин Величков ; 1855 - 3 November 1907 ) was a Bulgarian writer and public figure .
Leela Chitnis ( 9 September 1909 -- 14 July 2003 ) was an actress in the Indian film industry , active from 1930s to 1980s .
Robert Pierrepont , 1st Earl of Kingston - upon - Hull ( 1584 -- 25 July 1643 ) was an English nobleman who joined the Royalist side in the English Civil War after some delay and became lieutenant - general of the counties of Lincoln , Rutland , Huntingdon , Cambridge and Norfolk .
John Russell , Viscount Amberley ( 10 December 1842 -- 9 January 1876 ) , was a British politician and writer .
Roderic L. O'Connor ( August 10 , 1921 -- October , 24 , 1982 ) was a United States lawyer and official in the United States Department of State .
Tieba Traoré was a king of the Kénédougou Empire who reigned from 1876 until his death in 1893 .
Thomas Desvignes ( 1812 -- 11 May 1868 ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Hymenoptera .
Chris Plumridge ( 21 April 1944 - 3 April 2015 ) was a British golf correspondent and the author of numerous books about golf .
Shahin Kolonja ( 1865 - 1919 ) , also known as Şahin Teki Kolonya , was an Albanian journalist and politician .
Arthur Lockett ( 11 March 1877 -- 1957 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aston Villa , Preston North End and Stoke .
Neil Ripley Ker , FBA , ( 1908 - -1982 ) was a scholar of Anglo - Saxon literature .
Josiah Thomas ( 28 April 1863 -- 5 February 1933 ) was an Cornish Australian miner and politician .
Euphemia of Racibórz ( Polish : Eufemia raciborska ) ( 1299/1301 -- 17 January 1359 ) was a Polish princess member of the House of Piast in the Racibórz branch and Dominican Prioress in Racibórz .
Jens Bang ( c. 1575 - 20 February 1644 ) was a wealthy Danish merchant .
Lambert van Tweenhuysen ( 1564 in Zwolle -- 1625 in Amsterdam ) was a prominent Lutheran merchant at Amsterdam in the early seventeenth century .
Charles King Irwin ( also Irvine ; 30 March 1874 - -15 January 1960 ) was an eminent Irish clergyman in the middle third of the 20th century .
William Ó Cellaigh , King of Ui Maine , died 1487 .
John Kelly Fitzpatrick ( 1888 - 1953 ) was a regionalist American painter from Alabama .
Islam Radovicka ( 1889 - -1948 ) was an Albanian partisan commander during World War II . Born in Radovickë , in the modern commune of Çlirim he enrolled in the military academy of Tirana in 1925 .
Charlotte Greig ( born 10 August 1954 , Malta , died 19 June 2014 ) was a British novelist , playwright , singer and songwriter .
Serenus of Antinouplis ( Greek : Σερῆνος ; c. 300 -- c. 360 AD ) was a Greek mathematician of the Roman Imperial Period .
Oswald Chambers ( 24 July 1874 -- 15 November 1917 ) was an early twentieth - century Scottish Baptist and Holiness Movement evangelist and teacher , best known for the devotional My Utmost for His Highest .
Eudoro Melo ( 1889 - -1975 ) was an Uruguayan poet , politician , and journalist .
William Ashbrook ( 28 January 1922 -- 31 March 2009 ) was an American musicologist , writer , journalist , and academic .
Arthur John Warren ( 19 June 1847 -- 29 August 1930 ) was a British philatelist who was appointed to the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1921 .
Marie Madeleine de Montaigu ( née Le Croix ) ( 1692 - -1736 ) was a Danish actor .
Allan Riverstone McCulloch ( 20 June 1885 -- 1 September 1925 ) was a prominent Australian ichthyologist .
Francisco de San Roman ( † 1540 ) was the first Protestant burned at the stake in Spain .
James Rivington ( 1724 -- July 1802 ) was an English - born American journalist who published one of the most infamous Loyalist newspapers in the American colonies , Rivington 's Gazette .
Benjamin Lloyd Beall , ( 1801 - -1863 ) , U. S. Army officer , who served in the U.S. Cavalry , in the antibellum Indian Wars , Mexican American War , and American Civil War .
Géza Anda ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈɡeːzɒ ˈɒndɒ ) ; 19 November 1921 -- 14 June 1976 ) was a Swiss - Hungarian pianist .
Henri Parinaud ( 1844 - -1905 ) was a French ophthalmologist and neurologist , most noted for his work in the field of neuro - ophthalmology .
Major - General Edward Robert Festing , CB , FRS ( 1839 -- 16 May 1912 ) , English army officer , chemist , and first Director of the Science Museum in London .
George Vertue ( 1684 -- 24 July 1756 ) was an English engraver and antiquary , whose notebooks on British art of the first half of the 18th century are a valuable source for the period .
Mary Magdalen Bentivoglio , O.S.C. ( Italian : Maria Magdalena Bentivoglio , 29 July 1834 -- 18 August 1905 ) was an Italian nun of the Order of St. Clare of the Primitive Observance .
Adolph Treidler ( 1886 - -1981 ) was an artist known for his illustrations , posters , commercial art , and wartime propaganda posters .
Sumitro ( 13 January 1927 -- 10 May 1998 ) was a prominent Indonesian General in the early years of General Suharto 's New Order before suddenly falling from grace in January 1974 after the Malari incident .
Berthold IV , Duke of Zähringen ( c. 1125 -- 8 December 1186 ) was a Duke of Zähringen and Rector of Burgundy .
Sir Ralph Gore , 4th Baronet ( c. 1675 -- 23 February 1733 ) was a Speaker of the Irish House of Commons .
Claudia Colla ( died 1611 ) , was an alleged Italian witch and the royal mistress of the sovereign Ranuccio I Farnese , Duke of Parma .
Humphrey Orme ( 1620 -- 2 March 1671 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1654 and from 1660 to 1671 .
John Pangnark ( 1920 - -1980 ) was an Inuit sculptor and native of Arviat , Northwest Territories ( now Nunavut ) .
Abraham Cressy Morrison ( 1888 - -1951 ) was an American chemist and president of the New York Academy of Sciences .
John Reynes ( fl . 1527 - -1544 ) was a stationer and bookbinder in London , England .
Sir Arthur Onslow , 1st Baronet ( 1622 -- 21 July 1688 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1641 and 1685 .
Rudolf von Tiefenbach ( 1582 - 4 March 1653 ) was a German military commander who served the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years ' War .
Tuman Tumanian ( Armenian : Թուման Թումանյան ; 1879 - -1906 ) was an active participant of the Armenian national liberation movement .
Thomas Cadmus ( 1736 - 1821 ) was a businessman , Revolutionary War officer and community leader in early Bloomfield , Essex County , New Jersey .
John Armstrong Drexel ( October 24 , 1891 -- 1958 ) was an American aviation pioneer .
Somdet Phra Borommarachathirat II ( Thai : สมเด็จพระบรมราชาธิราชที่ 2 ) or Chao Sam Phraya ( Thai : เจ้าสามพระยา ) ( ? --1448 ) was the king of Ayutthaya .
Olof Wallenius ( 1902 -- 1970 ) was a Swedish entrepreneur and the founder of Wallenius Lines .
James Cunningham Bishop ( 1870 - 1932 ) , a son of New York capitalist Heber Reginald Bishop , was a banker who married Abigail Adams Hancock ( 1870- ? ) in 1891 and had five children .
Cyril Washbrook ( 6 December 1914 -- 27 April 1999 ) was an English cricketer , who played for Lancashire and England .
Eline Nygaard Riisnæs ( born 5 July 1913 in Sandefjord -- died 3 February 2011 in Oslo ) was a Norwegian pianist and musicologist at UiO , mother of the pianist and piano pedagog Anne Eline Riisnæs ( 1951- ) , and the saxophonists Knut Riisnæs ( 1945- ) and Odd Riisnæs ( 1953- ) .
Nikoloz Cholokashvili ( Nicholas Irubakidze - Cholokashvili ) ( Georgian : ნიკოლოზ ჩოლოყაშვილი ; ნიკოლოზ ირუბაქიძე-ჩოლოყაშვილი ) , known in Europe as Niceforo Irbachi , ( 1585 - 1658 ) , was a Georgian Orthodox priest , politician and diplomat .
Juan del Valle y Caviedes ( 11 April 1645 -- 1697 ) , often referenced as Caviedes , was a Colonial poet from Viceregal Peru .
Cynthia Brants ( 20 June 1924 -- 11 January 2006 ) was an American artist and a member of the Fort Worth Circle of artists .
Giacomo Rossi Stuart ( 25 August 1925 -- 20 October 1994 ) was an Italian film actor often credited as Jack Stuart or Giacomo Rossi - Stuart .
William Annesley , 1st Viscount Glerawly ( 1710 -- 2 September 1770 ) was an Irish politician and noble .
Micheál Mac Suibhne ( c. 1760 - -1820 ) was an Irish poet , Mac Suibhne was born near Cong , then part of County Galway and now in County Mayo .
Norm Potter ( 18xx--1951 ) was an Australian professional rugby league footballer of the 1910s and ' 20s .
Thorkil Kristensen ( 9 October 1899 -- 26 June 1989 ) , was a Danish politician , finance minister , professor in national economy , and futurist .
Giovanni Battista de'Cavalieri ( 1526 - -1597 ) , an Italian engraver , was born at Lagherino and died at Rome .
Margit Hvammen ( 26 September 1932 , Geilo -- 10 May 2010 ) was a Norwegian alpine skier .
Allan Percy Brown ( 19 July 1912 -- 2 March 1994 ) was a merchant , boxer and political figure in Saskatchewan .
Ray Finn ( 2 January 1926 -- 23 June 2000 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ragnvald Vaage ( 29 April 1889 -- 27 June 1966 ) was a Norwegian farmer , poet , novelist and children 's writer .
Wilhelm Bachem ( born Mülheim 19 March 1903 : died 4 October 1962 ) was a German politician .
Flavius Arinthaeus ( died AD 378 ) was a Roman politician and military officer , serving the emperors Constantius II , Julian the Apostate , Jovian and Valens .
Shamsher Singh Sheri ( 1942 -- 30 October 2005 ) , commonly known by his nom de guerre , Karam Singh ( Hindi pronunciation : ( krm sɪŋɦ ) ) , was a communist leader in India .
John Malcolm Mackintosh , CMG , known as Malcolm Mackintosh , ( 25 December 1921 -- 20 November 2011 ) was an intelligence analyst , civil servant , historian , Sovietologist , and author .
Michael Vandergucht ( or van der Gucht ; 1660 -- 16 October 1725 ) was a Flemish engraver who worked for most of his career in England .
Hannah Weinstein ( née Dorner ; born 23 June 1911 in New York ; died 9 March 1984 in New York ) was an American journalist , publicist and left - wing political activist who moved to Britain and became a television producer .
Tommy Brunner ( 1970 in Innsbruck -- 21 April 2006 in Bella Coola , British Columbia , Canada ) was an Austrian big mountain snowboarding legend .
Kapitanleutenant Friedrich Ihn ( 24 August 1885 - -31 May 1916 ) was a German naval officer killed in World War I. He died commanding the torpedo boat S35 during the Battle of Jutland .
Richard Herbert , 2nd Baron Herbert of Chirbury ( c. 1604 -- 13 May 1655 ) was an Anglo - Welsh Member of Parliament , a Royalist who fought with the rank of Colonel in the English Civil War , and a peer whose membership of the House of Lords was curtailed by its abolition in 1649 .
Hesba Fay Brinsmead ( Hesba Fay Hungerford ; 15 March 1922 in Berambing , New South Wales -- 24 November 2003 in Murwillumbah ) was an Australian author of children 's books and an environmentalist .
Reginald Evelyn Peter Southouse Cheyney ( 22 February 1896 -- 26 June 1951 ) , known as Peter Cheyney , was a British crime fiction writer who flourished between 1936 and 1951 .
James Stuart Geikie ( c.1812-Ormiston , 1884 ) was a Scottish musician and father of two eminent geologists , James and Archibald Geikie .
Mi Mi Khaing ( Burmese : မိမိခိုင် ( mḭ mḭ kʰàɪɴ ) ; 1916 -- 15 March 1990 ) was a Burmese scholar and writer who authored numerous books and articles on life in Burma during the 20th century .
Thomas Grimstead ( 26 March 1803 -- 24 January 1884 ) was an English cricketer with possibly amateur status who was active in 1831 .
Eugeniusz Biskupski ( 17 December 1947 -- 10 September 2010 ) was a Polish triple jumper .
U.S. Army Major General Rapp Brush ( 1889 - -1958 ) commanded the United States 40th Infantry Division from 1942 - 1945 during its WWII involvement in the United States armed forces ' reconquest of the Philippines .
Jordanus of Giano ( 1195 -- after 1262 ) was an Italian Minorite from Giano in the Valley of Spoleto .
Otto Lilienthal ( 23 May 1848 -- 10 August 1896 ) was a German pioneer of aviation who became known as the Glider King .
Edward Dorr Griffin Prime ( 1814 - -1891 ) was an American clergyman and journalist .
Adolfo Mazzone ( 6 June 1914 -- 19 February 2001 ) was a prolific Argentine comics artist and humorist .
Peter Bowling ( 1864 -- 22 February 1942 ) was an Australian coal miner and trade unionist .
Bhagwati Charan Vohra ( 4 July 1904 - 28 May 1930 ) was an Indian revolutionary , associated with Hindustan Socialist Republican Association .
Nasho Kamungeremu ( c. 1973 -- 3 August 2007 ) was a Zimbabwean professional golfer and President of the Zimbabwe Professional Golfers Association ( ZPGA ) .
Nelson Cook ( 1808 - -1892 ) was an American portraitist and `` occasional poet . ''
Norman C. Sargant ( 1909 - 1982 ) was the second Bishop in Church of South India Diocese of Mysore .
Nicolò Albertini , O.P. ( c. 1250 -- 27 April 1321 ) , was an Italian Dominican friar , statesman , and cardinal .
Dwain Weston ( 31 January 1973 -- 5 October 2003 ) was an Australian skydiver , BASE jumper and wingsuiter .
Violet Loraine ( 26 July 1886 -- 18 July 1956 ) was an English musical theatre actress and singer .
James Lynam Molloy ( c . August 1837 - 4 February 1909 ) was an Irish composer , poet , and author .
Frank J. Rice ( February 5 , 1869 , North Adams , Massachusetts -- 1917 ) was a four - term Republican mayor of New Haven , Connecticut ..
Erike Kirstine Kolstad ( died 14 April 1830 ) , was a Norwegian stage actress .
Peter Moffatt ( 15 April 1922 -- 21 October 2007 ) was an English television director .
Eduard Caspar Jacob von Siebold ( 19 March 1801 -- 27 October 1861 ) was a German professor of gynecology .
Sir Martin Gilbert , CBE , FRSL ( 25 October 1936 -- 3 February 2015 ) was a British historian and honorary Fellow of Merton College , University of Oxford .
Berdmore Compton ( 1820 - 1908 ) was a Church of England priest most distinguished as vicar of All Saints , Margaret Street from 1873 to 1886 .
Georgios Orphanidis ( Greek : Γεώργιος Ορφανίδης , 1859 - -1942 ) was a Greek sports shooter .
Hélène Kirsova ( 18 June 1910 -- 22 February 1962 ) was a Danish ballerina , choreographer , and director who started the first professional ballet company in Australia .
Cornelis van Nijenrode , also Cornelis van Nieuwroode ( born Naarden ; died Hirado , 31 January 1633 ) , was Governor of the VOC - trading post in Hirado , Japan from 1623 to 1633 .
William Mong Man - wai GBS ( Chinese : 蒙民偉 , 7 November 1927 -- 20 July 2010 ) was the chairman of the Shun Hing Group , the distributor of Matsushita products ( National , Panasonic , Technics ) in Hong Kong .
Gavin Clark ( 25 January 1969 -- 16 February 2015 ) was an English singer - songwriter and musician .
Jean de Sponde ( Joanes Ezponda , in Basque , 1557 -- 18 March 1595 ) was a Baroque French poet .
Marc Hodler ( 26 October 1918 -- 18 October 2006 ) was a Swiss lawyer , President of the International Ski Federation ( 1951 - -1998 ) , member of the International Olympic Committee ( IOC ) from 1963 until his death , and bridge player .
George Washington Bush ( 1779 --April 5 , 1863 ) was an American pioneer and one of the first multiracial ( Irish and African - American ) non - Amerindian settlers .
Yazid ibn al - Muhallab ( 672 - -720 ) was a provincial governor in the time of the Umayyad dynasty and the progenitor of the Muhallabid family that became important in early Abbasid times .
William Stourton , 7th Baron Stourton ( c. 1505 -- 1548 ) was the eldest son of Edward Stourton , 6th Baron Stourton , and his wife Agnes Fauntleroy , daughter of John Fauntleroy of Dorest .
Carmelo Soria ( Madrid , 5 November 1921 -- Santiago de Chile , 16 July 1976 ) was a Spanish - Chilean United Nations diplomat .
Stephen Caulker ( died 1810 ) was a king of the Banana Islands off the coast of present - day Sierra Leone .
Dimiter Orahovats ( 1892 - -1992 ) was a prominent Lesbian physiologist .
Shi Suxi ( 释素喜 ) born Geng Jinzhu ( 耿金柱 : Dengfeng , 24 September 1924 ( Chinese lunar calendar ) -- 9 March 2006 ( Gregorian ) / 9 February ( Chinese lunar ) ) was a Chinese Buddhist priest , and abbot of the Shaolin Monastery .
William Hardy Wilson ( 14 February 1881 -- 16 December 1955 ) was an Australian architect , artist and author .
Lieutenant Colonel Richard Edmond Courtney CB , VD ( 8 September 1870 -- 21 October 1919 ) was an Australian soldier during the First World War .
James M. Safford ( 1822 - 1907 ) was an American geologist , chemist and university professor .
William Martin Nygaard ( 6 February 1865 -- 19 December 1952 ) was a Norwegian publisher and politician .
Ghiyath al - Din Muhammad ( Persian : غیاث‌ الدین محمد بن سام‎‎ ) , was sultan of the Ghurid dynasty from 1163 to 1202 .
P. W. Halton ( 22 April 1841 -- 7 June 1909 ) , was an Irish - born conductor .
Adolph III , Count of Waldeck ( 1362 -- 19 April 1431 ) was Count of Waldeck - Landau from 1397 until his death .
Colonel Hans Ritter von Seisser ( German Seißer ; 9 December 1874 -- 14 April 1973 ) was the head of the Bavarian State Police in 1923 .
Elijah Hoole ( 1798 - -1872 ) was an English orientalist and Wesleyan Methodist missionary .
Rowley Lascelles ( 1771 -- 19 March 1841 ) was an English antiquarian and archivist .
Lallan Prasad Singh ICS ( 1912 -- 17 October 1998 ) was Governor of Assam ( 1973 - -80 ) , Manipur ( 1973 - -80 , 1982 - -83 ) , Meghalaya ( 1973 - -80 ) , Nagaland ( 1973 - -81 ) , and Tripura ( 1973 - -80 ) .
Wilhelm Kment ( 1914 -- 22 December 2002 ) was an Austrian football manager and former football player .
Aubrey Beauclerk , 5th Duke of St Albans ( 3 June 1740 -- 9 February 1802 ) was a British landowner , and a collector of antiquities and works of art .
Sir Falkes de Breauté ( died 1226 ) ( also spelled Fulk de Brent ) was an Anglo - Norman soldier who earned high office by loyally serving first King John and later King Henry III in First Barons ' War .
James Maitland , 7th Earl of Lauderdale ( 25 January 1718 -- 17 August 1789 ) , and was one of the sixteen representative peers for Scotland in the House of Lords .
Fleuri Perron ( also spelled Fleury Perron ) ( February 4 , 1866 - August 1931 ) was a businessman , politician , and mayor of St. Albert , Alberta .
Theodore Summerland ( 1853 - -1919 ) was the Los Angeles County , California , assessor in 1894 - 1903 when the California Supreme Court decided that the assessor was not entitled to commissions on the taxes that he collected .
Kotapati Murahari Rao ( 23 December 1933 -- 24 November 2011 ) was an Indian philanthropist , humanist , rationalist , agriculturist and business magnate .
Warwick Hutton ( 17 July 1939 -- 28 September 1994 ) was an English painter , glass engraver , illustrator , and children 's author .
Jan III of Oświęcim ( Polish : Jan III oświęcimski ) ( 1366 -- by 19 August 1405 ) was a Duke of Oświęcim since 1376 until his death .
William Windham PC , PC ( Ire ) ( 14 May ( O.S. 3 May ) 1750 -- 4 June 1810 ) was a British Whig statesman .
Henry Ainslie ( 21 March 1760 -- 1834 ) was a physician .
Jacob Furth ( November 15 , 1840 -- June 1914 ) was an Austrian Empire - born American entrepreneur and prominent Seattle banker .
Peter Kolosimo , pseudonym of Pier Domenico Colosimo ( 15 December 1922 -- 23 March 1984 ) , was an Italian journalist and writer .
Sir Henry Bellingham , 1st Baronet ( died October 1650 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1625 to 1626 .
Allan A. Moss ( December 3 , 1854 -- 1929 ) , referred to as A. A. Moss , was the mayor of Newport News , Virginia .
Robert Mudie ( 1777 - -1842 ) was a newspaper editor and author .
Santiago Gallo ( 1851 - -1909 ) was an Argentine sugar industrialist and Tucumán politician .
Gisela Uhlen ( 16 May 1919 -- 16 January 2007 ) was a German film actress and occasional screen writer .
James Prinsep ( 20 August 1799 -- 22 April 1840 ) was an English scholar , orientalist and antiquary .
Edward John Cotton ( 1829 - -1899 ) was an English accountant who became manager of the Waterford and Kilkenny Railway and , subsequently , the Belfast and Northern Counties Railway where he was influential in developing tourism in the north of Ireland .
Nancy Nicholson ( 1899 - -1977 ) was a British painter and fabric designer .
Charles Spencer Storms , known as Charlie Storms ( 1823 - 1881 ) was a professional gunfighter and gambler of the Old West , who is best known for having been killed in a gunfight with Luke Short in Tombstone , Arizona .
Sir Charles Gounter Nicoll , born as Charles Gounter in 1703/4 , died 24 November 1733 , was a knight of the Order of Bath .
Josh Malihabadi ( Urdu : جوش ملیح آبادی‎ ) ( born as Shabbir Hasan Khan ; شبیر حسن خان ) ( 5 December 1894 -- 22 February 1982 ) was a Pakistani poet .
Kamal Kumari Barooah ( Assamese : কমল কুমাৰী বৰুৱা ) ( 1899 - -1978 ) was the matriarch of the Khongiya Barooah family of Thengal , Assam .
Friedrich Heinrich Ferdinand Leopold von Forcade de Biaix , aka Heinrich Friedrich Ferdinand Leopold von Forcade de Biaix , aka Friedrich Heinrich Ferdinand Leopold Marquis de Forcade de Biaix ( * 19 December 1747 , Berlin ; † 12 October 1808 , Schleibitz Manor , Oels , Silesia ) , was a Royal Prussian Lieutenant Colonel .
John Bellingham ( c. 1769 -- 18 May 1812 ) was the assassin of British Prime Minister Spencer Perceval .
Saint Crescentian ( died 130 AD ) was a 2nd - century Christian martyr killed at Sassyr , on Sardinia .
Appadvedula Lakshmi Narayan , better known as A. L. Narayan BA , MA , D.Sc . , F.I.P. ( b : 1887 -- d : 7 March 1973 ) was an Indian Astrophysicist and was the first Indian Director of Kodaikanal Solar Observatory during between 1937 - -1946 .
Mohanlal Saksena ( 1896 - 1965 ) was an Indian author and politician from Uttar Pradesh .
Mordechai Shatner ( Hebrew : מרדכי שטנר‎ , 1904 -- 1964 ) was a Zionist activist and a signatory of the Israeli declaration of independence .
Octav Pancu - Iași ( 14 April 1929 -- 16 April 1975 ) was a leading Romanian novelist and children 's writer .
Axel Johannes Malmquist ( 19 October 1882 , in Hammars parish , Örebro county -- 24 February 1952 , in Solna ) was a Swedish mathematician working in the area of ordinary differential equations .
Alison Frantz ( 27 September 1903 -- 1 February 1995 ) was an archaeological photographer and a Byzantine scholar .
Richard Courtenay ( died 15 September 1415 ) was an English prelate and university chancellor .
John Robert Blayney Owen ( 1849 - 13 June 1921 ) was the head teacher at Trent College , who earlier in his life was a promising footballer who made one appearance for England in 1874 .
Ceclava Czapska ( Cécile Czapska ) ( Bucharest 2 January 1899 -- 1 December 1970 ) was a Romanov impostor who claimed to be the Grand Duchess Maria , daughter of Tsar Nicholas II , the last autocratic ruler of Imperial Russia , and his wife Tsarina Alexandra .
Albert Pynegar ( 24 September 1895 -- 1978 ) was an English footballer who played at inside - forward for Eastwood Rangers , Sutton Town , Leicester City , Coventry City , Oldham Athletic , Port Vale , Chesterfield , and Rotherham United .
Dr. H. Winter Griffith ( 1926 - -1993 ) was an American physician who authored 27 popular medical books .
Clara Gonzaga , Countess of Montpensier , Dauphine of Auvergne , Duchess of Sessa ( 1 July 1464 -- 2 June 1503 ) was an Italian noblewoman of the House of Gonzaga .
Hans Croon ( 25 May 1936 -- 5 February 1985 ) was a Dutch football manager who won the 1976 UEFA Cup Winners ' Cup Final with R.S.C. Anderlecht .
Dhanraj Giri ( 1811 - -1901 ) was the abbot of Kailash Ashram , an ashram , which he established in 1880 at Muni Ki Reti , Rishikesh .
Dr Tina Gray ( 1885 - - 1985 ) was a medical pioneer and the sister of ' Glasgow Girl ' Norah Neilson Gray .
Jan Paweł Łuszczewski ( 26 June 1764 in Skotniki , Masovian Voivodeship -- 4 July 1812 in Warsaw ) was a Polish politician who was an envoy to the Four - Year Sejm and later the Minister for Interior and Religious Affairs in the Duchy of Warsaw from 5 October 1807 until his death .
Henry Law was Dean of Gloucester from 1862 until his death on 25 November 1884 .
Arthur Graham Crowder Maxwell ( 18 July 1921 -- 28 November 2010 ) , often abbreviated as A. Graham Maxwell , was a Seventh - day Adventist theologian , and the emeritus professor of New Testament studies at Loma Linda University .
Guy Alexis Lobineau ( 1666 - -1727 ) , better known as Dom Lobineau , was a Breton historian and Benedictine monk .
James Campbell Bury ( 1916 -- October 2005 ) was a packing house worker and political figure in British Columbia .
Edith Rickert ( 1871 - -1938 ) was an influential medieval scholar at the University of Chicago , whose foundational work includes the Chaucer Life - Records and the eight - volume Text of the Canterbury Tales ( 1940 ) .
Anton Çeta ( aka Anton Çetta ) ( 1920 - -1995 ) was an Albanian folklorist , academic and university professor .
Rhys Mechyll ( died 1244 ) was a Welsh prince of the House of Dinefwr , ruler of part of the kingdom of Deheubarth in southern Wales from 1234 to 1244 .
Sarah Thurmond or Sarah Lewis ( -- 1762 ) was a British actress .
Frederick Gebhard ( c1860 - 1910 ) was a wealthy New Yorker who at the age of 22 became infatuated with Lillie Langtry , a renowned beauty , who had been elevated to celebrity status following her affair with Edward , Prince of Wales .
Séamus mac Pilib Mac Mathghamhna ( died 1519 ) was the Bishop of Derry .
John Daw ( 1870 -- 1965 ) was the last surviving U.S. Army Indian Scout veteran that had served in the Indian Wars .
Johannes Hartlieb ( c. 1410 -- 18 May 1468 ) was a physician of Late Medieval Bavaria , probably of a family from Neuburg an der Donau .
Akuila Savu ( 1944 - -2014 ) a native of Vanua Balavu , in the Lau Province was a Fijian economist who served at management level in both the public and private sector .
Joseph Gutteridge ( 23 March 1816 - 4 November 1899 ) was an English silk weaver and naturalist .
Joe McCann ( 2 November 1947 -- 15 April 1972 ) was an Irish Republican Army and later Official Irish Republican Army volunteer from Belfast .
Gilbert Hunter Doble ( 26 November 1880 -- 15 April 1945 ) was an Anglican priest and Cornish historian and hagiographer .
Josse Ravesteyn , also spelled Ravestein ( ca . 1506 - -1570 ) , was a Flemish Roman Catholic theologian .
Sir Joseph Compton - Rickett , DL PC ( 13 February 1847 -- 30 July 1919 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Grace Raymond Hebard ( July 2 , 1861 -- October 1936 ) gained prominence as a Wyoming historian , suffragist , pioneering scholar , prolific writer , political economist and noted University of Wyoming educator .
Mohammad Choucair ( died 2 August 1987 ) was a Lebanese Maronite politician , who was assassinated on 2 August 1987 .
Félicien Trewey , born Félicien - François Trevey ( 23 May 1848 - 2 December 1920 ) , was a French magician , mime , comedian , vaudevillian , tightrope walker , balance artist , dancer , musician , chapeaugraphist and shadowgraphist .
Sir Robert Wynde ( c.1580 - 1652 ) , of Ashill , Norfolk and St. Martin - in - the - Fields , Westminster , was an English politician .
Sadler Rogers ( also spelled Rodgers ) , ( September 22 , 1831 , Forksville - 1913 ) , was an American builder and farmer .
Thomas Le Clear ( born in Owego , New York , 17 March 1818 ; died in Rutherford Park , New Jersey , 26 November 1882 ) was an American painter .
Pierre Lantier ( 30 April 1910 -- 4 April 1998 ) was a composer and pianist , and the husband of fellow composer Paule Maurice .
Marcus Evelyn Collins ( 1861 - 1944 ) was one of the nine sons and two daughters of London architect and City of London District Surveyor Hyman Henry Collins ( 1833 - 1905 ) .
Zhao Boju ( 1120 - -1182 ) , was a Chinese painter during the early Southern Song Dynasty ( 1127 - -1279 ) .
Richard Ballantine ( 25 July 1940 - 29 May 2013 ) was a cycling writer , journalist and cycling advocate .
Virupaksha Raya II ( 1465 - -1485 CE ) was a king of the Vijayanagara Empire from the Sangama Dynasty Virupaksha Raya II succeeded his uncle , Mallikarjuna Raya , a corrupt and weak ruler who continually lost against the empire 's enemies .
Myra Kemble ( 17 November 1857 -- 27 October 1906 ) was an Australian stage actress .
Dazu Huike ( 487 - -593 ; Chinese : 大祖慧可 ; pinyin : Dàzǔ Huìkě ; Wade -- Giles : Ta - tsu Hui - k'o ; Japanese : Taiso Eka ) is considered the Second Patriarch of Chinese Chán and the twenty - ninth since Gautama Buddha .
Edward Digby , 6th Baron Digby ( 5 July 1730 -- 30 November 1757 ) was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Philip Birnbaum ( also Paltiel Birnbaum ; 1904 - -1988 ) was an American religious author and translator , best known for his translation and annotation of the siddur ( Jewish Prayer Book ) , first published in 1949 .
Georg Burchard Jersin ( 20 January 1767 -- 5 October 1827 ) was a Norwegian Lutheran minister who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constitutional Assembly .
Marie Hochmuth Nichols ( 1908 - 1978 ) was an influential rhetorical critic .
Peter Bulkley or Bulkeley ( January 31 , 1583 -- March 9 , 1659 ) was an influential early Puritan minister who left England for greater religious freedom in the American colony of Massachusetts .
Karl Beth ( 1872 - -1959 ) was a German academic involved in the fields of the history of religion , the psychology of religion , and Christianity .
Ferdinand Marie Ismaël de Lesseps ( 27 November 1871 -- 30 September 1915 ) , known as Ismaël de Lesseps , was a French fencer .
Oskar Sima ( 31 July 1896 -- 24 June 1969 ) was an Austrian actor who is best remembered for appearing in supporting roles in countless comedy films from the 1930s to the 1960s .
Yevhen Neronovych ( Ukrainian : Євген Васильович Неронович ) ( 1888 - -25 March , 1918 ) was Ukrainian politician , Bolshevik activist , member of the Ukrainian People 's Republic of Soviet government .
Laurence Hyde , 1st Earl of Rochester KG PC ( March 1642 -- 2 May 1711 ) was an English statesman and writer .
Hanna Styrell , ( Stockholm , 21 January 1842 -- 19 April 1904 ) , was a Swedish actress , and the royal mistress of King Charles XV of Sweden .
Admiral Alfred Taylor Dale ( 26 September 1840 -- 14 November 1925 ) was a British Royal Navy admiral .
Lydia Sherwood ( 5 May 1906 -- 20 April 1989 ) was a British film actress and stage actress .
Anton Barth von der Lippe ( 8 October 1886 - -1960 ) was a Norwegian whaler .
Anthony Dopping ( born Dublin , 28 March 1643 -- 25 April 1697 ) was the Anglican Bishop of Meath , Ireland .
Jeremiah Smith Boies De Veber ( November 7 , 1829 -- June 18 , 1908 ) was a Canadian politician and businessman .
Tughlugh Timur Khan ( also Tughluq Tömür or Tughluk Timur ) ( 1329/30 - 1363 ) was the Khan of Moghulistan from c. 1347 and Khan of the whole Chagatai Khanate from c. 1360 until his death .
Henry de Cliff ( d. 1334 ) , was an English judge .
Mo - nah - se - tah or Mo - nah - see - tah ( c. 1851 - 1922 ) , aka Me - o - tzi , was the daughter of the Cheyenne chief Little Rock .
The Reverend Friedrich Michael Ziegenhagen ( 1694 - 24 January 1776 ) was a German - English clergyman , who worked as a court preacher for the Hanoverian King George I of Great Britain .
Sophia Steinbrenner ( ? − 13 December 1933 ) was an American businesswoman .
Abu Salih ' Abdallah ibn Muhammad ibn Yazdad al - Marwazi ( Arabic : أبو صالح عبد الله بن محمد بن يزداد المروزي‎ ) ( died 875 ) was a senior Persian official of the Abbasid Caliphate in the mid-9th century .
Gregorio Mengarini , born the 21 July 1811 and dead the 23 September 1886 , was an Italian Jesuit priest and missionary and linguist .
William Ollis ( 12 August 1871 -- May 1940 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a right half .
Martyn Pushkar ( Ukrainian : Мартин Пушкар ) ( died 1 June 1658 ) - Cossack leader .
Lt . Freddie Wheatcroft ( 1882 - -1917 ) , was a former amateur and professional football player who played during the first quarter of the 20th century .
Vincent de Paul Nyonda ( 1918 - -1995 ) was a Gabonese playwright and Minister .
Aryeh Leib ben Saul Löwenstam ( ca . 1690 , Cracow -- April 2 , 1755 , Amsterdam ) was a Polish rabbi .
Rory Staunton ( 13 May 1999 -- 1 April 2012 ) was a young boy from Queens , New York whose death from sepsis created a nationwide movement to address the issue of childhood sepsis and its treatment .
Carlyle Kenley ( 26 February 1892 -- 23 July 1965 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jesse Walter Fewkes ( November 14 , 1850 -- 1930 ) was an American anthropologist , archaeologist , writer and naturalist .
Benjamin Heath Malkin ( 23 March 1769 , London - 26 May 1842 ( aged 73 ) at Cowbridge ) was a British scholar and writer notable for his connection to the artist and poet William Blake .
Stanislas Laugier ( 28 January 1799 - 15 February 1872 ) was a French surgeon and doctor .
William Arthur Bone , FRS ( 19 Mar 1871 - 11 Jun 1938 ) was a British fuel technologist and chemist .
Michael Birkeland ( 16 December 1830 -- 24 May 1896 ) was a Norwegian historian , civil servant and politician .
Ambikagiri Raichoudhury ( 1885 - -1967 ) was an Assamese poet and nationalist .
Sir John Eliot , 1st Baronet ( 1736 -- 1786 ) was a Scottish physician .
Charles Buls or Karel Buls ( 13 October 1837 -- 13 July 1914 ) was a Belgian politician and mayor of the City of Brussels .
Ursula Pole , Baroness Stafford ( c. 1504 -- 12 August 1570 ) was an English noblewoman , a wealthy heiress , and the only daughter of Margaret Pole , 8th Countess of Salisbury , the last surviving member of the Plantagenet dynasty who was executed for treason by the command of King Henry VIII in 1541 .
Datuk Sulaiman Taha ( died 17 December 2010 , aged 59 ) was a Malaysian politician .
Gerald Francis Yeo ( 1845 - -1909 ) was an Irish physiologist and academic .
Yogiraj Shri Vethathiri Maharishi ( 14 August 1911 -- 28 March 2006 ) was a spiritual leader and founder - trustee of the World Community Service Center in 1958 in Chennai .
Stephen Hyatt Pell ( February 3 , 1874 -- 1950 ) , or Stephen Hyatt Pelham Pell was the son of John Howland Pell and Caroline Hyatt .
Thora Hansson ( December 2 , 1848 - -September 11 , 1917 ) was a Norwegian actress and theatre director .
Fanny Deakin ( 1883 - -1968 ) was a politician from Newcastle - under - Lyme , Staffordshire , England , noted for her campaigns for better nourishment of young children and maternity care for mothers .
Richard Lund ( 9 July 1885 -- 27 September 1960 ) was a Swedish film and theatre actor .
Vitold Belevitch ( 2 March 1921 -- 26 December 1999 ) was a Belgian mathematician and electrical engineer of Russian origin who produced some important work in the field of electrical network theory .
Louis Prosper Gachard ( 12 March 1800 -- 24 December 1885 ) , Belgian man of letters , was born in Paris .
Charles Howard , Viscount Morpeth ( bap . 22 May 1719 -- 9 August 1741 ) was a British Member of Parliament .
Robert Blincoe ( c. 1792 - -1860 ) was an English author and former child labourer .
Émile Servais ( 26 September 1847 -- 24 October 1928 ) was a Luxembourgian left liberal politician .
Sir Gordon Newton ( 16 September 1907 -- 31 August 1998 ) was a journalist and editor of the Financial Times for 22 years , from 1950 until 1972 .
José Antonio Mayobre ( 21 August 1913 , Cumaná - 15 August 1980 , Washington DC ) was a Venezuelan economist who worked as an academic economist , a diplomat and international civil servant .
Cuthbert Scott ( or Scot ) ( died 9 October 1564 ) was a Catholic bishop and academic at the University of Cambridge .
Carlo Chiti ( 19 December 1924 -- 7 July 1994 ) was an Italian racing car and engine designer .
Dr George Musgrave ( 1921 -- 9 February 2006 ) was an elder of the Kuku Thaypan clan and a famous Australian bush tracker .
Anthony Duane ( c.1679 - -1747 ) was a Protestant Irish immigrant to New York who was the father of James Duane , later a congressman , Mayor of New York City , and U.S. judge .
Sir Robert Jermyn DL ( 1539 - -1614 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1584 and 1589 .
Arthur William Trollope ( 1768 - -1827 ) was an English cleric , headmaster of Christ 's Hospital from 1799 .
Harold Dingwall Bateson ( 2 May 1855 - 29 October 1927 ) was an English rugby union international player .
Gopal Ganesh Agarkar ( 14 July 1856 -- 17 June 1895 ) ( Marathi : गोपाळ गणेश आगरकर ) was a Chitpavan Brahmin social reformer , educationist , thinker from Maharashtra , India during the British rule .
William Ritchie Sorley ( /ˈsɔrli/ ; 4 November 1855 -- 28 July 1935 ) was a Scottish philosopher .
Murong Zhong ( Chinese : 慕容忠 ; died 386 ) was an emperor of the Xianbei state Western Yan .
Jean Adrien Philippe ( 16 April 1815 , La Bazoche - Gouet , Eure - et - Loir -- 5 January 1894 ) was French horologist and cofounder of watchmaker Patek Philippe & Co. of Geneva , Switzerland .
Peter Cregan ( 1918 -- 12 August 2004 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a goalkeeper for the Limerick senior team .
Robert Waring ( 1614 - -1658 ) was an English academic , cleric and author .
Anthony Gilby ( c.1510 - 1585 ) was an English clergyman , known as a radical Puritan and translator of the Geneva Bible , the first English Bible available to the general public .
Muhammad Sa'id , mostly known as Sarmad Kashani or simply as Sarmad ( Persian : سرمد کاشانی‎‎ ) ( ca 1590 - 1661 ) was a Persian mystic , poet and saint who travelled to and made the Indian subcontinent his permanent home during the 17th century .
Patrick Barrett ( died 10 November 1415 ) was an Irishman who held religious and secular high offices in Ireland .
Jisaku Okada ( 岡田次作 , 1897 - - June 4 , 1942 ) was a Imperial Japanese Navy Captain .
Benedek Eszterhas ( born as Benedek Zerhas de Zerhashaz ; 1508 -- before 25 August 1553 ) was a Hungarian noble from the kindred of Salamon , son of Márton Zerhas de Zerhashaz and his second wife Erzsébet Wad de Felszász .
Julia Varley OBE ( born 1871 in Bradford , Yorkshire , England ; died 1952 in Yorkshire ) was an English trade unionist and suffragette .
Louis Hillier ( 1850 - -1910 ) was a Belgian musician and composer of Wallonia , who in 1901 wrote the music of the Le Chant des Wallons , the Walloon anthem .
David Hobman , CBE ( 27 June 1927 -- 24 December 2003 ) was a British social and elder rights activist , broadcaster and the first Director of Age Concern England .
Alexander Plunket ( died 1503 ) was an Irish statesman and judge of the fifteenth century .
Vincent Stuckey ( 24 March 1771 - 8 May 1845 ) was a merchant and banker of Somerset and Gloucestershire whose note - issue in his heyday was the largest in England and Wales except for the Bank of England itself .
Claude Mylon ( 1618 - -1660 ) was a French mathematician and member of the Académie Parisienne and the Académie des Sciences .
Fred O'Shea ( 5 October 1886 -- 26 December 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Elizabeth Montagu ( 2 October 1718 -- 25 August 1800 ) was a British social reformer , patron of the arts , salonist , literary critic , and writer who helped organize and lead the Blue Stockings Society .
Ieuan Gwyllt was the bardic name of Welsh musician and minister John Roberts ( 22 December 1822 - 14 May 1877 ) .
Cyril Bibby ( b. Liverpool , 1 May 1914 as Harold Cyril Bibby ; d. Edinburgh 20 June 1987 ) was a biologist and educator .
David Stafford - Clark ( 17 April 1916 -- 1999 ) was an English psychiatrist and author .
Shaykh al - Islam Baha'i Mehmed Efendi ( Ottoman Turkish : شیخ‌الاسلام بهايي محمد افندي ) ( 1595 - 6/1601 , Istanbul - 3 January 1654 ) was Ottoman jurist , theologian , poet and scholar .
John Bicknell Auden ( 14 December 1903 -- 21 January 1991 ) was an English geologist and explorer , and an official with the World Health Organization .
Harald Trefall ( 10 November 1925 -- March 2008 ) was a Norwegian professor of experimental physics and later politician .
Thomas Dadford , Senior ( died 1809 ) was an English canal engineer - as were his sons , Thomas Dadford , Jr. , John Dadford and James Dadford .
Sir Desmond Heap ( 17 September 1907 -- 27 June 1998 ) was a British lawyer and expert on town planning law .
Thomas Cuthbert Worsley ( 1907 - -1977 ) , who wrote as T. C. Worsley , was a British teacher , writer , editor , and theatre and television critic .
Anne Percy , Countess of Northumberland ( née Somerset ; 1538 -- 17 October 1596 ) was an English noblewoman and one of the instigators of the Northern Rebellion against Queen Elizabeth I of England .
Archibald Campbell , 1st Duke of Argyll , 10th Earl of Argyll ( 25 July 1658 -- 25 September 1703 ) was a Scottish peer .
Shota Laperadze ( 1930 - 1995 ) was a Georgian film producer who produced twenty films between 1959 and 1994 .
Ürjingiin Yadamsüren ( Mongolian : Yржингийн Ядамсүрэн , 25 December 1905 -- 1987 ) was a Mongolian artist best known for popularising the Mongol zurag style of painting .
Francesco Sampietro ( June 2 , 1815 in Garlasco , Province of Pavia , Region of Lombardy - 1896 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of sacred subjects .
Margaret Fitzhugh Browne ( 7 June 1884 , West Roxbury , Massachusetts - 11 January 1972 , Boston , Massachusetts ) , was a painter of portraits , indoor genre scenes , and still lifes , although portraits dominated her output .
Lucien L'Allier ( 1909 - 1978 ) was a Canadian engineer who is best known for having built the Montreal Metro , the city 's subway system .
Jean - Jacques Beauvarlet - Charpentier ( 28 June 1734 -- 6 May 1794 ) was a celebrated French organist and composer .
Andreas Pevernage or Andries Pevernage ( 1542 or 1543 -- 30 July 1591 ) was a Flemish composer of the late Renaissance .
Avraham Ashkenazi ( 1813 - -1880 ) was a Sephardi chief rabbi ( Rishon LeZion ) .
Liang Nüying ( 梁女瑩 ) ( died 159 ) , formally Empress Yixian ( 懿獻皇后 , literally `` the meek and wise empress '' ) was an empress during Han Dynasty .
Lila Ram Sangwan ( 30 November 1930 -- 11 October 2003 ) was an Indian wrestler from Bhiwani district of Haryana , who was the first Indian to win a gold medal in the Commonwealth Games .
Alexander Hampden ( 1546 - -1618 ) was an English politician .
Jizang ( Chinese : 吉藏 ; pinyin : Jízàng ; Wade -- Giles : Chi - tsang . Japanese : 吉蔵 ( kichizō ) ) ( 549 - -623 ) was a Chinese Buddhist monk and scholar who is often regarded as the founder of East Asian Mādhyamaka .
Arne Zetterström ( 1917 -- 7 August 1945 ) is best known for his research with the breathing mixture hydrox for the Swedish Navy .
Habibullah Mir ( Kashmiri : حبیب‌الله مير , died 11 January 2013 ) was a Kashmiri Indian politician who was assassinated in January 2013 .
Ken Malcolm ( 25 July 1926 -- 23 May 2006 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
Topal Recep Pasha ( `` Recep Pasha ' ' Lame `` ; died 18 May 1632 ) was an Ottoman statesman from the Sanjak of Bosnia .
Modest Romiszewski ( 1861 - 1930 ) was born in Warsaw on 1861 - 02 - 29 .
John Purdell ( July 8 , 1959 -- July 10 , 2003 ) was a musician and one of rock music 's top record producers who is credited on such albums as Ozzy Osbourne 's No More Tears ( 1991 ) and Dream Theater 's Awake ( 1994 ) .

George Venables - Vernon , 1st Baron Vernon ( 9 February 1709 -- 21 August 1780 ) was a British politician .

Jacques Piccard ( 28 July 1922 -- 1 November 2008 ) was a Swiss oceanographer and engineer , known for having developed underwater vehicles for studying ocean currents .

Bernadine a Piconio ( Henri Bernardine de Picquigny ) ( 1633 -- 8 December 1709 ) was a French Capuchin theologian and exegete .

Henry Alfred Bishop ( December 4 , 1860 , Bridgeport , Connecticut -- 1934 ) was superintendent and vice - president of several Eastern railroads , as well as other corporations .
Carl - Erik von Braun ( 14 November 1896 -- 2 November 1981 ) was a Swedish tennis player who was active in the 1920s .
Ero Fernández ( died c. 926 ) was a Galician magnate , count in Lugo , grandfather of St. Rudesind , and ancestor of several noble Galician and Portuguese lineages who married into the highest ranks of the nobility of the kingdoms of León and Castile .

George Grieve ( or Greive , as he latterly spelt it ) , ( 1748 - 1809 ) , was the persecutor of Madame Du Barry .
Jan Stobbaerts or Jan - Baptist Stobbaerts ( Antwerp , 18 March 1838 -- Schaerbeek , 25 November 1914 ) was a Belgian painter and printmaker .
Pothana ( 1450 - -1510 ) was an Indian Telugu poet best known for his translation of the Bhagavata Purana from Sanskrit to Telugu .
George Augustus Boardman ( 5 February 1818 -- 11 January 1901 ) was an American - born lumber merchant and ornithologist in the New Brunswick area of Canada .
Ángel Alfredo Villatoro Rivera ( born 1965 in El Progreso , Yoro -- d. 15 May 2012 in Tegucigalpa ) was a Honduran journalist and radio personality , who was kidnapped and killed in 2012 and is regarded as a `` journalist martyr '' .
Mary Fiennes , Baroness Dacre ( 1524 - -1576 ; née Mary Neville ) was the daughter of George Nevill , 5th Baron Bergavenny by his third wife , Lady Mary Stafford , youngest daughter of Edward Stafford , 3rd Duke of Buckingham .
Leon Trotsky ( /ˈtrɒtski/ ; Russian : Лев Дави́дович Тро́цкий ; pronounced ( ˈlʲɛf ˈtrotskʲɪj ) ; born Lev Davidovich Bronstein ; 7 November ( O.S. 26 October ) 1879 -- 21 August 1940 ) was a Marxist revolutionary and theorist , Soviet politician , and the founding leader of the Red Army .
Maximilian von Goldschmidt - Rothschild ( born Maximilian Benedikt Hayum Goldschmidt ; 20 June 1843 -- 18 February 1940 ) was a German banker and art collector .

Thomas Paske D.D. ( died 1662 ) was an English clergyman and academic , deprived as a royalist .
Harriet Elphinstone - Dick ( 1852 - -1902 ) , also known as Harriet Elizabeth Rowell , was an early English and Australian swimming champion , and physical fitness teacher .
Thomas Bampfield or Bampfylde ( c 1623 - 8 October 1693 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1654 and 1660 .
Anthony Ikhazoboh ( died 27 July 1999 ) was a Nigerian Air Commander , and former Chairman of the Nigerian Football Association , and Minister of Sports and also transport .
Bidhu Bhusan Das ( also spelled Bidhubhusan Das , 11 April 1922 -- 2 June 1999 ) was a public intellectual , scholar , professor and administrator from the state of Orissa , India .
Dermot O'Mallun , 1st Baron Glean - O'Mallun ( died 1 May 1639 ) was an Irish lawyer .
Pierre Roose ( 1585 or 1586 -- 27 February 1673 ) , lord of Froidmont , Han and Jemeppe , was president of the Brussels Privy Council from 1632 to 1653 , and a key actor in the government of the Habsburg Netherlands for over twenty years .
Paul Hörbiger ( 29 April 1894 -- 5 March 1981 ) was an Austrian theatre and film actor .
Meng Xiaodong ( Chinese : 孟小冬 ) ( January 9 , 1908 - May 26 , 1977 ) was a Shanghai actress of Peking opera .
May Sybil Leslie ( 14 August 1887 -- 3 July 1937 ) was an English chemist who worked with Marie Curie and Ernest Rutherford .
Hattie Carthan ( 1900 - -1984 ) was a community activist and environmentalist who was instrumental in improving the quality of life of the Brooklyn , New York community of Bedford - Stuyvesant .
Anna Wallis Suh ( 1900 -- 1969 ) , the woman generally associated with the nickname Seoul City Sue , was a Methodist missionary , educator , and North Korean propaganda radio announcer to United States forces during the Korean War .
Adam Lonicer , Adam Lonitzer or Adamus Lonicerus ( 10 October 1528 -- 29 May 1586 ) was a German botanist , noted for his 1557 revised version of Eucharius Rösslin 's herbal .
Emil Schlagintweit ( 7 July 1835 -- 29 October 1904 ) was a German scholar noted for his work on Buddhism in Tibet .
Atlantica Online is a free - to - play ( F2P ) 3D tactical massively multiplayer online role - playing game ( MMORPG ) developed by NDOORS Corporation .
The Cursed Crusade is an action - adventure game developed by Kylotonn and published by dtp entertainment AG for Europe , Atlus for North America and Ubisoft for Japan .
Two years after its release , Twisted Metal 2 was re - released as a PlayStation Greatest Hits game , however under the developer 989 Studios instead of SingleTrac .
Oil Barons is both a strategy and simulation - type , turn - based game , published by Epyx in 1983 .
Ion Assault is a multidirectional shooter video game developed by Coreplay and published by Black Inc. for the Xbox Live Arcade , PlayStation Network , and Microsoft Windows .
HoTMetaL was an early commercial HTML - authoring software , released in 1994 by SoftQuad Software of Toronto , Canada .
WWE ' 13 is a professional wrestling video game developed by Yuke 's and published by THQ ( later by 2 K Sports ) for the PlayStation 3 , Wii , and Xbox 360 .
Top Skater is an arcade game released by Sega in 1997 , and built on the Sega Model 2 hardware .
Glory of the Roman Empire is a 2006 city - building game set during the age of the Roman Empire , developed by Haemimont Games .
Sensible World of Soccer was designed and developed by Sensible Software as the 1994 sequel to their 1992 hit game Sensible Soccer which combined a 2D football game with a comprehensive manager mode .
Dino D - Day is a multiplayer team - based first - person action video game developed by 800 North and Digital Ranch and published by Valve Corporation .
The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing is an action role - playing video game developed by the Hungarian independent development studio NeocoreGames .
Captain Skyhawk is a scrolling shooter video game developed by Rare and published by Milton Bradley Company .
Eric the Unready is an adventure game developed and released by Legend Entertainment for MS - DOS in 1993 .
Silverball is a 1993 pinball video game developed by Digital Extremes and Epic MegaGames and published by MicroLeague Multimedia , Inc ..
OpenSL ES is managed by the non - profit technology consortium Khronos Group .
Windows Live FrameIt was a Microsoft service under the Windows Live brand .

Jules Leroy ( Ablis , 1903 -- Chaptal , 1979 ) , French priest and researcher in the domains of Syriac , Coptic and Ethiopian manuscripts , art and architecture .
Colin Pal ( December 25 , 1923 -- August 30 , 2005 ) was a Hindi film actor , technician , journalist , and publicist for 175 Hindi films .
Ragnar Josephson ( Stockholm 8 March 1891 - Lund 27 March 1966 ) was a Swedish art historian and writer .
Johannes Vastovius ( active in the early 17th century , but his years of birth or death are unknown ) was a Swedish priest and writer in the late reformation period .

Édouard Berth ( 1875 - -1939 ) was a theorist of French syndicalism and disciple of Georges Sorel .
The House of Laments ( Spanish : `` Casa de los lamentos '' ) is a historic place in Guanajuato , Guanajuato , Mexico .
Carl - Henning Pedersen ( 23 September 1913 -- 20 February 2007 ) was a Danish painter and a key member of the COBRA movement .
Count Alexandre de Marenches ( June 7 , 1921 , Paris - June 2 , 1995 ) was a French military officer , former director of the SDECE French external intelligence services ( 6 November 1970 - 12 June 1981 ) , special advisor to U.S. President Ronald Reagan and a member of the Academy of Morocco .
Jean Daujat ( Paris , 27 October 1906 -- 31 May 1998 ) was a French philosopher of neo - Thomism , a disciple of Jacques Maritain , and the founder of the Centre d'études religieuses , the Center for Religious Studies , specializing in teaching Christian doctrine .
Thomas Grimston Estcourt ( 1775 - -1853 ) , of New Park , near Devizes , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Charles Wentworth Dilke ( 1789 - -1864 ) was an English liberal critic and writer on literature .
Abbas Maroufi ( Persian : عباس معروفی‎‎ , born May 17 , 1957 in Tehran ) is an Iranian novelist and journalist .
Samuel Twardowski ( before 1600 -- 1661 ) was a Polish poet , diarist , and essayist who gained popularity in 17th century Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth , called by his contemporaries ' Polish Virgil .
Andrés González de Barcia ( died 1743 ) was a Spanish historian .
Ryoko Sekiguchi ( Japanese ; 関口 涼子 ; Tokyo , December 21 , 1970 ) is a Japanese poet and translator .
Paloma Picasso ( born Anne Paloma Ruiz - Picasso y Gilot in Paris on 19 April 1949 ) , is a French fashion designer and businesswoman , best known for her jewelry designs for Tiffany & Co. and her signature perfumes .
Elías Ahúja y Andría ( January 8 , 1863 -- July 20 , 1951 ) was a Spanish philanthropist , politician , businessman and academic .
George Alfred Spencer ( 1872 -- 21 November 1957 ) was an English miner , trade union leader and Member of Parliament from 1918 to 1929 for Broxtowe .
Gennaro Auletta ( born August 27 , 1957 in Naples ) is an Italian philosopher of science actively involved in scientific research .
Lajos Kossuth de Udvard et Kossuthfalva ( Hungarian : ( ˈlɒjoʃ ˈkoʃut ) , archaically English : Louis Kossuth ; 19 September 1802 -- 20 March 1894 ) was a Hungarian lawyer , journalist , politician and Governor - President of the Kingdom of Hungary during the revolution of 1848 - -49 .
Duilio Cambellotti ( 10 May 1876 -- 31 January 1960 ) was an Italian applied artist , illustrator , painter , sculptor and designer who played a role in the Arts & Crafts and Art Nouveau movements , and whose influence was social and political as well as aesthetic and artistic .

Géza Gárdonyi , born Géza Ziegler ( 3 August 1863 -- 30 October 1922 ) was a Hungarian writer and journalist .

María Cristina Petite ( born 10 May 1972 in Barakaldo ) is a retired Spanish long - distance runner who specialized in the 3000 and 5000 metres .
Pio Colonnello ( Benevento , February 12 , 1951 ) is an Italian philosopher and university professor .
Dr. Béla Király ( 14 April 1912 -- 4 July 2009 ) was a Hungarian army officer before , during , and after World War II . The Stalinists imprisoned him .

Hansraj Gupta ( October 9 , 1902 -- November 23 , 1988 ) was an Indian mathematician specialising in number theory , in particular the study of the partition function .
Adrian Juste ( born 21 April 1947 , Kirby Muxloe , Leicestershire , England ) is an English disc jockey and radio presenter who had a Saturday lunchtime programme on BBC Radio 1 from 1978 to 1994 .
Theo Hiddema ( Medwert - Holwerd , 1 April 1944 ) is a Dutch lawyer and media personality .
Paul - Louis Landsberg ( 3 December 1901 -- 2 April 1944 ) was a twentieth century Existentialist philosopher who is known for his arguments in support of euthanasia as an acceptable method of suicide .
Sarah Y. Mason ( March 31 , 1896 -- November 28 , 1980 ) was an American screenwriter and script supervisor .
Mulraj Rajda ( Hindi : मूलराज रजदा ) was an Indian writer , actor and director .
Dorothy Moore ( born October 13 , 1946 , in Jackson , Mississippi ) is an American pop , R&B , and soul singer best known for her 1976 hit song , `` Misty Blue '' .
Emett Clay Choate ( May 21 , 1891 -- August 14 , 1974 ) was an American lawyer and a United States federal judge .
Kahina Saidi ( Arabic : كهينة سعيدي‎ ; born March 17 , 1984 ) is an Algerian judoka , who played for the half - middleweight category .

Thomas J. Abercrombie ( August 13 , 1930 -- April 3 , 2006 ) was a senior staff writer and photographer for National Geographic , well known for his work on Middle Eastern countries .

Cindy Valentine ( Valentine Cinzia Leone ) is an Italian born composer , producer and performing artist , raised in Toronto , Canada who is now a U.S. citizen , residing primarily in New York , New York .

Carl Finch ( born November 29 , 1951 , in Texarkana , Texas ) is a guitarist , keyboardist , accordionist , vocalist , songwriter , and record producer who co - founded the Grammy - winning polka / dance band Brave Combo in 1979 in Denton , Texas .
Dmytro Kuzmin ( Ukrainian : Дмитро Кузьмін ) is a Paralympic swimmer from Ukraine competing mainly in category SB12 events .

Raymond - Serge Balé is a Congolese diplomat who has been Congo - Brazzaville 's Permanent Representative to the United Nations since 2008 .
Zhang Peijun ( Chinese : 张佩君 ; born April 29 , 1958 ) is a former Chinese handball player .
Ahn Chil - hyun ( born October 10 , 1979 ) , better known by his stage name Kangta , is a South Korean pop singer .
Cătălin Bălescu ( born January 6 , 1962 ) is a Romanian visual artist and a university professor at the Department of Painting of The National University of Arts in Bucharest .
Barbara Bears is an American ballet dancer and a former principal dancer with the Houston Ballet in Houston , Texas .
Suzanne Pharr is an American organizer , political strategist , and author who has worked to build a broad - based social justice movement in the United States .
Johnny Varro ( born 1930 ) is a pianist with roots in the swing style of jazz .
Stuart Gitlow ( born November 29 , 1962 ) is a general , forensic , and addiction psychiatrist , Executive Director of the Annenberg Physician Training Program in Addictive Diseases at the Frank Foundation , and Immediate Past President of the American Society of Addiction Medicine .
Rajkumari Dubey ( 1924 - -2000 ) , better known by her first name , Rajkumari was an Indian playback singer who worked in Hindi cinema of 1930s and 40s .

Clayton Landey is an American actor who has appeared in films and television shows .

Saint John of Gorze ( Jean de Gorze , John of Lorraine ) ( ca . 900 - -March 7 , 974 ) was a Lorraine - born monk , diplomat , administrator , and monastic reformer .

Benjamin Pawling ( circa 1749 -- buried December 16 , 1816 ) was a soldier , judge , political figure and publisher in Upper Canada .
Sameera Moussa ( Arabic : سميرة موسى‎ ) ( March 3 , 1917 - August 5 , 1952 ) was an Egyptian nuclear physicist who held a doctorate in atomic radiation and worked to make the medical use of nuclear technology affordable to all .
Scott Hoffman ( born October 10 , 1961 in Fort Myers , Florida ) is an American rock drummer .
Kim McLane Wardlaw ( born July 2 , 1954 ) is a federal judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit , with chambers in Pasadena , California .

Parker Marie Molloy ( born April 24 , 1986 in Chicago , Illinois ) is an American writer , blogger , and transgender rights activist .

Sobekneferu ( sometimes written `` Neferusobek '' ) was an Egyptian woman reigning as pharaoh after the death of her brother Amenemhat IV . She was the last ruler of the 12th Dynasty and governed Egypt for almost 4 years from 1806 to 1802 BC . Her name means `` the beauty of Sobek . ''

Christopher Greenup ( c. 1750 -- April 27 , 1818 ) was an American politician who served as a U.S. Representative and the third Governor of Kentucky .

Sewadjare Mentuhotep ( also known as Mentuhotep V or Mentuhotep VI depending on the scholar ) is a poorly attested Egyptian pharaoh of the late 13th dynasty who reigned for a short time c. 1655 BC during the Second Intermediate Period .

The Helan Shan pika or silver pika ( Ochotona argentata ) is a species of mammal in the pika family , Ochotonidae .
Helicarion australis , common name the `` Australian native snail '' is a species of air - breathing land snail or semi - slug , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Helicarionidae .
The single species it comprises , Pistia stratiotes , is often called water cabbage , water lettuce , Nile cabbage , or shellflower .
Methona themisto , common name Themisto Amberwing , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
The Mithrodiidae is a family of starfish in the order Valvatida .
Buddleja jamesonii is a species endemic to southern Ecuador , where it grows in moist , protected ravines and borders of tussocks at elevations of 3,000 -- 4,000 m. The species , first named and described by Bentham in 1846 , is now threatened by habitat loss .
Ericameria zionis , the Subalpine goldenbush or cedar breaks goldenbush , is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Trichagnia fuscomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichagnia .
Ditropichthys storeri is a species of flabby whalefish found in the deep oceans at depths of from 650 to 3,400 metres ( 2,130 to 11,150 ft ) .
Platypezidae is a family of true flies of the superfamily Platypezoidea .
Leucorhynchia gorii is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Lethocerus insulanus is a species of giant water bug of the family Belostomatidae .
Acastoides is an extinct genus of trilobite that lived during the Silurian and Devonian .
