Xerophyllum asphodeloides is a North American species of flowering plants in the Melanthiaceae known by the common names turkey beard , eastern turkeybeard , beartongue , grass - leaved helonias , and mountain asphodel .
The Badidae ( the chameleonfishes ) are a small family ( about 23 species ) of perciform fishes .
Trematolobelia singularis , the lavaslope false lobelia , is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family .
The genus consists of only one species , Epatolmis caesarea , which is found in Europe , Asia Minor , Southern Siberia , Amur , Mongolia , Northern China up to Korea and Japan .
Pleuromenus baccifer is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pleuromenus .
Microsorum pustulatum ( kangaroo fern or hound 's tongue , in Māori : kōwaowao , pāraharaha ) is a species of fern within the Polypodiaceae family .
Carabus albrechti echigo is a subspecies of ground beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to Japan .
Poikilospermum is a tropical genus of shrubs or tall woody climbers , consisting of at least four accepted species and another 23 species with unresolved taxonomic status .
Gossia is a genus of rainforest trees in the myrtle family first described as a genus in 2003 .
Rodents ( from Latin rodere , `` to gnaw '' ) are mammals of the order Rodentia , which are characterized by a single pair of unremittingly growing incisors in each of the upper and lower jaws .
Pyura herdmani , one of two southern African species of `` red bait '' ( or `` rooiaas '' in Afrikaans ) , is a sessile ascidian , or sea squirt , that lives in coastal waters attached to rocks or artificial structures .
Allium narcissiflorum is a European species of wild onion native to northwestern Italy ( Piemonte and Liguria ) , southwest France ( Provence and Dauphiné ) and northern Portugal .
Rhynchosporium is a genus of fungi that causes leaf scald disease on several graminaceous hosts .
Pheidole megatron ( named after Megatron from the toy line Transformers ) is a species of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Acropora cytherea is a colonial species of coral that grows in large horizontal plates .
Plasmodium ovale is a species of parasitic protozoa that causes tertian malaria in humans .
Adelpha plesaure , common name Pleasure Sister , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Tegula excavata , common name the green - based tegula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Erigeron maniopotamicus is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Mad River fleabane .
Senecio cedrorum is a shrub species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae and endemic to Madagascar .
Alaena bjornstadi is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Myoxanthus exasperatus is a species of orchid native to Central America and tropical South America .
Kalophrynus is a genus of microhylid frogs .
Anabarilius qiluensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Anabarilius .
Symphysops is a genus of trilobite of average size , belonging to the Cyclopygidae family .
Hyperolius sankuruensis , the Omaniundu reed frog , is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Atherinosoma microstoma , commonly known as the small mouth hardyhead , is a species of silverside native to southeastern Australia .
Phoronids ( scientific name Phoronida , sometimes called horseshoe worms ) are a phylum of marine animals that filter - feed with a lophophore ( a `` crown '' of tentacles ) , and build upright tubes of chitin to support and protect their soft bodies .
Eustomias jimcraddocki is a species of abyssal barbeled dragonfish of the family Stomiidae , found in the western North Atlantic .
Drakaea confluens , commonly known as late hammer orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Gastrotheca lateonota ( common name : El Tambo marsupial frog ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Enneabatrachus hechti is an extinct species of an extinct genus of prehistoric frog known from the late Jurassic Morrison Formation .
Octodontidae is a family of rodents , restricted to southwestern South America .
Awaouichthys menoni is a species of goby native to the Sunderbans of India .
Petrobius maritimus , the shore bristletail or sea bristletail , is a species of Archaeognatha found on rocky shores from the Mediterranean Sea to the North Sea .
Vicia hassei is a species of vetch known by the common names Hasse 's vetch and slender vetch .
Epischura lacustris is a species of copepod in the family Temoridae .
Tectella patellaris , commonly known as the Veiled Panus , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
The Colosteidae are a family of labyrinthodont amphibians that lived in the Carboniferous period .
Aphos porosus , the banded toadfish , is a species of toadfish found along the Pacific coast of South America where it is found in Chile , Ecuador and Peru .
Coprinellus xanthothrix is a species of fungus in the Psathyrellaceae family .
Unquatornoceras is an extinct cephalopod genus from the Late Devonian belonging to the ammonoid order Goniatitida .
Venjukovia is an extinct genus of non - mammalian synapsid from the Middle Permian of Russia .
Chaetophora elegans is the type species in the algae genus Chaetophora .
Eulobus californicus , is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name California suncup .
Acalolepta sumatrana is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Asia in countries such as the Sumatra and Malaysia .
Microtropis rigida is a species of plant in the family Celastraceae .
Pilobolus is a genus of fungi that commonly grows on herbivore dung .
Delias ottonia is a species of pierine butterfly endemic to Mindanao in the Philippines .
Philibertia is a genus of flowering plants in the Apocynaceae family , first described as a genus in 1819 .
Epilobium howellii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names Yuba Pass Willowherb and Subalpine Fireweed ( though it is not a true fireweed ) .
Margarites smithi , common name the Smith margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Ptorthocera calva is a genus of beetles in the family Callirhipidae , and the only species in the genus Ptorthocera .
Pelmatellus caerulescens is a species of ground beetle in the genus Pelmatellus .
Itea ilicifolia ( holly - leaved sweet spire ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Iteaceae , native to western China .
The Mediterranean pine vole ( Microtus duodecimcostatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Apolemichthys xanthurus , the Indian yellowtail angelfish , is a species of marine angelfish of the family Pomacanthidae .
Ardisia crenata is a species of flowering plant in the primrose family , Primulaceae , that is native to East Asia .
Indascia is a genus of hoverflies native to India and Sri Lanka .
Asplenium listeri , commonly known as the Christmas Island Spleenwort , is a species of fern in the Aspleniaceae family .
Tropheops gracilior is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it lives in caves .
Solanum marginatum is a species of nightshade known by the common names purple African nightshade and white - margined nightshade .
The Santalales are an order of flowering plants with a cosmopolitan distribution , but heavily concentrated in tropical and subtropical regions .
Gomphidius roseus was initially described by Swedish mycologist Elias Magnus Fries as Agaricus glutinosus β roseus in 1821 , before he elevated it to species status and gave its current genus and binomial name in 1838 .
Ulex ( gorse , furze or whin ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae .
Parhippolyte sterreri is a species of marine decapod crustacean in the family Barbouriidae , formerly placed in the genus Somersiella .
Tilia heterophylla , the white basswood , is a species of Tilia native to mesic forests in eastern North America from central New York south to northernmost Florida and west to Missouri ; it is most common in the Appalachian Mountains .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Pseudotyphula ochracea , found in North America .
Piveteausaurus ( meaning `` Jean Piveteau 's lizard '' ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur known from a partial skull discovered in the Middle Jurassic Marnes de Dives formation of Calvados , in northern France .
The Ecuadorian hillstar ( Oreotrochilus chimborazo ) is a species of hummingbird .
Alaginella is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Marginellidae .
The genus contains a single described species Haidoterminus cippus and is known from one Late Cretaceous fossil which has been found in North America .
Parcoblatta caudelli , Caudell 's wood cockroach or Caudell 's wood roach , is a species of cockroach native to the United States .
The Tarsophlebiidae is an extinct family of medium - sized fossil odonates from the Upper Jurassic and Lower Cretaceous period of Eurasia .
The discovery of Thermococcus celer played an important role in re - rooting the tree of life when it was discovered that T. celer was more closely related to methanogenic Archaea than to other phenotypically similar thermophilic species T. celer was the first archaeon discovered to house a circularized genome .
Emblemaria is a genus of chaenopsid blennies found throughout the Pacific and Atlantic oceans .
Dardanus calidus is a species of hermit crab from the East Atlantic ( Portugal to Senegal ) and Mediterranean Sea .
The Cuban yellow bat ( Lasiurus insularis ) is a species of bat from the family Vespertilioninae .
Penicillium salamii is a species of the genus of Penicillium which occurs on dry - cured meat products .
Cirsium arvense is a species of Cirsium , native throughout Europe and northern Asia , and widely introduced elsewhere .
Diospyros quaesita or calamander is a species of tree endemic to Sri Lanka .
Inca clathrata is a species of flower chafer in the family Scarabaeidae , indigenous to Central and South America .
Maxillaria palmifolia is a species of orchid that ranges from the Caribbean to Guyana .
Nebria araschinica is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Armenia and Turkey .
Kalmiopsis fragrans is a rare species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common name North Umpqua kalmiopsis .
Agyneta ressli is a species of sheet weaver found in Austria , Germany , Greece and Switzerland .
Erigeron strigosus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Common eastern fleabane .
Odontoglossum lindleyanum , the Lindley 's Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid found from northwestern Venezuela to Ecuador .
Oligobrycon microstomus is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the upper middle Paraíba do Sul River basin .
Spaniblennius is a genus of combtooth blennies native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Taraxacum californicum , also known as the California dandelion , is an endangered species of dandelion endemic to the San Bernardino Mountains of California .
Hodgkinsonia frutescens , commonly known as Atherton turkey bush , is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family native to north Queensland in Australia .
Agave striata is a plant species native to Northeastern Mexico .
Gorgodera amplicava is a species of digenetic trematode whose definitive hosts include amphibians .
Acanthocharax microlepis is a species of characin endemic to Guyana , where it is found in the Essequibo River basin .
Tropidema chrysocephala is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tropidema .
Melongena pirum is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Melongenidae , the crown conches and their allies .
Microzancla ignitalis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Microzancla .
Sematuridae is a family of moths in the lepidopteran order that contains two subfamilies ( Minet and Scoble , 1999 ) .
Oncidium leucochilum is a species of orchid occurring from southeastern Mexico to Honduras .
Coreius is a genus of cyprinid fish belonging to the subfamily Gobioninae .
Gymnoschoenus sphaerocephalus , commonly known as button grass , is a species of tussock - forming sedge from southeastern Australia .
Phaeomoniella chlamydospora is a fungus species of mitosporic ascomycota in the genus Phaeomoniella .
Brickellia macromera is a rare Mexican species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Bothriembryon is a genus of tropical air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Bothriembryontidae .
Haemosporidiasina ( Haemosporidia ) is a subclass of apicomplexans described by Jacques Euzéby in 1988 that is not widely used by biologists .
Cerceris fumipennis , the only species of buprestid - hunting Crabronidae occurring in eastern North America , is found throughout the continental United States east of the Rockies : from Texas and Florida , north to Maine and Wyoming and is now known from more than twenty colonies of varying size in Canada .
Chryseobacterium greenlandensis is an ultramicrobacteria species of bacteria that is able to live for long periods of time in habitats low - temperature , high - pressure , reduced - oxygen and nutrient - poor habitats .
Mycena rosea , commonly known as the rosy bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Zostera is a small genus of widely distributed seagrasses , commonly called marine eelgrass or ( outside North America ) simply eelgrass .
Restio is the name of a group of plants within the Restionaceae described as a genus in 1772 .
Puntioplites is a genus of cyprinid fish that occurs in Southeast Asia .
Monocentris is a genus of pinecone fishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
The Chocó screech owl ( Megascops centralis ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Crataegus × macrocarpa , is a hybrid between two species of hawthorn ( Hawthorn ) , C. laevigata and C. rhipidophylla , both in series Crataegus .
Pterocarya rhoifolia is a species of tree in the Juglandaceae family that grows in moist areas along riverbanks and mountain streams in Laoshan District , China .
Polyrhaphis spinosa is a species of longhorn beetles of the Lamiinae subfamily .
Goldman 's jaguar was proposed as a subspecies of jaguar , with the taxonomic name `` Panthera onca goldmani '' ( Mearns , 1901 ) , which ranged from the Yucatán Peninsula in Mexico , in the north , to Belize and Honduras in the south , before 1939 .
Nematus ribesii is a species of sawfly in the family Tenthredinidae .
Myriocarpa is a genus woody plant which ranges in size from shrubs to small trees and is endemic to Central and South America .
Uropeltis smithi , commonly known as Smith 's earth snake or the violet shieldtail , is a species of nonvenomous shieldtail snake .
Camellia sinensis is a species of evergreen shrub or small tree whose leaves and leaf buds are used to produce tea .
Brachytarsophrys intermedia ( common name : Annam spadefoot toad ) is a species of frog in the Megophryidae family .
Mycobacterium brumae is a rapidly growing environmental mycobacterial species identified in 1993 .
Phacelia viscida is a species of phacelia known by the common names sticky phacelia and tacky phacelia .
The Syngamidae are a family of nematodes which commonly parasitize mammals , birds , and rarely humans .
Scopulini is a tribe of the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) , with about 900 species in seven genera .
Maricopodynerus is a Nearctic genus of potter wasps distributed west of the 100 ° western meridian in the United States and Mexico .
Cyathocalyx is a small genus with about 22 species distributed from southern India , Sri Lanka , through Malaysia , Indomalayan islands and reaches as far as Fiji in the South Pacific .
Apis mellifera adami ( often misspelled `` adamii '' ) is a honey bee subspecies from the Mediterranean area , endemic to Crete .
Oncidium cheirophorum is a species of orchid found from Mexico ( Chiapas ) to Colombia .
Pethia nankyweensis is a species of cyprinid fish found in Myanmar where it is known from smaller streams in the area of Myitkyina .
Rhacophorus annamensis ( Annam flying frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in the Annamite Mountains in Cambodia and Vietnam .
Leptospermum polygalifolium , commonly known as tantoon , is a species of shrub of the family Myrtaceae native to eastern Australia and Lord Howe Island .
Emblemaria hypacanthus , the Gulf signal blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from the Gulf of California , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Imagocnus is an extinct genus of ground sloth from the early Miocene of Cuba .
Glottiphyllum longum is a species of succulent plant in the Aizoaceae family , native to South Africa .
Buddleja colvilei is endemic to the eastern Himalaya ; discovered by Hooker in 1849 , he declared it ' the handsomest of all Himalayan shrubs ' The species was awarded the RHS First Class Certificate ( FCC ) in 1896 .
Xenoceratops is a genus of centrosaurine ceratopsid dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous ( middle Campanian stage ) of Alberta , Canada .
The Cretan wildcat ( Felis silvestris cretensis ; Greek : φουρόγατος , fourógatos ) is a European wildcat subspecies that inhabits the Greek island of Crete and was first described in 1953 .
Ochlodes venatus is a skipper butterfly species in the family Hesperiidae .
Grammomys brevirostris is a species of rodent endemic to Kenya .
Scorpaena is a widespread genus of scorpionfishes
Calymene blumenbachii , sometimes spelled - erroneously - blumenbachi , is a species of trilobite discovered in the limestone quarries of Wren 's Nest Hill in Dudley , England .
Dioryctria albovittella , the pinyon tip moth , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
Loxommatinae is an extinct subfamily of baphetids , a group of early tetrapods from the Late Carboniferous .
Planctomycetes are a phylum of aquatic bacteria and are found in samples of brackish , and marine and fresh water .
Pleurotus dryinus is a species of fungus in the family Pleurotaceae .
Cakile edentula ( American searocket ) is a species of the flowering Cakile plant .
Crataegus triflora is an uncommon hawthorn species of the south - eastern U.S. , of known by the common name three - flowered hawthorn .
Schistometopum thomense is a species of amphibian in the family Dermophiidae , endemic to São Tomé and Ilhéu das Rolas .
Heppsora is a genus of lichenized fungi in the family Ramalinaceae .
Acorus is a genus of monocot flowering plants .
Dyoplosaurus ( meaning `` double - armored lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of ankylosaurid dinosaurs within the subfamily Ankylosaurinae .
The Turkana Haplochromis ( Haplochromis turkanae ) , also known in brief as Turkana Haplo , is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Turkana .

Dalea candida is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name white prairie clover .
Acremonium strictum is an environmentally widespread saprotroph species found in soil , plant debris , and rotting mushrooms .
Astragalus loanus is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Glenwood milkvetch .

Thoburnia is a genus of suckers found in the eastern United States .
The Malayan weasel ( Mustela nudipes ) is a species of weasel .
Batrachocephalus mino , the Beardless sea catfish , is the only species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Batrachocephalus of the family Ariidae .

Chrysothamnus humilis called Truckee rabbitbrush , is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Anisopodus affinis is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae that was described by Martins in 1974 It is known from Costa Rica , Panama , eastern Ecuador , and Bolivia .

Blechnum rimbachii is a species of fern in the Blechnaceae family .

Deltadromeus ( meaning `` delta runner '' ) is a genus of large basal ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur from Northern Africa .

Phaius philippinensis is a species of orchid in the genus Phaius that was described by N. E. Brown in 1889 .
Sepiella ocellata is a species of cuttlefish known only from the type locality off Java .
Kaiparathina vaubani is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae .
Dracaena fragrans ( cornstalk dracaena ) is a flowering plant species that is native throughout tropical Africa , from Sudan south to Mozambique , west to Côte d'Ivoire and southwest to Angola , growing in upland regions at 600 - -2,250 m ( 1,970 - -7,380 ft ) altitude .
Hoya carnosa , the porcelainflower or wax plant , is an Asclepiad species in the dogbane family ( Apocynaceae ) .
Recilia dex is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that is endemic to Liberia .
Granata imbricata , common names the imbricate margarite , tiled false ear shell , true wide - mouthed shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae .
The Lesser Antillean tanager ( Tangara cucullata ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
Euryzygomatomys is a South American rodent genus in the family Echimyidae .
Brachycephalus auroguttatus is a species of frog in the Brachycephalidae family .
Sclerocactus papyracanthus is a species of cactus known by the common names paperspine fishhook cactus , grama grass cactus , paper - spined cactus , and toumeya .
Calosoma abbreviatum , Short Caterpiller Hunter , is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae .
F.White - most of species range Euclea racemosa subsp .
Bema ydda is a species of snout moth in the genus Bema .
Acanthamoeba is a genus of amoebae , one of the most common protozoa in soil , and frequently found in fresh water and other habitats .
Limonium narbonense is a species of sea lavender belonging to the family Plumbaginaceae .
The superfamily Membracoidea includes two of the largest families among what used to be the `` Homoptera '' ; the leafhoppers ( Cicadellidae ) and the treehoppers ( Membracidae ) .
Amolops chunganensis ( common names : Chungan sucker frog , Chungan torrent frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
The Terebridae , commonly referred to as auger shells or auger snails , is a group or family of small to large predatory marine gastropods .
Ptychochromis grandidieri is a species of fish in the Cichlidae family endemic to river basins along a large part of the eastern coast of Madagascar , although it has been recorded as far as 100 km ( 62 mi ) inland .
Jerdon 's sea snake ( Kerilia jerdonii ) is a species of venomous sea snake .
The subfamily Tylomyinae consists of several species of New World rats and mice including the vesper and climbing rats .
Pseudoperipatus is a monospecific genus of annulated ecdysozoan worm known only from its posterior portion , from a single Burgess Shale specimen .
Abra alba or the white furrow shell is a species of bivalve mollusc in the Semelidae family .
Pireneitega is a genus of araneomorph spiders in the family Agelenidae .
Polygala cruciata , commonly called drumheads milkwort , is a species of flowering plant in the milkwort family .
Neillia is a genus of the botanical family Rosaceae .
Layia heterotricha is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name pale yellow tidytips , or pale yellow layia .
Pterallastes is a genus of bee - mimicking hoverflies .
Symphoromyia ( meaning bane / blight fly in Greek ) is a genus of predatory snipe flies .
Murex occa , also known as the Harrowed murex , is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Carabus clathratus is a species of beetle widespread in the Palearctic .
Geissois imthurnii is a species of forest tree belonging to the plant family Cunoniaceae .
Pseudanos trimaculatus , the Threespot headstander , is a species of headstander found in Argentina , Brazil , Guyana and Peru .
The Carlemanniaceae are a tropical East Asian and Southeast Asian family of subshrub to herbaceous perennial flowering plants with 2 genera .
Acalypha integrifolia is a species in the botanical family Euphorbiaceae .
Neopsittacus is a genus of parrot in the family Psittaculidae .
Ozyptila is a genus of rather small crab spiders .
Diagramma is a genus of grunts native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Choristoneura freemani , the western spruce budworm , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Deinopis subrufa ( also called Rufous Net - casting Spider ) is a species of net - casting spiders .
Costoanachis avara , common name the greedy dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Allium aeginiense is a plant species endemic to Greece .
Opistophthalmus is a genus of scorpions known commonly as burrowing scorpions , tri - colored scorpions , serkets , or hissing scorpions .
Centaurium davyi is a species of flowering plant in the gentian family known by the common name Davy 's centaury .
Aromobates meridensis ( common name : Merida rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Celypha rivulana is a small moth species of the family Tortricidae .
Navarretia prostrata is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names prostrate pincushionplant and prostrate vernal pool navarretia .
Navarretia rosulata is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names Marin County navarretia , Marin County pincushionplant and San Anselmo navarretia .
Tectivirus is a genus of viruses , and is currently the only genus in the family Tectiviridae .
Blenniella paula , the Blue - dashed rockskipper , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Jilinicaris is an extinct genus of crustacean in the order Decapoda , and is the earliest fossil assigned to the Stenopodidea , having been found in rocks of Late Cretaceous age .
Ctenosaura flavidorsalis , commonly known as the yellowback spiny - tailed iguana , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
The family Cephalotaxaceae is a small grouping of conifers , with three genera and about 20 species , closely allied to the Taxaceae , and included in that family by some botanists .
Pseudopaludicola pusilla ( Spanish : Ranita Enana ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Mesoptila compsodes is the type species of the Mesoptila Genus .
Schayera baiulus is a species of grasshopper in the family Acrididae , endemic to Australia .
Grandisonia alternans is a species of caecilian in the family Indotyphlidae , endemic to the Seychelles islands of Mahé , Praslin , Frégate , and La Digue .
Pseudodiachipteryx expansipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pseudodiachipteryx .
Coccinella leonina , common name orange - spotted ladybird , is a species of ladybird native to New Zealand .
Nephtheis fascicularis , commonly called the lollipop tunicate , lollipop coral , or blue palm coral , is a species of tunicate that is native to the shallow reefs of Indonesia .
Smilax jamesii is a species of flowering plant in the greenbriar family known by the common name English Peak greenbriar .
Mystiornis is an extinct genus of bird which existed in what is now western Siberia , Russia during the early Cretaceous period ( Barremian / Aptian age ) .
Anoteropsis aerescens is a species of wolf spiders , that is distinguished from all other Anoteropsis species by the shape of the median apophysis of the male bulb and the external sclerites of the female epigyne , especially the wide median septum .
Conus marmoreus , common name the `` marbled cone '' , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Echinocactus is a genus of cacti in the subfamily Cactoideae .
Trifolium longipes is a species of clover known by the common name longstalk clover .
Omochroa is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae with one species :
Gerres is a genus of mojarras found mostly in marine waters from the eastern Atlantic Ocean through the Indian Ocean to the western Pacific .
Austrochthonius insularis is a species of pseudoscorpion in the family Chthoniidae .
Trichocirca is a genus of moths in the Choreutidae family , containing only one species , Trichocirca tyrota , which is known from Kenya .
Nigma puella is a species of spider belonging to the family Dictynidae .
The Oreasteridae are a family of sea stars in the class Asteroidea .
It contains the single species Faguetia falcata , which is endemic to eastern Madagascar .
Megalytoceratinae is a subfamily of lytoceratids ammonites consisting of planulate forms , i.e. those with moderately evolute compressed shells with bluntly rounded venters , in which the outer whorls become smooth and sutures tend to resemble those of the Perisphinctidae .
Conus vicweei , common name the Vic Wee 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Xanthonicias prostrata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Xanthonicias .
Guardiola diehlii is a very rare ( quite possibly extinct ) North American species of plants in the sunflower family , found only in the State of New Mexico in the southwestern United States .
Granulorsidis flavidosignatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Granulorsidis .
Choleoeimeria is a genus of protozoan parasites that infect the biliary tracts of reptiles .
Quintalia flosculus is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail or semislug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicarionidae .
Astacus astacus , the European crayfish , noble crayfish or broad - fingered crayfish , is the most common species of crayfish in Europe , and a traditional food source .
Petalifera is a genus of sea slugs or sea hares , marine gastropod mollusks belonging to the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Ornithostoma ( meaning `` bird mouth '' ) is a genus of pterodactyloid pterosaurs .
Euchilichthys guentheri is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Congo Basin of the Democratic Republic of the Congo , the Republic of the Congo and Zambia .
Clostridium septicum can cause gas gangrene , but unlike other Clostridium species like Clostridium perfringens , no trauma is necessary at the site of the infection .
Hippodamia tredecimpunctata , commonly known as the thirteen - spot ladybeetle , is a species of lady beetle .
Strobilops labyrinthicus , common name the maze pinecone , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Strobilopsidae .
Leptecodon ( meaning `` small tooth '' ) is a genus of prehistoric mackerel - like fish which was described by Williston in 1899 and was possibly preyed on by other sea creatures .
Hoploranomimus harmandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hoploranomimus .
Prosotas is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Australasian ecozone ( New Guinea ) and the Indomalaya ecozone .
Allium umbilicatum is an Asian species of wild onion native to Pakistan , Afghanistan , Turkmenistan , Uzbekistan , Iran , and Tajikistan .
Phyllospadix serrulatus , the toothed surfgrass , is a plant species found along the shorelines of British Columbia and southern Alaska .
Pseudopsocus rostocki is a species of Psocoptera from Trichopsocidae family that can be found in England and Ireland .
Maylandia or Metriaclima is a genus of haplochromine cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
Clausena excavata is a species of evergreen shrub 1 - -2 m tall , in the family Rutaceae , native to Bangladesh , Bhutan , Burma , Cambodia , China , India , Indonesia , Laos , Malaysia , Nepal , Philippines , Thailand , and Vietnam .
Leiostyla concinna is a species of land snail in the family Lauriidae .
Lepeta caeca , common name the northern blind limpet , is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lepetidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Culter flavipinnis is a species of Cyprinid fish that is endemic to Vietnam .
Andamia amphibius is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific Ocean .
Neocrepidodera simplicipes is a species of flea beetle in the leaf beetle family that is endemic to Austria .
Agra liv ( Erwin , 2002 ) is a species of carabid beetle named after the `` first name of the actress Liv Tyler , starlet of the movie , Armageddon ... because the ' ' existence of this species of elegant beetle is dependent upon the rainforest not undergoing an armageddon .
Caecilia crassisquama is a species of caecilian in the Caeciliidae family .
Micromelerpetontidae is an extinct family of dissorophoid temnospondyl amphibians that lived from the Late Carboniferous to the Early Permian in what is now Europe .
Brefeldia maxima is a species of non - parasitic plasmodial slime mold , and a member of the Myxomycetes class .
Scyliorhinotheca is an extinct genus of cartilaginous fish first described in 2012 from the state of Washington .
The Echinosteliales are an order of Amoebozoa in the class Myxomycetes .
Elachistocleis bicolor ( common name : two - colored oval frog , Spanish : rana pinguino or sapito panza amarilla ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Atolla wyvillei , also known as Atolla jellyfish or Coronate medusa , is a species of deep - sea crown jellyfish ( Scyphozoa : Coronatae ) .
Parodia leninghausii is a species of South American cactus commonly found as a houseplant .
Acrolophitus is a genus of grasshoppers in thefamily Acrididae .
Harpalinae is a huge subfamily of ground beetles that contains 20,000 species .
Typhlocypris is a genus of ostracods , which are a class of small , bivalved crustaceans .
Tachina vulgata is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to South America .
Siphonaria compressa is a species of small , air - breathing sea snail .
It contains only one species , Prohepialus incertus , which was described from a Thanetian crater lake diatomite ( Paleocene ) in Menat ( Puy - de - Dôme ) , France .
Podocoma is a genus of South American plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Hypsugo anthonyi , also known as Anthony 's pipistrelle , is a species of vesper bat .
Trifolium oliganthum is a species of clover known by the common name fewflower clover .
Rhacophorus duboisi is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family found in China and Vietnam .
Eleutherodactylus melacara is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Sierra Maestra , Cuba .
Mongolicosa mongolensis is a species of wolf spider only known from Gurvanbulag district , Bayankhongor Province , Mongolia .
Anomalopus mackayi , commonly known as the five - clawed worm skink , long - legged worm skink , and MacKay 's burrowing skink , is a species of smooth - scaled burrowing skink endemic to eastern Australia .
Pelagocephalus marki , the Rippled blaasop , is a species of pufferfish known from the coasts of South Africa and New Zealand .
Metallanchista perlaeta is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that can be found in such Asian countries as Malaysia and Indonesian islands such as Java and Sumatra .
Peperomia obtusifolia ( baby rubberplant or pepper face ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Piperaceae , native to Florida , Mexico and the Caribbean .
Stylocline masonii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Mason 's neststraw .
Pristimantis mutabilis , also known as mutable rainfrog , is a species of frog found in the Ecuadoran Andes in the Pichincha and Imbabura Provinces .
Trochosa hungarica is a wolf spider species in the genus Trochosa found in Hungary .
Clubiona nigromaculosa is a sac spider species found in the Seychelles and Réunion .
Nipponocypris is a genus of cyprinid fish containing two species , one endemic to Japan , the other to South Korea .
Novacaesareala is a genus of prehistoric bird .
Sappinia diploidea is a free - living amoeba species .
Chrysotus pallidipalpus is a fly species in the genus of Chrysotus found in Hawaii .
Sparbambus gombakensis is a species of jumping spider that has to date only been found in Malaysia .
Pseudoceroprepes piratis is a species of snout moth
It contains the single species Laelapia notata , which is found in Madagascar .
The Eucnemidae , false click beetles , are a family of polyphagan beetles including about 1700 species distributed worldwide .
Also known as skin - toe forest gecko , Cyrtodactylus interdigitalis is a species of gecko found in Phetchaburi , Phetchabun and Loei provinces of Thailand as well in Laos .
Neoischnolea papuana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neoischnolea .
Savalia savaglia , the gold coral , is a species of colonial false black coral in the family Parazoanthidae .
Trachelipus palustris is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus that can be found on islands like Crete and Cyclades , and also in mainland Greece .
Apterameles rammei is a species of praying mantis found in the Republic of Macedonia .
Uberabasuchus is an extinct genus of crocodylomorph from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Acer palaeorufinerve is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from series of isolated fossil samaras and leaves .
Nassarius lima , common name the clathrate nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
The perennial vine Lonicera hispidula is a species of honeysuckle known as pink honeysuckle and , less often , California honeysuckle .
Hygrophorus eburneus , commonly known as the ivory waxy cap or the cowboy 's handkerchief , is a species of edible mushroom in the waxgill family of fungi .
Tachina vallata is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Europe .
Neodrillia cydia , common name the Cydia drillia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Drilliidae .
Mangifera decandra is a species of mango trees in the Mangifera subgenus Limus ( family Anacardiaceae ) .
Papilio karna is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Java , Sumatra , Borneo and the Philippines .
Bruckenthalia is a genus of plants consisting of only one species , Bruckenthalia spiculifolia ( spike heath ) an evergreen shrub native to southeastern Europe and Asia Minor .
Hemiodus is a genus of halftooths from South America with the greatest species richness in the Amazon Basin , but also found in the Orinoco , Essequibo , Paraná--
Osmidus guttatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Osmidus .
Trombicula alfreddugesi , also called Eutrombicula alfreddugè , is a species in the genus Trombicula .
Viola cheiranthifolia is a species of the genus Viola .
It was described by Ruzicka in 1931 , and the type species is Eulomina mitratum , which the author originally described under the genus Euloma in 1926 .
Sphaeriodesmus filamentosus is a species of millipede in the family Sphaeriodesmidae that is endemic to San Vito , Costa Rica .
It contains only ones species , Banghaasia ildefonsella , which is found in Spain .
Bayerotrochus midas , common name King Midas 's slit shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
The Cuban giant owl or giant cursorial owl ( Ornimegalonyx ) is an extinct genus of giant owl that measured 1.1 metres ( 3 ft 7 in ) in height .
Stellaria solaris , common name the sun carrier shell , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Xenophoridae , the carrier shells .
Eriogonum prociduum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name prostrate buckwheat .
The Moroccan jird ( Meriones grandis ) is a species of rodent from the family Muridae .
It contains only one species , Congoprinsia juratae , which is found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Amorphoscelis griffini is a species of praying mantis found in Côte d'Ivoire and Cameroon .
The Dixidae ( meniscus midges ) are a family of aquatic nematoceran flies ( Diptera ) .
Ampharete is a genus of polychaete annelid worm with a single , chevron - shaped row of teeth .
Pouteria eerwah is a rare species of Australian rainforest tree in the Sapotaceae family .
Haptoclinus apectolophus , the Uncombed blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny known only from Arrowsmith Bank off of the Yucatan Peninsula .
Schiedea membranacea is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name valley schiedea .
The Mollicutes are a class of bacteria distinguished by the absence of a cell wall .
Cyathea hancockii is a species of tree fern endemic to Kinabalu National Park in Borneo , where it grows in ridge forest at an altitude of 2400 - 3000 m. It is a rather small species , having an erect trunk about 50 cm tall or more .
Ericameria bloomeri is a species of flowering shrubs in the daisy family known by the common names Bloomer 's rabbitbush and Bloomer 's goldenbush .
Carex diandra is a species of sedge known by the common names lesser tussock - sedge and lesser panicled sedge .
Glaphurochiton is a genus of fossil chiton known from the Mazon Creek biota .
Calliostoma bonita , common name the kelp top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Allium hemisphaericum is a species of onion endemic to the Island of Sicily in the Mediterranean .
Pseudocrenilabrus is a small genus of haplochromine cichlids that are endemic to rivers and lakes in Central and Eastern Africa .
Phiditia is a genus of moths of the Phiditiidae family .
Cayratia japonica ( common names Bushkiller , Yabu Garashi and Japanese Cayratia Herb ) is a species of herbaceous plant native to Australia and Asia .
Nebulasaurus is an extinct genus of basal eusauropod dinosaur known from the early Middle Jurassic Zhanghe Formation ( Aalenian or Bajocian stage ) of Yunnan Province , China .
Illex illecebrosus , commonly known as the northern shortfin squid or Boston squid , is a species of neritic squids in the family Ommastrephidae .
Potamogeton trichoides is a species of aquatic plant known by the common name hairlike pondweed , native to Europe and western Asia where it grows in calcareous , usually nutrient - rich standing or slow - flowing water .
Carabus faustus is a species of ground beetle from Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to the Canary Islands .
Adiantum reniforme ( Lotus - leaved Maidenhair Fern ) is a species of fern in the genus Adiantum ( maidenhairs ) .
Coelioxys nitidoscutellaris is a species of leaf - cutting bee in the genus Coelioxys , of the family Megachilidae .
Rickettsia akari is a species of Rickettsia which causes rickettsialpox .
Ramonda nathaliae , also known as Natalie 's Ramonda , is a species of flower in the genus Ramonda that grows in Serbia and Macedonia , mostly in the east of both countries .
Lasius speculiventris is a species of ant that is commonly found in the northern United States and lives in forests , woodlands , and meadows .
Heliothis is a genus of moths , whose larvae are agricultural pests on crop species such as tobacco , cotton , soybean and pigeon pea .
Corylus yunnanensis is a species of hazelnut found in western China .
Anteosaurus ( meaning `` Antaeus reptile '' ) is an extinct genus of large carnivorous synapsid .
Trillium ludovicianum , the Louisiana wakerobin or Louisiana trillium , is a plant species found only in the south - central United States ( Louisiana , Mississippi , and eastern Texas ) .
Meconopsis aculeata is a blue - flowered thorny species of the genus Meconopsis with a small geographical distribution restricted to specific areas of Pakistan and India , in the west Himalayas .
Octodon is a genus of octodontid rodents native to South America .
Primula cusickiana is a species of flowering plant in the primrose family known by the common name Cusick 's primrose .
Myrmoteras is a genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae and the sole member of the tribe Myrmoteratini .
Callicarpa rubella is a species of beautyberry native to Southeast Asia .
The Phyllobacteriaceae are a family of bacteria that contain nine genera .
Lhotzkyella is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1882 .
Pycnostachys is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 1826 .
Acrolepis ( Ancient Greek for `` Tip Scale '' ) is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived from the Tournaisian stage of the Mississippian epoch to the Late Permian .
Geastrum leptospermum is a species of fungus in the Geastraceae family .
Blaberus is a genus of cockroaches generally found in South America .
Harttia surinamensis is a species of armored catfish of the family native to the coastal rivers of Suriname and French Guiana .
Vespinitocris is a genus of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , containing the following species : subgenus Ichneumonitocris Vespinitocris ichneumon ( Hintz , 1919 ) subgenus Vespinitocris Vespinitocris camerunica Breuning , 1956 Vespinitocris dux ( Jordan , 1894 ) Vespinitocris morio ( Jordan , 1903 ) Vespinitocris sessensis Breuning , 1950 Vespinitocris tavakiliani Sudre & Téocchi , 2005
Psoralea plicata is a herb species in the genus Psoralea found in Pakistan .
Acer yangbiense is a species of maple with a very restricted distribution in Yunnan , China , only known from around ten specimens from a single locality in Yangbi county .
Ussurella napolovi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ussurella .
Sabal maritima , is a species of palm which is native to Jamaica and Cuba .
Podocarpus cunninghamii is a species of conifer in the Podocarpaceae family , commonly known as Hall 's tōtara , mountain tōtara or thin - barked tōtara .
The Xylariaceae are a family of mostly small ascomycetous fungi .
Piptothrix is a genus of Mesoamerican plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Jaffueliobryum arsenei is a species of moss in the Grimmiaceae family .
Dendrortyx is a genus of bird in the Odontophoridae family .
Myxodes cristatus , the Sailfin clinid , is a species of clinid native to the Pacific coast of South America from central to southern Chile .
Limonium californicum is a species of sea lavender known by the common names western marsh rosemary and California sea lavender .
Ecsenius shirleyae , known commonly as the Shirley 's blenny in Indonesia , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Dactylicapnos ( climbing dicentra ; formerly included in Dicentra ) is a genus of frost - tender perennial or annual climbers native to the Himalayas , northern Burma , central southern China , and northern Vietnam .
Agyneta obscura is a species of sheet weaver found in Congo and Tanzania .
Bernardia myricifolia is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family known by the common names mouse 's eye .
Cadlina sparsa , common name the Dark - spot cadlina , is a species of sea slug or dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cadlinidae .
Steatocranus gibbiceps is species of cichlid native to the Malebo Pool and lower parts of the Congo River in Africa .
Holothyrus is a genus of mites in the order Holothyrida .
Allium siculum , known as honey garlic , Sicilian honey lily , Sicilian honey garlic , or Mediterranean bells , is a European and Turkish species of plants genus Allium .
Tropeognathus is a genus of large pterosaurs from the late Cretaceous Period of South America .
Promachoteuthis sulcus is a species of promachoteuthid squid .
Conus pennaceus , common name the feathered cone or the episcopal cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Philodromus vulgaris is a species of spider , commonly called the longlegged crab spider , in the genus Philodromus found in the USA and Canada .
Picea glauca , the white spruce , is a species of spruce native to the northern temperate and boreal forests in North America .
Phitosia is a genus of Greek plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family .
Telmatobius macrostomus , also known as the Lake Junin ( giant ) frog or Andes smooth frog , is a very large and endangered species of frog in the Telmatobiidae family , endemic to altitudes of 3,200 - -4,300 m ( 10,500 - -14,100 ft ) in the Andes of Junín in central Peru .
Galium johnstonii ( Johnston 's bedstraw ) is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Poecilopsetta is a genus of small righteye flounders mainly found in deep water in the Indo - Pacific .
It contains only one species , Minicorona tricarpa , which is found in South Africa .
Rhinosardinia is a small genus of sprats restricted to the rivers of South America .
Sphodromantis annobonensis is a species of praying mantis found in Guinea and on the Equatorial Guinea island of Annobón Province .
Crataegus rivularis is a species of hawthorn known by the common name river hawthorn .
Horsfieldia carnosa is a plant species in the family Myristicaceae .
Baccharis neglecta ( also known as False Willow , Jara dulce , Poverty Weed , New Deal weed , and Roosevelt Weed ) is a species of perennial plant from sunflower family .
Terminalia ivorensis ( also called Ivory Coast almond , idigbo , black afara , framire , emeri and various other names ) is a species of tree in the family Combretaceae .
Berteroa incana is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family , Brassicaceae .
Barbarea orthoceras is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name American yellowrocket .
Eremias lalezharica ( commonly known as the Lalehzar Racerunner ) is a species of lizard found in the Iranian village of Lalehzar .
Eremias suphani ( commonly known as the Suphan Racerunner ) is a species of lizard found in the vicinity of Lake Van , Turkey .
Stanhopea nigripes is a species of orchid endemic to Peru .
Sibynophis collaris , commonly known as the common many - toothed snake or the collared black - headed snake , is a species of colubrid snake endemic to South Asia .
The Strawberry Spider or Orange Wheelweaving Spider ( Araneus alsine ) is a species of the orb - weaving spider ( Araneidae ) family .
The Proserpine rock - wallaby ( Petrogale persephone ) is a species of rock - wallaby restricted to a small area in Conway National Park , Dryander National Park , Gloucester Island National Park , and around the town of Airlie Beach , all in Whitsunday Shire in Queensland , Australia .
Suevoleviathan is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur , found in the Early Jurassic , Toarcian , of Holzmaden , Germany .
Discothyrea is a genus of small ants in the subfamily Proceratiinae .
Trautvetteria is a genus of flowering plants in the buttercup family .
Bandfishes are a family , Cepolidae , of perciform marine fishes .
Blepharotes aterrimus is a species of assassin fly native to Indonesia .
Nimbaphrynoides liberiensis is a species of toad from highlands in the Mount Nimba region of Liberia .
Stenurella melanura is a beetle species of flower longhorns belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Lepturinae .
Merodoras nheco is the only species in the genus Merodoras of the catfish ( order Siluriformes ) family Doradidae .
Scyllarus arctus is a species of slipper lobster which lives in the Mediterranean Sea and eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Tachymenes is a small ( 3 species currently recognized ) afrotropical genus of potter wasps restricted to Southern Africa .
Helixanthera schizocalyx is a species of loranth , or tropical mistletoe , discovered by a research team from Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew on Mount Mabu in northern Mozambique in 2008 .
Asclepias cryptoceras is a species of milkweed known by the common names jewel milkweed , pallid milkweed , Humboldt Mountains milkweed , and cow - cabbage .
Rubus arcuans , the wand dewberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Pachyiulus asiaeminoris is a species of millipede from Julidae family .
Clusia carinata is a species of flowering plant in the Clusiaceae family .
Athous propinquus is a species of click beetle from Elateridae family which can be found in Bulgaria and European part of Turkey .
Oreobates saxatilis is a frog species in the Craugastoridae family .
Lasthenia fremontii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Frémont 's goldfields ( after John C. Frémont ) .
Maxillaria lindleyana , the Lindley 's Maxillaria , is a species of orchid occurring from Brazil to Peru .
Cladorhizidae is a family of demosponges which are carnivorous and prey on crustaceans and other small animals .
Leuciscus merzbacheri , or the Zhungarian ide , is a species of cyprinid fish from the Junggar basin in Xingjian , China .
Albertaceratops ( meaning `` Alberta horned face '' ) was a genus of centrosaurine horned dinosaur from the middle Campanian - age Upper Cretaceous Oldman Formation of Alberta , Canada .
Hermosilla azurea , the zebra - perch sea chub , is a species of sea chub native to the Pacific coast of North America where it occurs from Monterey Bay , California to the Gulf of California .
Erigeron acomanus is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names bluewater fleabane and Acoma fleabane .
The Deccan ground gecko , Cyrtodactylus deccanensis , is a species of gecko found in the northern Western Ghats of India .
Devario annandalei is a species of fish of the family Cyprinidae found in the Chao Phraya , Salween and Mekong river basins .
Allium archeotrichon is a species of onion endemic to the Greek island of Rhodes in the Aegean Sea .
Tragopogon mirus Ownbey , the remarkable goatsbeard , is a species native to the States of Washington and Idaho .
Scuticaria salesiana is a species of orchid ranging from southeastern Ecuador to Peru .
Euprepiophis is a genus of nonvenomous colubrid snakes , containing three species of Asian rat snakes which were formerly assigned to the genus Elaphe .
Mesothelae is a suborder of spiders ( order Araneae ) that includes a single living ( extant ) family , Liphistiidae , and a number of extinct families .
Erigeron neomexicanus , the New Mexico fleabane , is a plant species native to New Mexico , Arizona , Sonora , and Chihuahua .
Dorylaimida ( dorylaims ) is a diverse order of nematodes with both soil and freshwater species .
Rosa spithamea is a species of rose known by the common names ground rose and coast ground rose .
Abbottina obtusirostris is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Abbottina who are found in the upper Yangtze River in Szechwan , China .
Hieronyma macrocarpa is a species of plant in the family Phyllanthaceae , which was recently separated from the Euphorbiaceae .
Cupaniopsis baileyana is a species of flowering tree in the soapberry family .
Omobranchus banditus , the Bandit blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean .
Esomus danricus , a Danionin known as the Indian Flying Barb is one of the species known as Flying Barbs owing to their extremely long barbels .
Amphibulima browni is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Amphibulimidae .
Cosberella lamaralexanderi , or the Lamar Alexander springtail , is a species of springtail native to the southern Appalachian Mountains of the United States .
Moodnodes plorella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Moodnodes .
Ayarnangra estuarius is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Erethistidae .
Antennaria is a genus of herbaceous perennial plants in the family Asteraceae , native to temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere , with one species ( A. chilensis ) in temperate southern South America ; the highest species diversity is in North America .
Litoria macki is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to West Papua , Indonesia .
It contains a single species , Androngo trivittatus .
Juniperus cedrus ( Canary Islands juniper ) is a species of juniper , native to the western Canary Islands ( Tenerife , La Palma , Gran Canaria , Gomera ) and Madeira ( J. cedrus Webb & Berthel . subsp . maderensis ( Menezes ) Rivas Mart et al . )
Stereognathus is a genus of tritylodont therapsids from the Bathonian ( Middle Jurassic ) of the United Kingdom .
Allium grisellum is a plant species endemic to Xinjiang .
Darwinilus sedarisi is a species of rove beetle , the only species in the genus Darwinilus .
Quercus hintoniorum is a Mexican species of trees in the beech family .
Thalassoma amblycephalum , the blunt - headed wrasse , is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
The Miliolida are an order of protists which comprise Foraminifera with calcareous , porcelacous tests that are imperforate and commonly have a pseudochitinous lining .
Rhytidocaulon is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described in 1962 .
Cynophalla hastata is a plant species in the genus Cynophalla .
Lindmania cylindrostachya is a species in the genus Lindmania .
Juncus maritimus , known as the sea rush , is a species of rush that grows on coastlines .
Phaseolus filiformis is a species of wild bean native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Calappoidea is a superfamily of crabs comprising the two families Calappidae and Matutidae .
Monardella siskiyouensis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Siskiyou monardella .
The Dark Broken - band Oakblue or Indian Oakblue ( Arhopala atrax ) is a species of lycaenid or blue butterfly found in Asia .
Elacatinus chancei , the shortstripe goby , is a species of ray - finned fish in the family Gobiidae .
Astrophytum asterias is a species of cactus in the genus Astrophytum , and is native to small parts of Texas in the United States and Mexico .
Sphecius speciosus , often simply referred to as the cicada killer or the cicada hawk , is a large digger wasp species .
The order Notostraca comprises the single family Triopsidae , containing the tadpole shrimp or shield shrimp .
It contains the species Spratticeps gaultinus .
Papaver somniferum , the opium poppy , is the species of plant from which opium and poppy seeds are derived .
Scobinichthys granulatus also known as the Rough leatherjackets is a species of filefish native to the coastal waters of southern Australia .
Hymenocallis proterantha is a species of spider lily known only from Mexico ( States of Colima , Jalisco , Michoacán , Nayarit ) .
Aecidium magellanicum , commonly known as the calafate rust , is a species of rust fungi .
Drosera prolifera is a species of Drosera found in Queensland , Australia .
The species name refers to the similarity between Galagete consimilis and Galagete darwini .
The only species is Hydrorion brachypterygius .
The Gulf Coast box turtle ( Terrapene carolina major ) is the largest subspecies of the North American box turtle ( Terrapene carolina ) .
The genus Poromera is monotypic , containing the single species , Poromera fordii , commonly known as the West African striped lizard .
Chalcides bedriagai , commonly known as Bedriaga 's skink , is a species of lizard endemic to the Iberian Peninsula .
Amblychilepas javanicensis , common name the rayed keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Aethiessa floralis is a species of beetles belonging to the family Scarabaeidae , subfamily Cetoniinae .
Minopa legrandi , common name Legrand 's top shell , is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Neuquensaurus ( meaning `` Neuquén lizard '' ) is a genus of saltasaurid sauropod dinosaur that appeared in the Late Cretaceous , 71 million years ago in Argentina and Uruguay in South America .
Shigella ( /ʃɪˈɡɛlə/ ) is a genus of Gram - negative , facultative anaerobic , non - spore - forming , non - motile , rod - shaped bacteria closely related to Salmonella .
Carabus catenulatus is a species of beetle endemic to Europe , where it is observed in Bosnia and Herzegovina , mainland Italy , Slovenia , and Switzerland .
Lichnomesopsyche is an extinct genus of mesopsychid mecopteran which existed in what is now China during the middle Jurassic period .
Liaoxipterus is a genus of pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Barremian - Aptian - age Lower Cretaceous Jiufotang Formation of Chaoyang , Liaoning , China .
Saprolegniaceae is a family of freshwater mould .
Sagittaria isoetiformis , common name quillwort arrowhead , is an aquatic plant species native to Cuba and to the southeastern United States ( Florida , Alabama , Mississippi , Georgia , North Carolina and South Carolina ) .
Cercospora is a genus of ascomycete fungi .
The longicorn beetle Phoracantha obscura is a species of beetle native to Australia .
Trissonchulus janetae is a species of nematode from the Ironidae family .
Hadogenes soutpansbergensis is a scorpion species .
Acanthoctenus is a spider genus from Central to South America .
Microvenator ( meaning `` small hunter '' ) is a genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous Cloverly Formation in what is now south central Montana .
Boerhavia wrightii is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family known by the common name largebract spiderling .
Duerotherium is an extinct genus of anoplotheriine artiodactyl which existed in Iberian Peninsula during the middle Eocene .
Austroplatypus is a genus of weevils native to Australia that includes Austroplatypus incompertus , the first beetle to be recognized as a eusocial insect .
Laticranium mandibulare is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Laticranium .
Terpnissa listropterina is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Terpnissa .
Cicada orni is a species of cicada belonging to the family Cicadidae , subfamily Cicadinae and the genus Cicada .
Synchytriaceae is a chytrid fungus family in the division Chytridiomycota .
The cold - growing cymbidium ( Cymbidium kanran ) is a species of orchid .
Tachyporus is a genus of rove beetle in the tribe Tachyporini .
Anniealexandria is an extinct genus of amphisbaenian lizard known by the type species Anniealexandria gansi from the earliest Eocene of Wyoming .
Armina semperi is a species of sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Arminidae .
Methanobrevibacter cuticularis is a species of methanogen archaeon .
Shamosaurus is an extinct genus of herbivorous basal ankylosaurid ankylosaur from Early Cretaceous ( Aptian to Albian stage ) deposits of Höövör , Mongolia .
Polybaphes is a genus of fruit and flower chafers belonging to the family Scarabaeidae , subfamily Cetoniinae .
Agyneta gulosa is a species of sheet weaver found in the Palearctic .
Belgica antarctica , the Antarctic midge , is a species of flightless midge , endemic to the continent of Antarctica .

Acanthoceras rhotomagensis is an extinct cephalopod species belonging to the subclass Ammonoidea and family Acanthoceratidae .
Echiostoma barbatum , the Threadfin dragonfish , is a species of barbeled dragonfish and is the only known species in its genus .
The Goat - horned Epidendrum ( Epidendrum capricornu ) is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Sagittaria ambigua , the Kansas arrowhead , is an aquatic plant species native to the central United States ( Indiana , Illinois , Arkansas , Missouri , Kansas and Oklahoma ) .
Onychomyrmex doddi is a species of ant in the genus Onychomyrmex , endemic to Australia .
Koanophyllon solidaginifolium , the Shrubby umbrella thoroughwort , is a plant species native to Arizona , western Texas , New Mexico , Chihuahua , Coahuila , Durango , Jalisco , and Zacatecas .
Catabrosa is a small but widespread genus of plants in the grass family native to temperate areas of Eurasia , the Americas , and a few places in Africa .
Hessea is a genus of bulb - forming plants in the Amaryllis family native to Namibia and South Africa .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pseudociboria umbrina .
Buckley 's slender - legged tree frog , Osteocephalus buckleyi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , French Guiana , Guyana , Peru , Suriname , and Venezuela .
Beris clavipes , the scarce orange legionnaire , is a European species of soldier fly .
Ficopomatus enigmaticus , commonly known as the Australian tubeworm , is a species of serpulid tubeworms .
Neolamprologus tretocephalus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is found in sandy areas in the northern half of the lake .
Pavoclinus caeruleopunctatus is a species of clinid native to the Atlantic coast of South Africa where it has been found at a depth of about 6 metres ( 20 ft ) .
Albinaria hippolyti is a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the genus Albinaria of the family Clausiliidae , the door snails .
Brickellia floribunda ( Chihuahuan brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
The conifers , division Pinophyta , also known as division Coniferophyta or Coniferae , are one of 12 extant division - level taxa within the Kingdom Plantae ( Viridiplantae ) and 10 within the extant land plants .
Galium glaucum or waxy bedstraw is a plant species of the Rubiaceae .
Eunephrops bairdii is a species of marine lobster , commonly called the `` red lobster '' , endemic to the Caribbean Sea .
Dorstenia umbricola is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Peru and Ecuador .
Moron distigma is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Moron .
Dubautia kalalauensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Aperioptus is a genus of loach only found in Southeast Asia .
Acacia nigricans is a species of wattle which is endemic to an area on the south coast of Western Australia .
Chloropeta was a genus of Acrocephalidae warblers ; formerly , they were placed in the paraphyletic `` Old World warblers '' .
Tepuidessus breweri is a member of the order Coleoptera ( Beetles ) in the family of water dwelling Dytiscidae beetles , and is the only species in the genus Tepuidessus .
Mordellistena csiki is a species of beetle in the Mordellidae family which is in the Mordellistena genus .
Pimoa cthulhu is a species of the spider family Pimoidae .
Altenglanerpeton is an extinct genus of microsaur amphibian from the Late Carboniferous or Early Permian of Germany .
Leptospermum nitidum , commonly known as Shining Tea - tree , is a shrub species that is endemic to Tasmania .
Liogma is a genus of crane fly in the family Tipulidae .

Masdevallia weberbaueri is a species of orchid found from southern Ecuador into northern Peru .

Aenigma iris is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Aenigma .
Bathymodiolus marisindicus is a species of deepwater hydrothermal vent mussel , a marine bivalve mollusk species in the family Mytilidae , the mussels .

Aegires punctilucens is a species of sea slug .
Ochrosia kilaueaensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the Plumeria family , Apocynaceae .
Prosopis humilis , the algarrobilla or algaroba ( carob in Spanish ) , is a mesquite , a flowering plant and a tree species in the genus Prosopis found in Argentina .
Drimiopsis maculata , also known by the common names little white soldiers , African false hosta , African hosta , leopard plant , is a flowering plant species in the genus Drimiopsis .
Scirpus ancistrochaetus is a rare species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names barbedbristle bulrush and northeastern bulrush .
