Juglans hindsii , commonly called the Northern California walnut and Hinds ' black walnut , is a species of walnut tree endemic to Northern California .
The genus Enchytraeus includes about 40 species of annelid worms .
Malapterurus shirensis is a species of electric catfish native to the Zambezi River basin where it occurs in the countries of Mozambique , Zambia and Zimbabwe .
Sporophila is a genus of Neotropical birds in the family Thraupidae .
Streptomyces baliensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from the Eka Karya Botanic Garden on the Bali Island in Indonesia .
Atriplex suberecta is a species of saltbush known by the common names sprawling saltbush , lagoon saltbush and ( in Britain and Ireland ) Australian orache .
Halictus lucudipennis is a species of bees in the genus Halictus , of the family Halictidae .
Cyrteumenes is a member of the malagasy genus of potter wasps .
Cabomba furcata is a species of aquatic plant in the water shield family known by the common names red cabomba and forked fanwort .
Ranunculus aconitifolius ( aconite - leaf buttercup , bachelor 's buttons ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae , native to central Europe .
Hongshuia is a genus of cyprinid fish that consists of three species , all endemic to China .
Leafhopper is a common name applied to any species from the family Cicadellidae .
Crataegus maximowiczii is a species of hawthorn with fruit that are red to purple - black .
Tetradymia tetrameres is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name fourpart horsebrush and dune horsebrush .
Skipperlings are butterflies in the subfamily Heteropterinae .
Austroglossus is a genus of soles native to the Atlantic coast of southern Africa .
Phragmipedium hirtzii is a species of orchid endemic to northern Ecuador .
Cyrnaonyx is an extinct genus of Lutrinae , otters from the Pleistocene .
Archaeohyracidae is an extinct family comprising four genera of notoungulate mammals known from the Paleocene through the Oligocene of South America .
Anguispira alternata , common name the flamed disc or flamed tigersnail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Discidae , the disk snails .
Trachysphaera is a genus of pill millipedes in the order Glomerida .
Nemanthus is a genus of sea anemones that contains three recognised species .
Leptotyphlops macrops , or the Large - eyed worm snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Cumnoria is a genus of herbivorous iguanodontian dinosaur .
Agathiceras applini is a species of Agathiceras , named by Plummer and Scott in 1937 .
Delavalia polluta is a species of copepod in the family Miraciidae , first described in 1928 by Monard .
Ilex serrata is a species in the Ilex ( holly ) genus and the Aquifoliaceae family .
Daphne blagayana is a species of plant in the genus Daphne .
Athrotaxis laxifolia is a species of Athrotaxis , endemic to Tasmania in Australia , where it grows at 1,000 - -1,200 m altitude .
Potamotrygon is a genus of freshwater stingrays native to the rivers of South America .
Donax trunculus ( abrupt wedge shell , wedge clam ) , is a bivalve species in the family Donacidae .
Trochochlamys ogasawarana is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Euconulidae .
Stagnicola elodes is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Lymnaeidae , the pond snails .
Balanoglossus australiensis is a species of 20 centimetres ( 7.9 in ) long acorn worm in Ptychoderidae family which can be found in Gulf of Carpentaria , New Zealand , Western Australian cities such as Hawkesbury and Manning as well as Solomon Archipelago and its sea .
Phymata crassipes is a species of assassin and thread - legged bugs belonging to the family Reduviidae , subfamily Phymatinae .
Zosne matangensis is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Zosne that was discovered by Breuning in 1950 .
Heuchera pilosissima is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name seaside alumroot and Parish 's alumroot .
Leontiniidae is an extinct family comprising eleven genera of notoungulate mammals known from the middle Eocene through middle Miocene of South America ( McKenna and Bell , 1997 ) .
Norfolcioconch iota is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc , in the family Charopidae .
Chlorops pumilionis is a species of pest fly from the family Chloropidae .
Persicaria capitata , the pink - headed persicaria , pinkhead smartweed , pink knotweed , Japanese knotweed , or pink bubble persicaria , is an Asian species of plants in the Persicaria genus within the buckwheat family .
Nebria caucasica is a species of ground beetle from the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Caucasus .
Gonocephalum assimile is a species of darkling beetle in the family Tenebrionidae .
Sauropleurinae is an extinct subfamily of lepospondyl amphibians .
Kemkemia is a genus of crocodyliforms living in the Cretaceous , described from a single fossil in 1999 recovered from Morocco by an Italian team searching for fossil invertebrates .
Otopharynx tetraspilus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the southern end of the lake .
Imperata brevifolia is a species of grass known by the common name California satintail .
Acaronia is a small genus of cichlids found in the Amazon , Orinoco and other basins in northern South America .
Mycena interrupta , commonly known as the pixie 's parasol , is a species of mushroom .
Scaptia is a genus of horse fly .
Oncidium crispum is a species of orchid endemic to eastern and southern Brazil .
Jepsonia parryi is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common names coast jepsonia and Parry 's jepsonia .
Pulsatilla pratensis ( small pasque flower ) is a species of the genus Pulsatilla , native to central and eastern Europe , from southeast Norway and western Denmark south and east to Bulgaria .
Richardsonius balteatus , the redside shiner , is a species of cyprinid fish found in the western United States and Canada .
Pseudagrion acaciae , the acacia sprite is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
The family Crangonidae is a taxon of shrimp , of the superfamily Crangonoidea , including the commercially important species Crangon crangon .
Lycodon fasciatus , commonly known as the banded wolf snake , is a species of colubrid snake .
Rhinophis sanguineus , commonly known as the salty earth snake , is a species of uropeltid snake found in the Western Ghats of India .
Zanthoxylum nitidum is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family .
Mycena stylobates , commonly known as the bulbous bonnet , is a species of inedible mushroom in the family Mycenaceae .
Chionactis palarostris , commonly known as the Sonoran shovelnose snake , is a species of small nonvenomous colubrid which is a native of the Sonoran Desert in North America .
Ulearum sagittatum is a species in the family Araceae .
Aegocidnexocentrus tippmanni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aegocidnexocentrus .
Procerusternarchus pixuna is a species of bluntnose knifefish endemic to Amazonas , Brazil where it occurs in several tributaries of the Rio Negro .
Lambertocyon is a genus of ungulates from western North America .
Edenopteron is a genus of large tristichopterid fish from the Late Devonian ( Famennian ) of what is now southeastern Australia .
Eremospatha is a genus of climbing flowering plants in the palm family found in tropical Africa .
Krameria is the only genus in the Krameriaceae family , of which any of the approximately 17 species are commonly known as Rhatany , ratany or rattany .
Conomurex persicus , common name : the Persian Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Magnolia wilsonii , the Wilson 's Magnolia , is a species of Magnolia native to China , in the provinces of western Guizhou , Sichuan and northern Yunnan , where it grows in the forest understory at altitudes of 1,900 - 3,000 m , rarely up to 3,300 m.
Disciseda bovista is a rare species of gasteroid fungus in the family Agaricaceae .
Diplometopon zarudnyi , also called Zarudny 's worm lizard , is a species of amphisbaenian reptile in the Trogonophidae family .
Rhododendron sphaeroblastum ( 宽叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to southwestern Sichuan and northern Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 3300 - -4400 meters .
Chiloglanis reticulatus is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Dja River system in Cameroon and the Luala and Lufu River drainages in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Allium schubertii is a plant species found in Israel , Palestine , Syria , Lebanon , Turkey and Libya but grown as an ornamental elsewhere .
Incilius ibarrai ( common name : Jalapa toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Xenambyx lansbergei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Xenambyx .
Pterygoplichthys joselimaianus , is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Tocantins River basin .
Colpodellida is an order of alveolate protists , which includes small predatory species such as Colpodella pugnax .
Brachycephalus pernix is a species of frog in the Brachycephalidae family endemic to Brazil ; it is known from Morro do Anhangava and Morretes , Paraná and occurs at 450 meters above sea level .
Hydrophis obscurus , commonly known as Russell 's sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Lissonanchus lusheri , the Streaky clingfish , is a species of clingfish only known from one specimen collected off the coast of southern Mozambique .
Cyathostemon is a genus of flowering plants in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Micropelta rugosicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Micropelta .
Anaxidia is a genus of Limacodid moths found in Australia , including Western Australia .
Syngnathus safina is a pipefish species , inhabits the western part of the Indian Ocean , the Gulf of Aqaba .
Calliergon cordifolium is a species of moss in the Amblystegiaceae family commonly known as the calliergon moss ( though this name refers to the genus Calliergon generally ) or heart - leaved spearmoss .
Pohlidium is a genus of Panamanian plants in the grass family .
Comparison of mtDNA NADH dehydrogenase subunit 2 and 3 sequences indicates that the Ipswich sparrow , formerly usually considered a valid species ( as Passerculus princeps ) , is a well - marked subspecies of the Savannah sparrow , whereas the southwestern large - billed sparrow should be recognized as a distinct species ( Passerculus rostratus ) .
Paraprefica , a medium - sized bird , has skull and legs somewhat resembling today 's potoos , in the genus Nyctibius .
Dehalogenimonas is a genus in the phylum Chloroflexi ( Bacteria ) .
The Crassulaceae , also known as the stonecrop family or the orpine family , are a family of dicotyledons with succulent leaves .
Neocrepidodera puncticollis is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Romania , Slovakia , and Ukraine .
Goniobranchus fidelis , also commonly known as the faithful sea slug , is a species of colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Acer douglasense is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from fossil leaves .
Acropora tenuis is a species of acroporid coral found in the Red Sea , the Gulf of Aden , the southwest , northwest and northern Indian Ocean , the Persian Gulf , the central Indo - Pacific , Australia , Southeast Asia , Japan , the East China Sea and the oceanic west and central Pacific Ocean .
Colombian weasel ( Mustela felipei ) , also known as the Don Felipe 's weasel , is a very rare species of weasel only known with certainty from the departments of Huila and Cauca in Colombia and nearby northern Ecuador ( where only known from a single specimen ) .
Bagrichthys vaillantii is one of species of bagrid catfish in the genus Bagrichthys .
Streptomyces hypolithicus is a filamentous bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Miers Valley in the McMurdo Dry Valleys in Eastern Antarctica .
Tauschia kelloggii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Kellogg 's umbrellawort .
Pupilla muscorum , commonly known as the Moss Chrysalis snail , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pupillidae .
Poraster superbus is a species of sea star in the family Orestieridae .
Bessera is a genus of Mexican plants in the cluster lily subfamily within the asparagus family .
Dolomena labiosa , common name : the Thick - lipped Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Franklinoceras is an extinct cephalopod genus from the nautiloid order , Discosorida .
Nemacladus sigmoideus is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name sigmoid threadplant .
Ictidosuchoides is an extinct genus of ictidosuchid therocephalian .
Capito is a genus of birds in the Capitonidae family .
Chlorophytum holstii is a flowering plant species in the genus Chlorophytum , endemic to Tanzania and Kenya .
Holochilus brasiliensis , also known as the Brazilian marsh rat or web - footed marsh rat , is a species of semiaquatic rodent from South America .
Tulipa serbica is a species of tulip native to southeastern Serbia and northern Kosovo .
Lilium pumilum is an Asian species of bulbous plants native to Mongolia , Siberia , the Russian Far East ( Amur Krai , Primorye , Khabarovsk ) , Korea and northern China .
Stigmatomma saundersi is a species of ant in the genus Stigmatomma , endemic to New Zealand .
Leptolalax bourreti ( Bourret 's Asian toad or Bourret litter frog ) is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Uncinia ecuadorensis is a species of plant in the Cyperaceae family .
Zabrus seriatus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that can be found in Turkey and Erzerum , Armenia .
Antennohyllisia rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Antennohyllisia .
Prunum boreale , common name the boreal marginella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Plantago patagonica is a species of plantain known by the common name woolly plantain .
Euphorbia antiquorum , known as Antique Spurge and `` Euphorbia of the Ancients '' , is a species of succulent plant in the Euphorbiaceae family .
Cymopterus gilmanii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Gilman 's springparsley .
Uroleucon erigeronense , described by Thomas ( 1878 ) , is a species of aphid that feeds on plants of the Erigeron or fleabane genus .
Uropeltis beddomii , commonly known as Beddome 's earth snake , is a species of snake in the family Uropeltidae .
Parapezus angolensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parapezus .
Lycomormium is a genus of orchids , with 5 currently recognized species found in Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
Aedes africanus is a species of mosquito that is found on the continent of Africa with the exclusion of Madagascar .
Solidago altissima , the Canada goldenrod or late goldenrod , is a North American species of goldenrod widespread across much of Canada , the United States , and northern Mexico .
It contains only one species Notiopostega atrata which is known only from the coastal hills of the Valdivia Province in Chile .
Zingel asper , the apron , is a species of fish in the Percidae family that is at a high risk of becoming extinct due to habitat destruction and pollution .
Luzula canariensis is a plant species in the genus Luzula , family Juncaceae .
Tettigonia viridissima , the Great Green Bush - Cricket , is a large species of katydid or cricket belonging to the family Tettigoniidae , subfamily Tettigoniinae .
Sinogastromyzon tonkinensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sinogastromyzon .
Odontella aurita is a diatom and the type species of genus Odontella .
Ceratophrys is a genus of frogs in the family Ceratophryidae .
The genus contains a single species , Hartwrightia floridana , native to the US States of Georgia and Florida .
Astacus ( from the Greek αστακός , astacós , meaning `` lobster '' or `` crayfish '' ) is a genus of crayfish found in Europe and western Asia , comprising three extant and four extinct species .
Ruiz 's robber frog , scientific name Strabomantis ruizi , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Pelycodus is an extinct genus of adapiform primate that lived during the early Eocene ( Wasatchian ) period in Europe and North America , particularly Wyoming and New Mexico .
Schizostachyum chinense is a species of bamboo ( tribe Bambuseae of the family Poaceae ) .
The shining ram's - horn snail , Segmentina nitida , is a species of minute , air - breathing , freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails .
Eriphia is a genus of crabs , including the following species :
Vieraea is a genus of Canary Island plants in the Inuleae tribe within the daisy family .
Jacquinia is a genus of evergreen shrubs and trees in the family Primulaceae , native to Central America and the Caribbean .
It is known from one fossil found at Jianchang , Liaoning Province , in rocks of the Jiufotang Formation , representing the type species Zhongjianornis yangi .
Porcellio spinipennis is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found in such European countries as Austria , France , Germany , Italy , and Slovakia .
Tanganya virus ( TGNV ) is an enveloped , single - stranded , negative - sense RNA virus species of the genus hantavirus in the Bunyaviridae family .
Reishia armigera , common name : the Belligerent Rock Shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Oonopsis , false goldenweed , is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Cyathea decrescens is a species of tree fern endemic to Madagascar .
Myrichthys is a genus of snake eels currently containing 12 recognized species found in tropical and warm temperate oceans worldwide .
Polaribacter franzmannii is a species of gas vacuolate polar marine bacteria .
Paratanais tara is a species of tanaidomorphan malacostracan crustacean found in New Zealand .
Pilobolus crystallinus var . crystallinus , commonly known as the `` Dung Cannon '' or `` Hat Thrower '' , is a species of fungus belonging to the Mucorales order .
Urothemis thomasi , the Omani dragonfly , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Kolponomos is an extinct genus of carnivoran mammal that existed from the Hemingfordian age to the Aquitanian age of the Miocene epoch , about 20 million years ago .
Dinochloa is a genus of tropical clumping high - climbing bamboos in the grass family .
Carabus linnaei is a species of gray - coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Bulgaria , Czech Republic , Germany , Hungary , Italy , Moldova , Poland , Romania , Russia , Slovakia , and Ukraine .
Hydroptila apalachicola is a species of microcaddisfly .
Aurelia labiata is a species of Moon Jellyfish in the genus Aurelia .
The genus contains a single species , Majungasaurus crenatissimus .
Ophiorrhiza is a genus of flowering plants in the coffee ( Rubiaceae ) family .
Vaccinium myrsinites is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common name shiny blueberry .
The Entolomataceae , also known as Rhodophyllaceae , are a large family of pink - spored terrestrial gilled mushrooms which includes the genera Entoloma , Rhodocybe , and Clitopilus .
Aldrovandia gracilis is a species of fish in the Halosauridae family .
Platydemus manokwari , also known as the New Guinea flatworm , is a species of large predatory land flatworm .
Trigona corvina ( Cockerell , 1913 ) is a species of stingless bees that lives primarily in Central and South America .
Dusky pipefish ( Syngnathus floridae ) is a species of the pipefishes , widespread in the western Atlantic from the Bermuda , Chesapeake Bay ( USA ) , northern part of the Gulf of Mexico , Bahama , and the western Caribbean Sea to Panama in south .
Mercuria confusa , common name the ' `` swollen spire snail '' , is a northern European species of small brackish water or freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Cephalotes supercilii is a species of arboreal ant of the genus Cephalotes , characterized by an odd shaped head and the ability to `` parachute '' by steering their fall if they drop off of a tree .
Longitarsus suturellus is a species of beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae that can be found in Central Europe , Central Italy , Southern England , South Sweden , Mongolia , and Algeria .
Stegodibelodon is an extinct genus of elephant or gomphothere from the Miocene .
Euonymus fortunei ( common names spindle or Fortune 's spindle , winter creeper or wintercreeper ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Celastraceae , native to east Asia , including China , Korea , the Philippines and Japan .
Arenga engleri , or the Formosa Palm , Taiwan Sugar Palm , Dwarf sugar palm , or Taiwan arenga palm , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Aulopora is an extinct genus of tabulate coral characterized by a bifurcated budding pattern and conical corallites .
Rubus conanicutensis called the Conanicut Island blackberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Sigmodontomys is a genus of rodent in the tribe Oryzomyini of family Cricetidae .
Calochortus eurycarpus ( white mariposa lily ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the lily family .
It contains only one species , Thallostoma eurygrapha , which is found in New Zealand .
Euphilotes is a genus of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family , which consists of a number of species found in western North America .
The Manipur white - toothed rat ( Berylmys manipulus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Cryptocentroides is a genus of gobies native to the western Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Trachyderomorpha notabilis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Trachyderomorpha .

Engystomops coloradorum ( common name : Colorado dwarf frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Genista pilosa , commonly known as hairy greenweed , silkyleaf brooom , silkyleaf woadwaxen and creeping broom , is a plant species in the genus Genista .
Orthosternarchus tamandua is a species of weakly electric knifefish in the family Apteronotidae , native to the deep river channels of the Amazon basin .
Portieria hornemannii is a species of red algae in the family Rhizophyllidaceae .
Hydriris is a genus of pyraloid moths .
Neodavisia singularis is a species of snout moth in the genus Neodavisia .
Daviesia corymbosa , also known as narrow leaf bitter pea , is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae native to the state of New South Wales in eastern Australia .
Zabrus ignavus is a species of ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that can be found in Bulgaria , France , Greece , Italy , Kosovo , Montenegro , Portugal , Serbia , Slovenia , Spain , Voivodina , on islands such as Balearic , Corsica , Gibraltar , Sardinia , and Sicily , and in Morocco .
Nicotiana longiflora , the longflower tobacco or long - flowered tobacco , is a species of tobacco native to South America that is sometimes cultivated for its tubular flowers that emit a very sweet odour at night .
Hylocereus costaricensis , the Costa Rican pitahaya or Costa Rica nightblooming cactus , is a cactus species native to Central America and northwestern South America .
Sesamothamnus leistneranus is a species of plant in the Pedaliaceae family .
Albericus exclamitans is a species of frog in the family Microhylidae , the narrow - mouthed frogs .
Lupinus pratensis is a species of lupine known by the common name Inyo meadow lupine .
Oxalis pes - caprae ( Bermuda buttercup , African wood - sorrel , Bermuda sorrel , buttercup oxalis , Cape sorrel , English weed , goat's - foot , sourgrass , soursob and soursop ; ( Afrikaans : suring ) ) is a species of tristylous flowering plant in the wood sorrel family Oxalidaceae .
Lioptilodes arequipa is a species of moth in the genus Lioptilodes , known from Peru and Chile .
Zabrus distinctus is a species of ground beetle in the Aulacozabrus subgenus that can be found in Algeria and Morocco .
Neurothemis terminata is a species of dragonfly in family Libellulidae .
Eoscapherpeton is an extinct genus of prehistoric amphibian from the Bissekty Formation .
California mule deer ( Odocoileus hemionus californicus ) is a subspecies of mule deer whose range covers much of the state of California .
Odontotrema is a genus of fungi in the family Odontotremataceae .
Gigantoscorpio willsi is an extinct species of scorpion .
Phacelia affinis is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common names limestone phacelia and purple - bell scorpionweed .
Stomatella varia , common name the variable stomatella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Castanopsis hystrix is a species of evergreen broadleaf tree , which grows up to 30 meters in height .
Dipodium purpureum is an orchid species that is native to Borneo .
Cattleya crispata , commonly known as Laelia flava , is a species of orchid endemic to Minas Gerais , Brazil .
Calosoma marginatus is a species of grey coloured ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae which is endemic to Kazakhstan .
Maorimorpha is a small genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mitromorphidae , in the superfamily Conoidea the cone snails and their allies .
Exocarpos latifolius is a species of parasitic trees , of the plant family Santalaceae .
Herennia multipuncta , commonly known as the ornamental tree trunk spider , is a species of spider in the family Nephilidae native to Asia .
Milium effusum ( vernacular name American milletgrass or wood millet ) is a perennial species of grass in the Poaceae family , native to damp forests of the Holarctic Kingdom .
Adromischus marianae is a species of succulents in the genus Adromischus belonging to the family Crassulaceae .
Acidisphaera is a genus in the phylum Proteobacteria ( Bacteria ) .
Streblus banksii , commonly known as the large - leaved milk tree , is a species of plant in the family Moraceae that it endemic to New Zealand .
The only species is Haestasaurus becklesii .
Thylacoleo ( `` pouch lion '' ) is an extinct genus of carnivorous marsupials that lived in Australia from the late Pliocene to the late Pleistocene ( 2 million to 46 thousand years ago ) .

Synodontis irsacae is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Lake Tanganyika , where it is common and widely distributed .
Glossogobius is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters from Africa to the coasts of the western Pacific Ocean .
Corallimorphus is a genus of colonial anthozoans similar in appearance to sea anemones and in body format to scleractinian stony corals .
Prosthogonimus ovatus is a species of a trematode , or fluke worm , in the family Prosthogonimidae .
Pellaea breweri is a species of fern known by the common name Brewer 's cliffbrake .
Anoplotheriidae is an extinct family of even - toed ungulates ( order Artiodactyla ) .
Cadlina laevis , common name the white Atlantic cadlina , is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cadlinidae .
Sclerocactus glaucus is a rare species of cactus known by the common name Colorado hookless cactus .
Haliotis semiplicata , common name the semiplicate abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
The Nama padloper ( Homopus solus ) , previously known as Berger 's cape tortoise , is a species of tortoise in the Homopus ( `` padloper '' ) genus .
Pristimantis permixtus ( in Spanish : rana de muslos naranja , meaning `` Andean orange - thighed frog '' ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Marinula filholi is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Ellobiidae ; found in New Zealand .
Cirsium mohavense is a species of thistle known by the common name Mojave thistle .
Flourensia pringlei , Pringle 's tarwort , is a species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Bipedidae is a family of amphisbaenian lizards that includes the extant genus Bipes represented by four species from Mexico and the extinct genus Anniealexandria represented by one species that lived in what is now Wyoming during the earliest Eocene approximately 55 million years ago .
Melolontha is a genus of beetles in the family Scarabaeidae .
Bochicidae is a family of pseudoscorpions distributed throughout the Caribbean , Central America and Mexico with one species found as far north as Texas .
Cancelloxus longior is a species of clinid found in subtropical waters of the South African coast .
Megomphicidae is a taxonomic family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Acavoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Sirindhornia is a genus of flowering plants in the orchid family , Orchidaceae native to China and Indochina .
Dimeresia is a monotypic genus in the sunflower family containing the single species Dimeresia howellii , known by the common name doublet .
Rhagomys is a genus of South American rodents in the tribe Thomasomyini of the family Cricetidae .

Aspistor is a genus of sea catfishes found along the northeastern coast of South America where they occur in marine , brackish and fresh waters .

Melanoxena is a genus of moths in the Choreutidae family , containing only one species , Melanoxena falsissima , which is known from Colombia .
Costellariidae sometimes called the `` ribbed miters '' is a taxonomic family of minute to medium - sized predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks .
Sertulariidae is a family of cnidarians within the class Hydrozoa .
The Chloroperlidae are a family of stoneflies , commonly known as green stoneflies , with more than 180 species in 15 genera .
Rhabdinopora is a genus of graptolite .
Orthetrum brunneum , the southern skimmer , is a species of ' skimmers ' belonging to the family Libellulidae .
The Ratardinae are a small subfamily of large moths from Southeast Asia .
Crassula elegans , the Elegant Crassula , is a flowering plant species in the genus Crassula .
Clytra cingulata is a species of leaf beetle from the subfamily Clytrini that can be found in Asia Minor and the Middle East .
Kurixalus idiootocus is a small species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Brickellia hastata is a North American species of shrubs in the daisy family .
Helianthodae is a supertribe in the family Asteraceae , the aster family , containing the tribes Anthrosimeae , Coreopsideae , Eupatorieae , Helenieae , Heliantheae , Inuleae , and Tageteae .
Recilia trifasciatus is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that can be found on Canary Islands and countries including Iran and Burkina Faso .
The Ifola tree - kangaroo ( Dendrolagus notatus ) is a species of marsupial in the family Macropodidae .
Ligusticum grayi is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Gray 's licorice - root .
Mycena adscendens , commonly known as the frosty bonnet , is a species of fungus in the family Mycenaceae .

Pterygotrigla is a genus of searobins native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Mezobromelia pleiosticha is a species in the genus Mezobromelia .
Masdevallia elephanticeps is a species of orchid occurring at high elevations in the Cordillera Oriental of Colombia .
Spathicephalus is an extinct genus of stem tetrapods ( early four - limbed vertebrates ) that lived during the middle of the Carboniferous Period .
Salix nigra ( black willow ) is a species of willow native to eastern North America , from New Brunswick and southern Ontario west to Minnesota , and south to northern Florida and Texas .
Cymbiolacca pulchra wisemani is a subspecies of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family volutidae , the volutes .

Mopalia hindsii is a species of medium sized chiton that grows up to 7 cm long .

Horkelia rydbergii is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Rydberg 's horkelia .
Bistahieversor ( meaning `` Bistahi destroyer '' ) is a genus of tyrannosaurid dinosaur .
Myrsine fusca is a species of plant in the Primulaceae family of Old World tropical trees and shrubs , with some in Florida and Polynesia .
Nyctiphanes is a genus of krill , comprising four species with an anti - tropical distribution .
Cantherhines fronticinctus , known commonly as the Spectacled filefish , is a species of marine fish in the family Monacanthidae .
Sobralia is a genus of about 125 orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) and one of the two genera of the subtribe Sobraliinae ( the other is Elleanthus ) .
Forrest 's pika ( Ochotona forresti ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Whatcheeriidae is an extinct family of tetrapods which lived in the Mississippian sub - period , a subdivision of the Carboniferous period .
Drymarchon is a genus of large nonvenomous colubrid snakes , commonly known as indigo snakes , endemic to the Southeastern United States , Central America , and South America .
Cheiracanthium is a genus of spiders in the Eutichuridae family .
Clavariadelphus ligula , commonly known as the strap coral , is an inedible species of fungi in the Gomphaceae family .
Carabus agamemnon is a species of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily , that is endemic to Sichuan , China .
Milgithea alboplagialis is a species of snout moth in the genus Milgithea .
Polygonum polymorphum ( knotweed ) is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family , native to Russia .
Melodinus acutiflorus is a species of vines , commonly named white - flowered melodinus , byamurra , or merangarra and constituting part of the plant family Apocynaceae .
Salea is a genus of arboreal , slow - moving , diurnal , insectivorous , egg - laying agamid lizards endemic to the Western Ghats of South India .
