Perrin 's beaked whale ( Mesoplodon perrini ) is the newest species of beaked whale to be described .
Toxicoscordion brevibracteatum ( syn . Zigadenus brevibracteatus ) is a species of flowering plant known by the common name desert deathcamas .
Chrotichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived in the Induan stage of the Early Triassic epoch .
Pardosa subalpina is a species of wolf spider found in Switzerland .
Ocheyoherpia is a genus of sterrofustian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like , marinemollusks .
Acinetobacter venetianus is a species of bacteria notable for degrading n - alkanes .
Tugali stewartiana is a species of medium - sized sea snail or limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the Family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Fire - coloured beetles are the beetles of the Pyrochroidae family , which includes the red cardinal beetles .
Pinus krempfii , or Krempf 's pine , is a rare species of pine , endemic to the central highlands of Vietnam in the Da Lat--
Pleurosternon is an extinct genus of cryptodire turtle from the late Jurassic period to the early Cretaceous period .
Phrynus marginemaculatus is a species of Amblypygid found in southern Florida , the Bahamas , Cuba , and Hispaniola .
Clarkia virgata is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Sierra clarkia .
Nosodendridae is a family of beetles , with only 67 species in four genera :
Diaspidinae is the largest subfamily of armored scale insects , with 252 genera .
Pseudoeurycea brunnata is a species of salamander in the Plethodontidae family .
Haustellum tweedianum , common name : the Tweed murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Anthonotha vignei is a species of tree in the Fabaceae family endemic to tropical West Africa .
Physaria hemiphysaria ( formerly Lesquerella hemiphysaria ) is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Intermountain bladderpod and skyline bladderpod .
Lepidobatrachus asper ( common name : Paraguay horned frog ; in Spanish : escuerzo ) is a species of frog in the Ceratophryidae family .
Chrysolophus is a genus of the pheasant family of birds .
Hieracium venosum ( Robin 's plantain , rattlesnakeweed , or rattlesnake hawkweed ) is a species of hawkweeds in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Pleuroceridae , common name pleurocerids , is a family of small to medium - sized freshwater snails , aquatic gilled gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cerithioidea . These snails have an operculum and typically a robust high - spired shell .
Layia septentrionalis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Colusa tidytips , or Colusa layia .
Antaresia is a genus of pythons , non - venomous snakes found in Australia .
Cellana sandwicensis , common name the yellow - foot opihi , is a species of edible true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Hypargyria impecuniosa is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypargyria .
Lasius interjectus , or larger yellow ant , is a species of ant belonging to the genus Lasius , and was formerly apart of the genus ( now a subgenus ) Acanthomyops .
Trapania africana is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae .
Brodiaea kinkiensis is a species of Brodiaea also with the common name San Clemente Island brodiaea .
Sphaeramia is a genus of cardinalfish .
Oulophyllia crispa , sometimes called the intermediate valley coral , is a species of stony coral in the family Merulinidae .
Skenea concordia , common name the beaded skenea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Arnica fulgens is a species of arnica known by the common names foothill arnica and hillside arnica .
The taimen ( Hucho taimen ) , also known as Siberian taimen and Siberian salmon , is a species of fish in the salmon family ( family Salmonidae ) of order Salmoniformes .
Paedocypris progenetica is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Sumatra ( Indonesia ) where it is found in peat swamps and blackwater streams .
Trogia venenata , also known as the little white mushroom , is a species of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family indigenous to Yunnan province , in southwest China .
Encephalartos friderici - guilielmi is a species of cycad that is native to Eastern Cape province and KwaZulu - Natal province of South Africa at elevations of 700 up to 1400 meters .
Plesioplatecarpus is an extinct genus of plioplatecarpine mosasaur known from the Late Cretaceous ( middle Coniacian to middle Santonian stage ) of the northern Gulf of Mexico and the Western Interior Basin of North America .
Salix columbiana common name Columbia River willow is a species of willow known only from the US states of Washington and Oregon .
Chicoreus denudatus , common name the branch - bearing murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Episteme adulatrix is a species of moth in the genus Episteme of the family Noctuidae .
Genlisea filiformis is a species of carnivorous plant in the Genlisea genus .
Cotoneaster newryensis is a species of flowering plant in the Rosaceae family that can be found in Sichuan and Yunnan provinces of China .
Paraereis javanica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraereis .
Deudorix is a large genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Old world ( including Australia ) .
Dielsantha is a genus of plants in the family Campanulaceae .
Keera is a genus of spiders , containing the sole species Keera longipalpis , found in New South Wales , Australia .
Euneomys is a genus of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Pitar cordatus , or the cordate venus clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
Neamia is a genus of cardinalfishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Ecklonia cava is an edible marine brown alga species found in the ocean off Japan and Korea .
Richmondoceras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod , essentially a Nautiloid , that lived in what would be North America during the Ordovician and Silurian from 449.5 - -443.7 mya , existing for approximately 5.8 million years .
Stenodynerus is a rather large genus of potter wasps whose distribution spans the Nearctic , Palearctic , Oriental and Neotropical regions .
Ctenomeristis shafferi is a species of snout moth in the genus Ctenomeristis .
Cynanchum auriculatum is a species of climbing vine swallowworts .
Canthidermis maculata , also known as rough triggerfish or spotted oceanic triggerfish , is a species of triggerfish native to the tropical and subtropical oceans worldiwide .
Brickellia oblongifolia ( Mojave brickellbush ) is North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Ericameria brachylepis is a North American species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common names chaparral goldenbush and boundary goldenbush .
Rieppeleon is a genus of small , typically brown chameleons found in forests and savannas in central East Africa ( extending slightly into adjacent DR Congo ) .
Paphiopedilum hirsutissimum is a species of orchid ranging from Assam to southern China .
The orange hairy chiton , Chaetopleura pertusa , is a species of chitons in the family Chaetopleuridae .
Halophryne is a genus of toadfishes found in the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
The Kluchor birch mouse ( Sicista kluchorica ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Brookesia confidens , also known as the leaf chameleon , is a newly discovered and one of the world 's smallest species of chameleons .
Gaura drummondii is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names Drummond 's beeblossom and scented gaura .
Qualea impexa is a species of plant in the Vochysiaceae family endemic to Peru .
The genus Bryceomys ( `` Bryce mouse '' , after Bryce Canyon National Park ) was named by Eaton J.G. in 1995 .
Amsonia tomentosa is a species of flowering plant native to the southwestern United States ( S California , S Nevada , Utah , Arizona , New Mexico , W Texas ) and northern Mexico ( Chihuahua ) .
Pseudocolus is a genus of fungi in the stinkhorn family .
Leiocephalus inaguae , commonly known as the Inaguae Curly - tailed Lizard , is a lizard species from the family of curly - tailed lizards ( Leiocephalidae ) .
Viola flettii is a species of violet known by the common name Olympic violet .
Anarhichas is a genus of wolffishes native to the northern Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Micropterix avarcella is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Zagulajev in 1994 , and is endemic to Russia .
Lapiedra is a genus of Western Mediterranean plants in the Amaryllis family .
Hypogeomys is a genus of rodents in the family Nesomyidae , found in Madagascar .
Leavenworthia stylosa is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names cedar gladecress or long - styled gladecress .
Asteropeia matrambody is a species of plant in the Asteropeiaceae family .
Laevaricella perlucens is a species of tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oleacinidae .
Suchonosaurus is an extinct genus of procolophonid reptile from the Late Permian of Russia .
Mangifera persiciformis or Peach Mango , is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Solanum parishii is a species of nightshade known by the common name Parish 's nightshade .
Nerodia clarkii clarkii , the Gulf salt marsh snake , is a subspecies of N. clarkii that is indigenous to the southeastern United States .
Lupinus succulentus is a species of lupine known by the common names hollowleaf annual lupine , arroyo lupine , and succulent lupine .
Arctodiaptomus michaeli is a species of copepod in the family Diaptomidae which is endemic to two lakes in Jammu and Kashmir , India .
Aloe arborescens ( krantz aloe , candelabra aloe ) is a species of flowering succulent perennial plant that belongs to the Aloe genus , which it shares with the well known and studied Aloe vera .
Agonum decorum is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae family , that prefers to live near the waters of North America .
The black turban snail or black tegula , scientific name Tegula funebralis , is a species of medium - sized sea snail with gills and an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tegulidae .
Adiantum bellum ( Bermuda Maidenhair Fern ) is a species of fern in the genus Adiantum ( maidenhairs ) , and is native to Bermuda .
Hipposideros rotalis , the Laotian leaf - nosed bat or Laotian roundleaf bat , is a species of bat from the family Rhinolophidae which is endemic to Bolikhamsai Province , Laos .
Cortinarius subrubrovelatus is a species of fungus in the large mushroom genus Cortinarius ( subgenus Phlagmacium ) .
Minquartia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the Olacaceae family containing the single species Minquartia guianensis ( also called Black Manwood or Huambula ) .
Sphaerotheriida ( from the Latin sphaerium = ball ) is an order of millipedes in the infraclass Pentazonia , sometimes known as giant pill millipedes .
Sthenopis auratus , the gold - spotted ghost moth , is a species of moth of the family Hepialidae .
Afrivoluta pringlei , commonly known as the pringle 's marginella , is a species of large deepwater sea snail with a glossy shell , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Marginellidae , the marginellids .
Austrochaperina is a genus of microhylid frogs found on New Guinea , New Britain and Australia .
Amegilla zonata , is a species of blue - banded bees belonging to the family Apidae , widely distributed in SE Asia , where it is often confused with the Australian species Amegilla cingulata .
Pseudonocardia is the type genus of the bacteria family Pseudonocardiaceae .
Lebronnecia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Malvaceae .
The bronze rock skink ( Trachylepis lacertiformis ) is a species of skink .
Didimus laevis is a species of beetles of the family Passalidae .
Quasianosteosaurus is an extinct genus of basal ichthyosaur known from the late Early Triassic ( late Olenekian stage ) of Spitsbergen of the Svalbard archipelago , Norway .
Hylarana gracilis or Gravenhorst 's frog is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Swiftia pallida is a species of gorgonian - type octocoral in the family Plexauridae sometimes known as the northern sea fan .
Rubroboletus rubrosanguineus is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae that is found in Europe .
Allium bigelovii , the New Mexico Wild Leek , is a plant species native to Arizona and southwestern New Mexico .
Saurogobio is a genus of cyprinid fish found in eastern Asia .
The Tien Shan birch mouse ( Sicista tianshanica ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Ophthalmemeopedus macrophthalmus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ophthalmemeopedus .
Anadenanthera is a genus of South American trees in the Legume family , Fabaceae .
Scirpus fluviatilis ( syn . Bolboschoenus fluviatilis , Schoenoplectus fluviatilis ) is a species of flowering plant in the Cyperaceae family .
Stephanospondylus is an extinct genus of diadectid reptiliomorph from the Early Permian of Germany .
Plectropomus is a genus of fishes in the Serranidae family .
Carex pseudocyperus is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name cyperus sedge or hop sedge .
Eotheroides is an extinct genus of Eocene sirenian .
Nembrotha rosannulata is a species of colorful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
†Helenoconcha sexdentata was a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
Gnaphosa alacris is a ground spider species found in France , Italy , Croatia and Morocco .
Chromis vanderbilti is a species of damselfish native to the Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean .
Amyema preissii , commonly known as wireleaf mistletoe , is a species of mistletoe , an epiphytic , hemiparasitic plant of the family Loranthaceae .
Abies pinsapo ( Spanish fir ) is a species of fir native to southern Spain and northern Morocco .
The Galaxiidae , also known by the anglicised name as galaxiids , are a family of mostly small freshwater fish in the Southern Hemisphere .
Thalassoleon is an extinct genus of large fur seal .
Smelowskia ovalis is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name alpine false candytuft .
Echeveria derenbergii , the painted - lady , is a species of flowering plant in the family Crassulaceae , endemic to Mexico .
Paraclinus stephensi , the Professor blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Mexico where it can be found at depths of from near the surface to 14 metres ( 46 ft ) .
Pinus nelsonii , Nelson 's pinyon , is a species of pine native to the mountains of northeastern Mexico , in Nuevo León , San Luis Potosí and Tamaulipas at 1,800 - -3,200 m altitude .
Rileymillerus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Late Triassic of Texas .
Gyrostigma rhinocerontis ( also known as the Rhinoceros stomach botfly ) is the largest fly species known in Africa .
Mugilogobius wilsoni , commonly known as Wilson 's mangrove goby , is a species of goby native to the waters of northern Australia .
Teucrium ajugaceum is a plant species in the family Lamiaceae .
Bolivaroscelis is a genus of praying mantis in the family Amorphoscelidae .
Scolopsis is a genus of threadfin breams native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Tricolia tingitana is a species of a small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Vimba vimba , called also the vimba bream , vimba , zanthe , or zarte , is a European fish species in the Cyprinidae family .
Bagrus orientalis is a species of fish in the Bagridae family .
The species Boffius splendidus is known from Lower Paleocene remains found in Hainin , Belgium .
Tradescantia bracteata , the longbract spiderwort , or prairie spiderwort , is a species of Tradescantia .
Cyclopygidae is a family of asaphid trilobites from the Ordovician .
Comitas anteridion is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropoda orthogastropoda in the family Cochlespiridae .
Neptunea pribiloffensis , common name the Pribilof whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Diplodon pfeifferi is a species of bivalve in the Hyriidae family .
Leptosiphon harknessii ( syn . Linanthus harknessii ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Harkness ' flaxflower .
Oedipina carablanca ( common name : Los Diamantes worm salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Nassarius acutus , common name the sharp nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Aesculus flava , the yellow buckeye , common buckeye , or sweet buckeye , is a species of deciduous tree .
Lordomyrma vanua ( named after its type locality Vanua Levu ) is a species of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Frullania intermedia is a liverwort species in the genus of Frullania .
Trachelipus dimorphus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Romania , Kosovo , Montenegro , Serbia and Vojvodina .
Tetracha carolina is a species of tiger beetle in the genus Tetracha .
Microbregma is a monotypic genus of beetles in the family Anobiidae containing the single species Microbregma emarginatum .
Hypolepis poeppigii is a fern species in the Dennstaedtiaceae family that has no common name .
Chrysauge eutelia is a species of snout moth in the genus Chrysauge .
Galeruca pomonae is a species of leaf beetle native to Europe that has been reported feeding on rosettes of Dipsacus .
The spider genus Spintharus occurs from the northeastern USA to Brazil , with one species found in Pakistan .
Diaethria clymena or Cramer 's Eighty - eight is a species of butterfly of the family Nymphalidae .
Gadilidae is a family of tusk shells in the order Dentaliida .
Alangium is a small genus of flowering plants .
Antrocaryon micraster is a species of flowering plant in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae .
Tricarpelema giganteum serves as the type species for the genus .
The species was previously classified as Phrynichthys wedli , then Paroneirodes wedli , before being renamed shortly after as Bufoceratias wedli .
Pyrausta laticlavia , the southern purple mint moth , is a species of moth of the Crambidae family .
Clathria is a genus of demosponge in the family Microcionidae .
Cirripectes chelomatus , the Lady Musgrave blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Paraschistura punjabensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Paraschistura .
Hyophorbe amaricaulis ( also known as Loneliest palm ) is a species of palm tree of the order Arecales , family Arecaceae , subfamily Arecoideae , tribe Hyophorbeae .
Festuca subuliflora is a species of grass known by the common name crinkleawn fescue .
Oreolalax omeimontis ( Omei lazy toad or Omei toothed toad ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Neohyparpalus parcepunctatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neohyparpalus .
Carabus exiguus lanzhouicus is a black - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Gansu , China .
Theileria is a genus of parasitic protozoan that belongs to the phylum Apicomplexa and is closely related to Plasmodium .
Dongusia is an extinct genus of rauisuchid reptile from the Middle Triassic of Russia .
Mallosia tristis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Azerbaijan , Iran and Turkey .
Cotoneaster elegans is a plant species in the genus Cotoneaster .
Nebria derkraatzi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the Chinese capital , Beijing .
Aralazhdarcho is a genus of azhdarchid pterosaur from the Santonian - early Campanian Late Cretaceous Bostobe Svita of Kazakhstan .
Triphasia trifolia ( syn . Limonia trifolia Burm . f. , Triphasia aurantiola Lour . ; also called limeberry , lime berry , or limoncitong kastila ) is a species of Triphasia in the family Rutaceae , native to tropical southeastern Asia in Malaysia , the Philippines and possibly elsewhere .
Xenos vesparum is an insect species , whose females are permanent entomophagous endoparasites of Polistes paper wasps .
Cheiragonidae is a small family of crabs , sometimes called helmet crabs , placed in its own superfamily , Cheriagonoidea .
Cyphoma signatum , common name : the Fingerprint Flamingo Tongue , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ovulidae , the ovulids , cowry allies or false cowries .
Odostomia virginica , common name the Virginia odostome , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Skvortzoviothrix terrestris is an algae species in the genus Skvortzoviothrix .
Nectriaster monacanthus is a species of sea star in the family Orestieridae .
Habromys is a genus of rodent in the family Cricetidae , found in Mexico and Central America .
Acacia denticulosa , commonly known as sandpaper wattle , is a species of Acacia native to the south - west of Western Australia .
Monodactylus sebae , the African moony , is a species of moonyfish native to fresh , brackish and marine waters from the eastern Atlantic , ranging from the Canary Islands down to Angola .
The Siberian brown lemming ( Lemmus sibiricus ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae found in the Russian Federation .
Pippenalia is a genus of Mexican plants in the groundsel tribe within the sunflowerfamily .
The Eurasian wolf ( Canis lupus lupus ) , also known as the common wolf or Middle Russian forest wolf , is a subspecies of grey wolf native to Europe and the forest and steppe zones of the former Soviet Union .
Xanthoidea is a superfamily of crabs , comprising the three families Xanthidae , Panopeidae and Pseudorhombilidae .
Lysimachia vulgaris ( garden loosestrife , yellow loosestrife or garden yellow loosestrife ) is a species of herbaceous perennial plants in the genus Lysimachia native to wetlands , damp meadows and forests of Eurasia .
Quercus austrina , the bastard white oak or bluff oak , is an oak species that is endemic to the southeastern United States from Mississippi to the Carolinas , with a few isolated populations in Arkansas .
Trifolium glomeratum is a species of clover known by the common names clustered clover and bush clover .
Petasites frigidus , the Arctic sweet coltsfoot or Arctic butterbur , is a species of Petasites native to Arctic to cool temperate regions of the Northern Hemisphere in northern Europe , northern Asia and northern North America .
Maculatoscelis gilloni is a species of praying mantis found in Côte d'Ivoire .
Bermudagidiella bermudiensis is a species of crustacean in the family Bogidiellidae .
The Aglaopheniidae are a family of cnidarians within the class Hydrozoa .
Alangium chinense is a species of flowering plant in the Cornaceae family .
Auricularia is a genus of jelly fungi in the family Auriculariaceae .
Allodapula is a genus of bees in the family Apidae , subfamily Xylocopinae .
Scoliopus hallii , the Oregon fetid adderstongue , is a plant species endemic to western Oregon .
Guzmania coriostachya is a species in the genus Guzmania , and is native to Costa Rica , Panama , Colombia , Venezuela and Ecuador .
Hypacrosaurus ( meaning `` near the highest lizard '' ( Greek υπο- , hypo- = less + ακρος , akros , high ) , because it was almost but not quite as large as Tyrannosaurus ) was a genus of duckbill dinosaur similar in appearance to Corythosaurus .
Exguiana is a genus of snout moths in the subfamily Phycitinae .
†Carelia olivacea was a species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Spinochariesthes albomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinochariesthes .
Parapterois heterura , the blackfoot firefish , is a species of scorpionfish widely distributed on the southeastern coast of Africa as well as off Japan and in Indonesia where it is usually found in sheltered coastal bays with a soft bottom , such as fine sand or mud .
Acer shirasawanum ( Shirasawa 's Maple or Fullmoon Maple ; Japanese : オオイタヤメイゲツ ooitayameigetsu ) is a species of maple native to Japan , on central and southern Honshū ( Fukushima Prefecture southwards ) , Shikoku , and Kyūshū .
Anderson 's four - eyed opossum ( Philander andersoni ) is an opossum species from South America .
Barnesoceras is a moderately large , Lower Ordovician ellesmoerceratid genus with a simple , but strongly cyctoconic shell that expands in the vertical dimension more rapidly than in the horizontal , resulting in its being laterally compressed .
Elaeocarpus apiculatus is a species of flowering plant in the Elaeocarpaceae family .
The Asian murex ( Chicoreus asianus ) is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Monachosorum is a genus of ferns described as a genus in 1848 .
Amandinea maritima is a species of lichen in the family Caliciaceae .
Doxocopa laure , common name Silver Emperor , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Carex muskingumensis is a species of sedge known by the common name Muskingum sedge .
Agrilus biguttatus is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the jewel beetles .
Shorea iliasii ( also called Yellow Meranti ) is a woody species in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Picea likiangensis is a species of spruce found in Bhutan and China .
Pistius truncatus is a species of crab spiders belonging to the family Thomisidae .
Lysimachia maxima is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae known by the common name Pelekunu Trail yellow loosestrife .
Holaxonia is a suborder of soft corals , a member of the phylum Cnidaria .
Heteropoda cervina , commonly called the brown huntsman , is a large species of spider in the Sparassidae family often found in leaf litter in Australia .
Pyrrocoma lucida is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names sticky goldenweed and sticky pyrrocoma .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Valdensinia heterodoxa .
Hemiargus is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae found in North America and South America .
Hainokisaruzo is a genus of Asian weevils , established in 2005 by Hiraku Yoshitake and Enzo Colonnelli .
Vanacampus is a genus of pipefishes endemic to the ocean waters around the Australian coasts .
Balitora meridionalis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Balitora .
It is the only species found in the genus Oryxis .
Nyctanthes arbor - tristis ( Night - flowering Jasmine ) is a species of Nyctanthes , native to South Asia and Southeast Asia .
Zacanthoides is an extinct Cambrian genus of trilobite .
Araneus angulatus is a species of orb - weaving spider found in the Palaearctic .
Rhacodactylus is a genus of medium to large geckos of the family Diplodactylidae .
The sunfish are a family ( Centrarchidae ) of freshwater ray - finned fish belonging to the order Perciformes .
Notylia punctata is a species of orchid that occurs from Trinidad , northern Venezuela , and the State of Pará in Brazil .
Stomatella impertusa , common name the strigose stomatella or the elongate false ear shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Larachelus is an extinct genus of basal pan - cryptodiran turtle known from the Early Cretaceous ( late Hauterivian to early Barremian stage ) of Spain .
Polygala lewtonii is a rare species of flowering plant in the milkwort family known by the common name Lewton 's polygala , or Lewton 's milkwort .
Calamanthus is a genus of bird in the Acanthizidae family .
Pariambus is a genus of amphipod crustaceans comprising the two species Pariambus typicus and Pariambus minutus .
Streptomyces africanus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Cape Town in South Africa .
Petrocosmea forrestii is a species of flowering plant in the family Gesneriaceae native to China , and sometimes cultivated as a houseplant .
Sporothrix is a ubiquitous genus of soil - dwelling fungus discovered by Schenck in 1898 and studied in more detail by Hektoen and Perkins .
Porcellio zarcoi is a species of woodlouse in the Porcellionidae family that is endemic to Madeira .
Vini is a genus of birds endemic to the islands of the tropical Pacific .
Lomatium dasycarpum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name woollyfruit desertparsley .
Pyrenomonas is a genus of cryptomonad .
Eriphiidae is a family of crabs , comprising three genera :
Vasconcellea parviflora is a species of Vasconcella found in Ecuador .
Neohipparion is an extinct genus of equid , from the Neogene ( Miocene to Pliocene ) of North America and Central America .
Leontopodium discolor , known as Ezo - usuyuki - sō or Rebun - usuyuki - sō in Japan , is a species of Edelweiss native to alpine areas of Hokkaidō .
Paracanthocobitis linypha also known as the Sewing needle zipper loach is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Paracanthocobitis .
Pacifastacus nigrescens , the sooty crayfish , was a species of crayfish in the family Astacidae .
Nephrolenellus is an extinct genus of trilobite , fossil marine arthropods , of relatively small size ( sagittal length of cephalon rarely exceeds 11 mm ) .
Celastrina idella , the American holly azure , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
Oxalis purpurea is a species of flowering plant in the woodsorrel family known by the common name purple woodsorrel .
Sphinctomyrmex stali ( named after the Swedish entomologist Carl Stål ) is a Neotropical species of ants in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Allium fetisowii is a plant species native to Kazakhstan , Uzbekistan , Xinjiang , Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan in Central Asia .
Eurystomus is a genus of roller , one of the two genera in that family of birds .
Osteochilus kerinciensis is a fish species in the genus Crossocheilus from Sumatra .
Pethia punctata is a species of cyprinid fish found in streams and ponds of the Western Ghats of India .
Glossaulax aulacoglossa is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Naticidae , the moons snails .
Salix chaenomeloides is a species of willow native to Japan , Korea and China .
Samolus valerandi is a species of water pimpernel native to a very wide area across Europe , Africa , Asia , Australia , and the Americas .
Scaphyglottis stellata is a species of orchid occurring from Central America to tropical South America .
Bisonalveus is represented by two known species :
Hedylopsoidea was defined as a taxonomic superfamily of sea slugs , mostly marine gastropod mollusks within the informal group Opisthobranchia according to the taxonomy of Bouchet & Rocroi ( 2005 ) .
Homo sapiens ( Latin : `` wise person '' ) is the binomial nomenclature ( also known as the scientific name ) for the only extant human species .
Curculio glandium is a species of weevil known as the acorn weevil .
Helcystogramma ceriochrantum was synonymized with Helcystogramma trijunctum on the basis of collected specimens of these species in the same place and time , and without other comments .
Erythroseris is a genus of African plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Paphiopedilum liemianum is a species of orchid endemic to northern Sumatra ( Kg . Susuk ) .
The Dermatemydidae are a family of turtles .
Diemeniana is a genus of cicada in the cicadettini tribe of the Cicadinae subfamily native to Australia .
Strabena is an Afrotropical butterfly genus endemic to Madagascar from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae .
Cilicitis phaeocremna is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Cilicitis .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pureke zelandicum .
Aechmea fendleri is a species of bromeliad in the genus Aechmea .
Serrasalmus neveriensis is a species of serrasalmid found in South America in the Coastal rivers of Venezuela .
Nepenthes maxima ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˈmæksɨmə/ ; from Latin : maximus `` greatest '' ) , the Great Pitcher - Plant , is a carnivorous pitcher plant species of the genus Nepenthes .
Doryrhamphus aurolineatus is a species of flagtail pipefish from the genus Doryrhamphus that occurs in the Western Indian Ocean .
Iris glaucescens is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Iris .
Elymus sierrae ( orth . var . Elymus sierrus ) is a species of wild rye known by the common name Sierra wild rye .
Kalidos mangokyanus is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ariophantidae .
Plumeria rubra is a deciduous plant species belonging to the genus Plumeria .
Dinocardium robustum , common name the Atlantic giant cockle , is a species of large saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Desmodus is a genus of bats often referred to as the vampire bats .
Eusirus holmi is a species of amphipod in the family Eusiridae .
The plant genus Caylusea is a small group of plants found in parts of Africa and India .
Licnodamaeidae is a family of mites ; nymphs retain their moulted exuviae until adulthood .
Daphnella lymneiformis is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae .
Iris ser . Longipetalae is a series of the genus Iris , in Iris subg .
Harpalus caspius is a species of black coloured ground beetle that can be found in Near East and the Palaearctic ecozone .
Anteaeolidiella takanosimensis , is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch .
Brisaster kerguelenensis is a species of sea urchins of the Family Schizasteridae .
Muraenesox is a small genus of eels found throughout the Indo - Pacific .
Rhiodenticulatus is an extinct genus of Early Permian captorinid known from Rio Arriba County , New Mexico of the United States .
Brachyplatys is a genus of shield bugs belonging to the family Plataspidae .
Psamateia is an extinct genus of moths within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing one species , Psamateia calipsa , which is known from the Crato Formation in Brazil .
Tamenes sarda is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Tamenes .
Vanda luzonica is a species of vanda , a flower of the orchid family .
Epiblapsilon tuberculatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Epiblapsilon .
Apteronotus is a genus of weakly electric knifefish in the family Apteronotidae , distinguished by the presence of a tiny caudal fin .
Kottelatia brittani is a species of cyprinid fish that occurs in the Southeast Asian nations of Indonesia and Malaysia .
Lycastrirhyncha is a genus of 5 neotropical flower flies or hoverflies .
Indocalamus is a East Asian genus of bamboo in the grass family , native to China and to northern Indochina .
Nephrurus deleani , a gecko , is a species of lizard in the family Carphodactylidae .
The Daghestan pine vole ( Microtus daghestanicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Arnica unalaschcensis is an Asian and North American species of arnica in the sunflower family .
Cynara is a genus of thistle - like perennial plants in the sunflower family .
Leioproctus fulvescens is a species of bee native to the South Island of New Zealand .
Allium alabasicum is a species of onion native to Nei Mongol ( Inner Mongolia ) in China .
Sumatratarda diehlii is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Sumatratarda .
The Empelinae are a subfamily of rove beetles ; their biology is virtually unknown .
The ripsaw catfish ( Oxydoras niger ) or cuiu cuiu is a species of thorny catfish native to the Amazon , Essequibo and São Francisco basins in Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , Guyana , Peru and Venezuela .
Virilastacus is a genus of freshwater burrowing crayfish species endemic to Chile .
Oelandia is an extinct genus of basal molluscs of the family helcionellid from the Middle Cambrian of Sweden , China and North America .
Dodecatheon meadia is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae , native to North America .
Typha albida is a plant species endemic to Afghanistan .
Oreoleuciscus is a genus of medium to large cyprinid freshwater fish which is only found in Mongolia and adjacent parts of Russia .
Kapal is a monotypic genus of shelled octopods comprising the species Kapal batavus .
Caulanthus californicus ( syn . Stanfordia californica ) is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names California jewelflower and St. Francis cabbage .
Clavelina cylindrica is a species of tunicate in the genus Clavelina .
Bulinus succinoides is a species of freshwater snail , a gastropod in the Planorbidae family .
Redigobius bikolanus , the Speckled goby , is a species of goby native to marine , fresh and brackish waters along the coasts of Asia from Japan to Australia out to the Pacific islands of New Caledonia and Vanuatu and along the coast of South Africa and the Seychelles .
It consists of only one species , Pseudoneaveia jacksoni , which is found in the Republic of Congo .
Anchomomys is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Europe and Africa during the middle Eocene .
Dorymyrmex bureni also known as pyramid ant is a species of ant in the genus Dorymyrmex .
Trichopsetta is a genus of small lefteye flounders native to the western Atlantic Ocean .
Ornithogalum nutans , known as drooping star - of - Bethlehem , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to Europe and South West Asia .
Paphiopedilum malipoense is a species of orchid commonly known as the Jade Slipper Orchid .
Porterella is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the bellflower family containing the single species Porterella carnosula , which is known by the common name fleshy porterella , or simply porterella .
Leucopholiota decorosa is a species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family of mushrooms .
Ostrea stentina is a species of oysters , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Ostreidae , the oysters .
Cyathea elmeri is a species of tree fern native to the Philippines , Talaud Islands , and northern Sulawesi , where it grows in forest at an altitude of 500 - 1400 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and 5 - 10 m tall .
Neogyps is an extinct monotypic genus of Aegypiinae from the Pleistocene .
Fragaria yezoensis is a species of strawberry native to the eastern side of the Japanese island of Hokkaidō , and the adjacent Kuril Islands and Sakhalin in Russia .
Eukrohniidae is a family of arrow worms .
Some 26 species names have been applied to populations of the Mexican woodrat and are now considered synonyms .
Fomes fasciatus is species of fungus in the Polyporaceae family .
Vokesimurex chrysostoma , common name the gold - mouthed murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Acanthosaura capra is a species of Agamid lizards : commonly known as the mountain horned dragon , it is also called the Indo - Chinese spiny lizard or the green pricklenape .
Cariniana ianeirensis is a species of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family .
Kraussia rugulosa is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Kraussia .
Laccophilus is a genus of water beetle found in nearly every temperate or tropical region in the world including but not limited to Europe , the Near East , the Nearctic , North Africa and the Oriental region .
Calathus asturiensis is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in France and Spain .
Archasteridae is a family of starfish found in shallow waters in the tropical Indo - Pacific region .
Savannosiphon is a genus of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae , first described as a new species in 1980 .
Tanichthys micagemmae is a species of freshwater fish .
Ebala is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the subfamily Ebalinae , family Murchisonellidae .
Atrosalarias fuscus , known commonly as the Dusky Blenny , is a species of marine fish in the family Blenniidae .
Gladiolus murielae is a species of flowering plant in the family Iridaceae , native to eastern Africa , from Ethiopia to Malawi .
It contains the single species Hoppiana aspasta , which is found in Colombia .
Pseudogarypus synchrotron is an extinct species of pseudoscorpion in the family Pseudogarypidae known from only two Eocene fossils found in Europe .
Geum bulgaricum is a flowering plant species native to eastern Europe and has small , bell - like yellow blossoms .
Mahonia ehrenbergii is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1847 .
Euterpnosia is a genus of cicada native to the island of Formosa , the Ryukyu Archipelago , Japan , Hainan and mainland Asia - China , Bhutan , Nepal and Vietnam .
Ctenoides ales is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Limidae , the file clams .
Archamia bleekeri also known as the Gon 's cardinalfish , is a species of fish in the family Apogonidae , the cardinalfishes .
Iridoviridae is a family of viruses with double - stranded DNA genomes .
Bronchocela smaragdina , also commonly known as Günther 's bloodsucker , is a Southeast Asian species of agamid lizard .
Conasprella pagoda , common name the pagoda cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Pecten maximus , common name the `` great scallop '' or `` king scallop '' , is a species of scallop , an edible saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pectinidae .
Laemolyta is a genus of headstander found in the Orinoco and Amazon Basins in South America .
Heliconia riopalenquensis is a species of plant in the Heliconiaceae family .
Carditidae is a family of marine bivalve clams of the order Carditoida , which was long included in the Veneroida .
Notoxus monoceros is a black and brown species of beetle that is about 4 millimeters long and resmebles ants .
Chaenophryne is a genus of dreamers .
Dinophysis acuta is a species of flagellated planktons belonging to the genus Dinophysis .
Otatea , called weeping bamboo , is a genus of clumping bamboos in the grass family , native to Mexico , Central America , and Colombia .
Anodonthyla jeanbai is an arboreal species of frog in the family Microhylidae .
Pulicaria is a genus of flowering plant in the sunflower family , native to Europe , Asia , and Africa .
Adamantinia is a monotypic genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) , described in 2004 by Cássio van den Berg and Cezar Neubert Gonçalves .
Beddomeia briansmithi is a species of very small freshwater snail that has a gill and an operculum , an aquatic operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Robuloidacea is a superfamily included in the Protista order Lagenida in which the test wall is either not secondarily lamellar or is only slightly so , as in later taxa .
Firmiana ( parasoltree ) is a genus of flowering plant in the Malvaceae family , formerly placed in the now defunct Sterculiaceae .
Eudihammus granulatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Eudihammus .
Paradiexia pellita is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paradiexia .
The type ( and only known ) species is Jinzhousaurus yangi .
Ohmdenosaurus ( meaning `` Ohmden lizard '' ) is the name given to a genus of herbivorous dinosaur from the Early Jurassic .
Botrychium ascendens is a species of fern known by the common names triangle - lobe moonwort and upswept moonwort .
Chloroclystis filata , the filata moth , is a species of moth of the family Geometridae .
Pritchardia schattaueri , the lands of papa pritchardia or Schattauer 's Loulu , is a species of palm tree in the genus Pritchardia that is endemic to mixed mesic forests on the southwestern part of island of Hawaiʻi , near Kona .
Lovoa trichilioides ( also called African walnut , Congowood , dibetou or tigerwood ) is a species of plant in the Meliaceae family .
Chorizanthe obovata is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name spoonsepal spineflower .
Chrysomyxa abietis , Spruce needle rust is a species of rust fungi in the Coleosporiaceae family that is native to eastern Europe ( including Siberia ) and northern Asia .
Manemergus was described in 2005 and contains only one species , M. anguirostris .
Ghost crabs are semiterrestrial crabs of the subfamily Ocypodinae .
Neoplecostomus franciscoensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the headwaters of the Das Velhas and Paraopeba River basins .
Kentrosaurus ( /ˌkɛntroʊˈsɔːrəs/ KEN - tro - SAWR - əs ) is a genus of stegosaurian dinosaur from the Late Jurassic of Tanzania .
Liatris cylindracea , also known as barrelhead gayfeather , cylindrical blazing star , or Ontario blazing star , is a plant species in the aster family Asteraceae and genus Liatris .
Ranularia caudata , common name the bent - neck triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Dicerca divaricata is a species of black coloured beetle from Chrysochroinae subfamily which is 15 - -22 millimetres ( 0.59 - -0.87 in ) long and is found throughout West Virginia .
Mastigopterus imperator is a species of cusk - eel found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans where it occurs at depths of from 394 to 2,365 metres ( 1,293 to 7,759 ft ) .
Braunsapis flaviventris is a species of bee belonging to the family Apidae subfamily Apinae .
Ectrepopterus uruguayensis is a species of characin only known from streams in Uruguay .
Phasianotrochus bellulus , common name the necklace shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The Thiotrichales are an order of Proteobacteria , including Thiomargarita namibiensis , the largest known bacterium .
Astranthium integrifolium , entireleaf western daisy or Eastern Western - daisy , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Conus cervus , common name the pallisade cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The new genus Polazzodus was erected based on a number of autapomorphies that distinguished it from similar pycnodontid fish .
Omalisus fontisbellaquaei is a species of beetle belonging to the family Omalisidae .
Bertiella mucronata is a species of Bertiella , a type of cestode known to cause Bertielliasis .
Buckinghamia celsissima , commonly known as the ivory curl , is a species of trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Oryza longistaminata is a perennial species of grass from the same genus as cultivated rice ( O. sativa ) .
Ophiocordycipitaceae is a family of parasitic fungi in the Ascomycota , class Sordariomycetes .
Paragorgia arborea is a species of coral in the family Paragorgiidae , commonly known as the bubblegum coral .
Mentzelia congesta is a species of flowering plants in the family Loasaceae known by the common name united blazingstar .
Stephanomeria pauciflora is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names brownplume wirelettuce , few - flowered wirelettuce , and prairie skeletonplant .
Dictyotaceae is large family of brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) .
Eucalyptus cambageana , commonly known as the Dawson River blackbutt or Coowarra box , is a species of eucalypt native to eastern Australia .
Pritchardia lowreyana , the Molokai pritchardia , is a species of fan palm that is endemic to Hawaii in the United States .
Lepisosteus is a genus of gars in the family Lepisosteidae .
Cecina manchurica is a species of sea snail that has a gill and an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Cancelloxus burrelli , the Slender platanna - klipfish , is a species of clinid found in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean along the South African coast from the Orange River to Algoa Bay in South Africa .

Astarte undata , or the waved astarte , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Astartidae .
Rubus centralis , the Illinois dewberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Cycas cairnsiana is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to northern Australia in northern Queensland on the Newcastle Range .
Steatogenys is a genus of bluntnose knifefishes found in tropical South America .
Allium therinanthum or summer garlic is a species of garlic that is found in the Mount Hermon area in Israel .
Rubus lambertianus is a flowering plant species in the genus Rubus found in Southern China ( including Hainan ) , Taiwan , Japan , and Thailand .
Calluella is a genus of microhylid frogs found in Southeastern Asia .
Deinacanthon urbanianum is a species in the genus Deinacanthon .
Ecsenius sellifer , known commonly as the Saddle blenny in Guam , or the Saddle clown blenny in Micronesia , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Baryancistrus is a genus of freshwater Loricariid catfish .
Mercurialis annua is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family known by the common name annual mercury .
Symphyglossum sanguineum is a species of flowering plant in the Orchidaceae family .
The Indian wolf ( Canis lupus pallipes ) is a subspecies of grey wolf which ranges from Israel to the Indian Subcontinent .
Pentacalia todziae is a plant species endemic to Perú , known only from San Martín Province .
Burying beetles or sexton beetles ( genus Nicrophorus ) are the best - known members of the family Silphidae ( carrion beetles ) .
Erythronium elegans is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Coast Range fawnlily and elegant fawnlily .
Eulaema is a genus of large - bodied euglossine bees that occur primarily in the Neotropics .
Trichanthemis is a genus of Central Asian plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
The Skeneopsidae are a family of very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Aglaia cucullata ( also called Pacific Maple ) is a species of plant in the Meliaceae family .
Nectoteuthis pourtalesi is a bathybenthic species of bobtail squid native to the tropical western Atlantic Ocean , specifically Florida and the Antilles .
Thymus vulgaris ( common thyme , German thyme , garden thyme or just thyme ) is a species of flowering plant in the mint family Lamiaceae , native to southern Europe from the western Mediterranean to southern Italy .
Alsodes montanus is a species of frog in the Alsodidae family found in Chile and possibly Argentina .
Hypochaeris chillensis ( sometimes spelled Hypochoeris ) also known as Brazilian cat 's ear is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
The Cassin 's honeybird ( Prodotiscus insignis ) , also known as the Cassin 's honeyguide , is a species of bird in the Indicatoridae family .
Dracocephalum rupestre is a plant species in the genus Dracocephalum , endemic to China .
Bohadschia argus , the leopard sea cucumber , is a species of marine invertebrate in the family Holothuriidae .

Caribbean pipefish ( Syngnathus caribbaeus ) is a species of the pipefishes .
Hanseniaspora is a genus of yeasts .
Zammara is a genus of cicadas .
Meganisoptera is an extinct order of very large to gigantic insects , occasionally called griffinflies .
The Pygmy wisp , ( Agriocnemis pygmaea ) , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Branchinecta gaini is a species of fairy shrimp from Antarctica and Patagonia .
Eocallionymus papilio , the Painted stinkfish , is a species of dragonet endemic to the Indian Ocean coasts of Australia and Tasmania where it is found at a depth of about 50 metres ( 160 ft ) .
Mellita quinquiesperforata ( Leske , 1778 ) is a tropical species of sand dollar , a flat , round marine animal related to sea urchins , starfish , and other echinoderms .
Antennaria stenophylla is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name narrowleaf pussytoes .
Leucostoma dapsile is a North American species of fly in the family Tachinidae .
Shibataea kumasaca , the ruscus - leaf bamboo or ruscus bamboo , is a species of bamboo .
Hermine Haselböck ( born 7 March 1967 in Melk , Lower Austria ) is an Austrian mezzo - soprano in opera , concert and lied .
Roberta Invernizzi ( born Milan 1966 ) is an Italian soprano .
Omar Ebrahim ( born 6 September 1956 in Greasbrough , Rotherham , South Yorkshire ) is an English baritone vocalist and actor .
Trebor Edwards ( born 1939 ) is a Welsh tenor , best known to Welsh - speaking audiences .
Isabelle Poulenard ( born 5 July 1961 ) is a soprano .
Neil Shicoff ( born June 2 , 1949 ) is an American Jewish opera singer and cantor known for his lyric tenor singing and his dramatic , emotional acting .
Ekkehard Wlaschiha ( born May 28 , 1938 ) is a German operatic baritone who specializes in Wagnerian villains of the `` howling - and - spitting '' type , such as Alberich , Klingsor , Friedrich von Telramund , Don Pizarro , and Kaspar .
Sarah Crane ( born 9 September 1972 in Brisbane ) is an Australian operatic soprano .
Rinat Shaham ( Hebrew : רינת שחם‎ ) is an Israeli born mezzo - soprano who has received numerous accolades for her international operatic , concert and recital performances .
David Gamrekeli ( Georgian : დავით გამრეკელი , 27 July 1911 -- 29 November 1977 ) was a Georgian baritone opera singer .
Francia White ( 1909 - October 22 , 1984 ) was an American soprano who had an active career in concerts , operas , operettas , radio , television , and film during the late 1920s through the 1940s .
Frederick Ranalow ( 7 November 1873 -- 8 December 1953 ) was an Irish baritone who was distinguished in opera , oratorio , and musical theatre , but whose name is now principally associated with the role of Captain Macheath in the ballad opera The Beggar 's Opera , which he sang close to 1,500 times .
Richard Torigi ( October 30 , 1917 -- April 6 , 2010 ) was an American baritone and voice teacher .
Elizabeth Amsden ( March 27 , 1881 , Boston -- July 20 , 1966 , New York City ) was an American operatic soprano and actress .
Željko Lučić ( born 24 February 1968 ) is a Serbian operatic baritone who has had an active international career since 1993 .
Dame Maggie Teyte , DBE ( 17 April 1888 -- 26 May 1976 ) was an English operatic soprano and interpreter of French art song .
Kurt Rydl ( born October 8 , 1947 ) is an Austrian operatic bass ( basso profondo ) .
Adele Addison ( born July 24 , 1925 in Springfield , Massachusetts ) is an African - American lyric soprano who was an acclaimed figure in the classical music world during the 1950s and 1960s .
Friedrich Weidemann ( 1 January 1871 -- 30 January 1919 ) was a German baritone who was a leading singer at the Vienna Court Opera ( Wiener Hofoper ) from 1903 until his death .
Arthur Newman ( 1908 -- August 6 , 2000 ) was an American operatic baritone and actor .
Hans Hopf ( August 2 , 1916 , Nuremberg - June 25 , 1993 , Munich ) was a German operatic tenor , one of the leading heldentenors of the immediate postwar period .
Anneliese Rothenberger ( 19 June 1924 -- 24 May 2010 ) was a German operatic soprano who had an active international performance career which spanned from 1943 to 1983 .
Fredrika Stenhammar , née Andrée , ( 19 September 1836 in Visby -- 7 October 1880 ) , was a Swedish singer ( soprano ) .
Leo Nucci ( born 16 April 1942 ) is an Italian operatic baritone , particularly suited to Verdi roles .
Annelies Kupper ( 21 July 1906 - 8 December 1987 ) , was a German operatic soprano , particularly associated with Mozart and the German repertory .
James Frederick Keel ( 8 May 1871 -- 9 August 1954 ) was an English composer of art songs , baritone singer and academic .
Birgit Finnilä ( born 20 January 1931 ) is a Swedish contralto and opera singer .
Franca Mattiucci is an Italian operatic mezzo - soprano who had an active international career from 1963 - 1987 .
Maria Jeritza ( 6 October 1887 -- 10 July 1982 ) was a celebrated Czech soprano singer , long associated with the Vienna State Opera ( 1912 - -1935 ) and the Metropolitan Opera ( 1921 - -1932 and 1951 ) .
Albert Lance ( 12 July 1925 -- 15 May 2013 ) was an Australian tenor , also holding French citizenship .
Hana Blažíková ( born 2 December 1980 ) is a Czech soprano and harpist .
Nicolai Gedda ( born Harry Gustaf Nikolai Gädda ; 11 July 1925 ) is a Swedish operatic tenor .
Harolyn Blackwell ( born November 23 , 1955 ) is an African - American lyric coloratura soprano who has performed in many of the world 's finest opera houses , concert halls , and theaters in operas , oratorios , recitals , and Broadway musicals .
Jean Morère ( 6 October 1836 -- February 1887 ) was a French operatic tenor , active from 1861 to 1871 .
Heinrich Schlusnus ( August 6 , 1888 -- June 18 , 1952 ) was Germany 's foremost lyric baritone of the period between World War I and World War II . He sang opera and lieder with equal distinction .
Carla Martinis ( 19 January 1922 -- 9 August 2010 ) was a Croatian operatic soprano particularly associated with the Italian repertoire .
Wanda Brister ( born August 12 , 1957 ) is an American operatic mezzo - soprano and voice teacher .
George Perren ( 1827 - 1909 ) was an English tenor active in both concert and opera .
Pumeza Matshikiza ( born in Lady Frere , often billed professionally as simply Pumeza , is a South - African operatic soprano .
Rudolf Christ ( 20 March 1916 in Vienna -- 20 April 1982 in Vienna ) was an Austrian tenor concert and opera singer .
Mark Padmore is a British tenor appearing in concerts , recitals , and opera .
Helen Boatwright ( November 17 , 1916 -- December 1 , 2010 ) was an American soprano who specialized in the performance of American song , recorded the first full - length album of songs by composer Charles Ives and had a career that spanned more than five decades .
Julius Patzak ( 9 April 1898 -- 26 January 1974 ) was an Austrian tenor distinguished in operatic and concert work .
Raquel Andueza ( born Pamplona ) is a Spanish soprano .
Paul Plishka ( born August 28 , 1941 ) is an American operatic bass .
Michéal Castaldo ( born September 25 , 1962 ) is an Italian - born classical crossover tenor , music producer and composer .
Norma Burrowes ( born 24 April 1944 ) is an Irish coloratura soprano , particularly associated with Handel and Mozart roles .
Madelyn Renee is an American soprano formerly known as Madelyn Renée Monti .
Spiro Malas ( born January 28 , 1933 in Baltimore , Maryland ) is a Greek - American bass - baritone opera singer .
Scipio Colombo ( May 25 , 1910 -- April 13 , 2002 ) was an Italian dramatic baritone , and was known for his abilities as a musician and singing - actor .
Gwendolyn Killebrew ( born August 26 , 1939 ) is an American operatic contralto who has worked in Germany and internationally , including the Metropolitan Opera and the Bayreuth Festival .
Roy Cornelius Smith is an American operatic tenor , from Big Stone Gap , Virginia .
Günther Treptow ( October 22 , 1907 in Berlin -- March 28 , 1981 in Berlin ) was a German operatic tenor , best known for Wagner roles .
Alexis Dupont ( 1796 , or 1798 according to his death certificate -- 29 May 1874 ) was a French operatic tenor who sang at the Opéra - Comique from 1821 to 1823 and the Paris Opera from 1826 to 1841 .
James Maddalena ( born 1954 ) is an American baritone who is chiefly associated with contemporary American opera .
Constance Hauman ( born 1961 ) is a soprano .
Aglaja Orgeni , real name Anna Maria von Görger St. Jörgen ( 17 December 1841 -- 15 March 1926 ) , was a Hungarian operatic coloratura soprano .
Harold Powell Lloyd ( known as Powell Lloyd ) ( 1900 -- 1987 ) was an English operatic tenor and opera director and producer .
Arijana Marić Gigliani ( pronounced ( arijǎːna mǎːritɕ dʑiʎâːni ) ; born 27 February 1979 ) is a Croatian - Bosnian opera singer ( dramatic soprano ) .
Serena Daolio ( born June 21 , 1972 in Carpi , Italy ) is an Italian soprano singer .
